One thing for sure, the cold cut prosciutto is good here. I like to have a few cut and go with the rose.  I got a bottle of Italian wine. It is good enough. They do have other Italian red. But I am interested on their rose. 

The store also has series of refrigerators that selling home made item. You should check it out.

Very interesting Mexican Bakery. It is tuck away at the strip plaza behind a building. You need to pay attention to find it. This bakery offer many interesting pastries, cake, jello, churros. The price is good. 

We got tamales there 4 for$5. The tamales is bean base with pork. It is quite good after heating up. It will be cheap lunch if you go with it. I also got some churros and dusted sugar pastry. These items are delicious. The cake is moist and great flavor. I have pound cake and coffee cake both are great. 

They sell the new year six cake Rosca de Reyes to celebrate the Epiphany. It is ring cake for sale. It is great to have a Taste of the cake. They also has the coconut pastry with cherry on top. Great dessert. Don't forget their refrigerator jello. Please check them out.

I like the new establishment of Zukku. The new restaurant set up is beautiful with high ceilings with beautiful wall decoration. The chair also decorative and fit the entire restaurant interior. This is something they were not able to do at Armateurwork. I have to give them an A in the interior. 

They welcome us with expandable hot tower. It is a good show to begin the meal. We started with the Centipede roll. It is a spicy tuna top with hamachi. It look delicious but I think their spicy tuna need some work. May be mixed in the sesame oil and quail egg to mixed in will better. 

I do like grilled hamachi collard. It has good large pieces. The dressing is good and complemented the collard. We also has one chicken and one steak Yakitori. Those have good flavor. The bake mussels is the one I recommend and the have good topping and baked seasoning. 

I would said they expanded the appetizers very well. Service is good. It is about 4.5 stars. Not yet 5 stars.

New method of the ice cream making. Icesmile catch my attention immediately after Mark review. I told my wife that we are going to try something new that night. If you want the fresh made ice cream, go no further. 

Icesmile just open less than a week when we visit. The procedure is choose you flavor then the three toppings. We have chosen tropical storm - mango, peach  pineapple flavor. Our toppings are lychee, blueberry and kiwi. It start with the vanilla liquid with the chop up fruits. The start to mixed on top of the ice frozen metal top. You can see the liquid start getting thicker in the process. The final is to spread over the plate in thin layer. They scooped it up in the roll format. Toppings then to be added. 

The taste is good. Not too sweet. Since they just opened, they are still make some decorations when we visit. They are more expensive than the regular ice cream scoop since they are make fresh from the beginning. It is worth to watch the ice cream form. 

There are some suggestions that the store can improve. More toppings selection included tapioca or jelly. Some snack items, may be free wifi. May be included drink item. Water for customers.

This Target is convenient if you need to to abandon Westfield mall and shop at Target. It is one stop location for the surrounding town center. The only bad thing is if you want to shop on target only, you must face the mall traffic. 

The Target here is super Target with the groceries. The place is nice and neat. I like the Target dog as a prop for the display. Star way DVD is under promotion to be on sale soon. 

They have enough counter open and self checkout which help the speed up the check out process.

This restaurant is a 3.5 stats restaurant in my book. We were here at their anniversary where they have free baklava for the customer. Today we are using the groupon to try the restaurant first time in this location. 

We have order the lamb, chicken and beef kabab. We also order extra meat on the gyro and added the falafel. Going big on order for this visit. Today the best chicken kabab. The lamb and steak is a bit chewy. I order meat with medium rare. The marinate is on point except the meat quality need to be better. The falafel is a bit below average. The baklava is excellent. The gyro also excellent since they shave of the main skew and cook it one more time to make this crispy. 

Overall the food is above average. Service is better than good. The place is well decorated.

This is the place I take my car for wash and oil change. I have been here several time. It is a quick thing to do. Sometime the line is too long that I have to come on other day. 

Today is Tuesday and they have the lube and oil change special. It is $19.95 include out side wash (normal is $29.95). The oil change service include the compliment wash. The price is a steal with two things accomplish in less than half hours. Alway inform them to use hand tight for the lube nut to avoid damage to the car. 

I have only car wash here before. They did an ok job for the price paid. Usually you will see some dirt in the trim line that difficult to get out. Overall they are clean. They have different wash or wax or cleaning the inside or steam clean with leather amor. The bug removal is extra. 

They also have the reward card if you come here regularly. Every dollar you spend you get 10% back in reward. It work for me like 10 wash get one free. Do not expect extremely clean. But is clean enough. It is good in winter since you don't need to wash in cold weather and someone take care for you here.

This is our neighborhood Dairy  Queen. We always receive the coupon in the mail. We alway like the coupon for the buy one and get one free coupon. The best thing about them is they run the manager special. 

Just a note, I am guessing they love to have the store at high visible area at the Main Street such as Bruce B Down to get more traffic with customer. It is great to have the store across to cinema. If you have a scary movie you need to have the ice cream to calm your heartbeat. If you watch a love movie, you can share the ice cream with your love one and continue in the love pool. 

I love their blizzard the way they have prepared it. They with mix the ice cream, milk, choices of mix and scramble together. Then they will show you the upside down mixed product in the cup to tell you how well they mix it. I love their cappuccino flavor with Heath bar. My wife usually cannot have any caffein after noon time. I am usually finish the cup myself. The Heath bar crunch make the blizzard more flavor increase the coffee flavor. Chocolate and cappuccino - get it together like the superglue in flavor. 

I can see their business is getting impact by nearby ice cream store. Competition among them getting stronger. I will continue to support them when I can.

This restaurant first day opening for business is Chinese New Year. We were looking for Chinese food after the celebration event. We didn't know they actually just opened for business that day. After checking for the menu, we decided to tryout the new restaurant. 

This is about 3.5 stars restaurant. Since they just open, the are some kink need to workout. The restaurant use to another Chinese restaurant. They have redecorated the interior and it is mor brighter than previous restaurant interior. I like the current lighting better. 

We have ordered the scallions beef, fried calamari, three cup chicken, sweet and sour ribs, and seafood fried noodle. The three cup chicken is compose of three different sauce in same measurement. This is chop up chicken with bone. I like it. I like the most is the seafood fried noodle. The noodle taste very good with the sauce. You need to mixed the sauce in and soak the fried noodle to soft and eat it. 

Overall our service is Average. Food is good. We enjoy our time there.

The Macy locates at the center of the Shop Wiregrass mall. They strategically located at the main attraction of this mall. Any big event of this mall is happening around this area. 

Macy is pleasant to shop due to wide space walkway and any good selection. They often provide discount when it comes close to any holiday. When you sign up the mailing list, they mail the coupons to your home. Although they are in the high side on many items, when it is discount, the price cut is deep. I often get discounts on top of another discount. Some of the work long sleeve dress I have purchased is only $12 of the 50% discount with another 30% off. 

The home good is at the second floor which is I often visit.  The bathroom is clean in Macy if I come to this mall.

The fish house is hidden secret for the local. Thanks God we have Yelp to locate this restaurant. This is favorite of the Ruskin residents in this remote area. This restaurant is buried deep inside town. If you didn't drive to this location, you would not notice it.

They have fresh fish and shrimp. But their signature dish is the smoke mullet. They serve limited fish for the day. If you come late, you may not be able to get one. However, there is plenty of other seafood you can choose. The choice included the shrimp, oyster, catfish, or soft shell crab. I got the mixed and match with shrimp and catfish. This dish is fresh and good. Two sites come with it for $12. Good deal. 

This place is open air with high ceilings. During the summer time, it is still cool breeze with fan blowing.

Great indoor club. The first sentence describes all. I enjoy our time there with three other friends. It was not mean for the father day's celebration, but I did it anyway without kid. During the same night, We saw the next table have the engagement party over 15 people. They are crazy enough to celebrate together in surprise. 

The story started with a selfie stick of that day. After we have some of the food, we decided to give the picture with the band. Fortunately I have brought one selfie stick that night. We have taken some selfie with band and the waitress. While we have selfie, our neighbor table customer came and has the video bomb. There where everything begin. We start going to their table with our selfie stick and take the picture of the engagement party. It's how the people there are very nice and party. 

Tonight we have the shrimp cocktail, chipotle BBQ wing, pull pork nacho, peanut soup, chicken and crab cake nacho, slice skirt steak. The only thing I not a fan is the shrimp cocktail. The shrimp must have sit in the refrigerator for some time. Freshness is not there. 

Tonight the band for the Amanda Drake and the barnburners provide a great country with blue vibe music entertain the crowd. Barnburners - I wonder how many barn they have burn. The music is mixed to current popular song. We enjoy it. Service is great. We have Xena the princess warrior serving us. We will be back to have fun since they have the indoor vibe. I would suggest come at 7pm enjoy two hour peaceful meal then enjoy the blasting music for another two hours.

The New Orleans Jazz National Historic Park is a unique place. This park is run by National Park Service. I definite like the ranger position here. They are located in the big easy and the work is much easy - no forest fire to worry, big animal attack tourist. The park has ranger program free tour around the French Quarter to the Old US Mint. Now I think more of it, I like the ranger assignment here. May be I should be apply for the special language tour guide. 

The park hosts the indoor and outdoor concert. Some concert in the Historic Park, some in the Old Mint, Some in the French Market. Today they have listed two concerts, one in the Historic Park and One in the Old Mint. We have gone to the Historic Park since our time has conflict with the parade for the other concert. 

The historic park is hosting a Cajun children Jazz concert. The performer is Johnette Downing. She is author for the children book, children jazz song, and performer of children jazz. It was rewarding that the song actually from food of the children eat in a week. Song like Monday red bean, Tuesday Po-Boys, Wednesday Gumbo, Thursday Jambalaya, Friday Cat Fish, Saturday Crawfish and Sunday Beignet. She also has song like Mississippi River, Cajun Dance Bonjour, Chef Creole, and Crawfish Song. It makes you think about Louisiana Cuisine.

Please check at the park for the schedule of the day with variety of free concert and location.

I have visit this place many time. After a year, they finally have some good sales. During this thanksgiving season, the Black Friday sale has some good discounts. Parking lots are full of cars. Hopefully this is a prosperous year for the mall. The Christmas decorations is not much in the mall. But the light colors is adjusted to green and red. 

Currently the mall has built up their surrounding with some good restaurant. It is good for the shopper who went there. There are some unique store such mimmic. There is a food court in the middle if you want to get something to eat. 

The mall has a lot of choices to shop. From small items to big ticket such as coach handbag. All has some bargains in the mixed.

The restaurant is located at the plaza was plan to be the china town 20 years ago. However the china town was not happen in tampa. It came close to the planing. 

The restaurant sales Chinese BBQ food such as pork, duck, crispy pork. You can buy it by the pound. This restaurant was here before along the Ding Ho oriental grocery store. 

The best value is the beef noodle soup. The beef is stir fry and then add to the soup. The soup broth is chicken and bone base. The noodle is the Hong Kong egg noodle. The are thin and great to chew. Compare to Mc Donald. I will pick the value ($5.99) of this noodle soup anytime. It is more nutrition and fun to eat. 

They also serve traditional Chinese dishes. If you like fried rice try their dry scallop fried rice. It stir fried with dried scallop and slice asparagus. The other dish are the beef with Chinese broccoli with beef in hoisin source also a good dish. This dish is more to American style dish but still kept the Chinese cuisine technic.

The surprise dish is the Taro Crispy Duck. The duck is deboned and marinated. The duck meat then lay on the bottom and top paste with ground taro. They are deep fried and chop into pieces. The accommodate with sweet soy sauce and garlic and scallion. They are crispy on top and bottom. The top is a crispy taro create the net type crispy good. The bottom is duck create slightly burn crispy. This is a killer dish.

Happy hour at Saturday??  Un heard off. This restaurant offer the happy hour sushi is at Saturday from 2 to 4 pm. The rolls are $4 each. They also have the reduce price appetizers. 

It is perfect to go there when I just finish my Saturday noon time badminton session. Compare to many places with happy hour sushi, their sushi rice is seasoning with good flavor before wrapping. In my book, only one happy hour place sushi rice is comparable to this place. I got six different roll for $24. I also get half price sangria sake. Good deal. 

Other than their happy hour sushi, they also have chef signature sushi roll. They are very attractive. The service is good, the ambients are nice. Can you believe they are the few pioneers who serve gourmet sushi in Bay Area.

Recently I was invited to the restaurant special Korean BBQ meet. The meet design a menu of $20 per person. It was very good deal. I have been to rice before but I have not given them a review.  

It is hard to see Korean BBQ that grilled in tradition charcoal. And we have it that night with charcoal and enhance gas grilled. I have to compliment to restaurant believe the traditional. 

We start the meal with kimchi pancake. It is interesting to see pancake with kimchi and they are delicious. Our side dish include the glass noodle in mushroom, grilled beef, spinach. The spinach, mushroom and grilled beef are cook separately then mixed together with sauce. This is my favorite dish. We also have typical Korean side dish that came with it but the glass noodle top everything.  

Our grilled meat include kalbi (short rib) bulgogi (slice beef) and spicy beef in sizzling plate.  They are very good indeed. We have a lot of food that night and we enjoy our company. Previously we were here, we have grill mackerel also a good dish if you know how to from bone.

Happy cow come with happy people. The store provides pink setting matching their logo. People come here more often when the sun was hot during the daytime and enjoy a ice down during the night. 

The store will give you a few sample cups to allow you sample the ice cream flavor they have during that day. The system here is to buy by weight. You can eat as little you want or fill the cup high as you go. Don't forget the topping. Yap topping. They have variety of topping include fruit flavor bubble pop. If you added the bubble pop, it will be pop inside your mouth and the fruit flavor enhance the experience. 

If you are checking in with yelp, you will have a free waffle cup. The store offer seating in the store with limited capacity. Buy by ounce is idea of how much you want. People stop by this store to have social time with each other. The only down side is the parking in front is very limited due to so many restaurant have to share. You may have to park far away and walk to store.

Curtis Hixon is prime real estate of City of Tampa. It connect the people and keep the business by host many event. The event include the Margarita Festival, Mayor O Green, Beer Festival, Food Truck and many music venue. It also has the Christmas series with ice skating rink.

What make this park successful as below: 1. The Tampa River Walk that connect the prime river bank estate create downtown living more attractive. 2. The Hillsborough River attract people like to come to the park have water. 3. Spectacular view of the University of Tampa with the old glory of the hotel look in the pass. 4. A dog park nearby that many bring animal friend to walk.

This bring the thrive living of the downtown more color full. Several apartment near the downtown make this attraction as a close by walking distance. What can you argue with this type living.

This restaurant close at 3 pm at weekday that I only can visit at my off day. They even open at Christmas Eve until 12 noon. We got there at 10:50 and they are very busy. 

We have ordered the lunch special with grilled steak sandwich and soup. We also added a breaded steak sandwich for the lunch. This is good Latin steak sandwich since they pay attention to make the edge of the meat seared well. This will release the meat burn taste. 

The soup is Caldo Gallego. White bean with collar green and tiny piece of ham. I believe the soup is meat base and they are good. The breaded steak make you feel hungry. They are very good. 

I like the floor is service by a young group of waiter and waitress. They are fast and effective. I wish there is restaurant like this with affordable price in New Tampa.

I like Lowe's better than other home hardware store due to store is well organize. The aisles are alway clear and not messy. I can in and out the store generally less than 30 minutes if I know the items I need. 

They are well stock and great selection of the items. I always can find the screw or bolt size that available. Hand tool or electric apparatus that fit my home can be located. I alway find the decorated ceiling fan that is easy to install and allowed me to switch on the light above or below the fan blade for lighting the room. The remote come handy to change the speed or reverse the direction of the wind flow depend on summer or winter. 

There are items bargain at each week. I found my appliance there with bargain most of time. Some time they selling the floor sample for a good pricing. The brand of the appliance ranging from May tag to the kenmore. I bought my no center blade washing machine there. I also bought my touch sensor faucets for my kitchen sink. It come very handy when your hand had soap or oil and you can open the faucets just a touch of the body part. 

I got most of the gardening flowering bush from their gardening section. Their selection is great or you can specific order any thing that is not in store for gardening and they arrange with their nursery. 

I alway love their power tool. It give me a right tool for the home project. It have wide selection of paint and color that create your interior setting like double tone color. Imprint pattern apparatus that can print on top of base coated color to create elegant interior setting. 

Lowe card come with 5% discount. If you just apply, they have special 10% discount when you buy the appliance with big ticket item.

I have pass by this boonies place and decided an adventure to try this restaurant. It locate at I-4 exit 22 and just north of the exit. When I was there they just opened the door for business. 

The interior design like a country kitchen. It have the old grandpa chairs at elliptical table. The menu selection mainly seafoods with fish. They call themselves the Catfish Shack but I am changing the norm to try their grouper. I have order the blackened topping. The way they cooked the fish is to provide black pepper and herb over the fish and broil in the oven. It is not open grilled. This is the first time I have eat the blacken fish this way. Because they broil it the fish juice came out and is quite good. 

My sides are the collars green, corn bread and hush puppies. The corn bread go well with the fish juice. I like the collars green cook in traditional southern style with pork crump. 

This restaurant is middle of nowhere but it provide exciting meet location for the biker or back country boy. I will try their cat fish next time. In their menu, they also offer the gator meat.

Is it Post Office, a Bazzar, souvenir shop, art store?  It is interesting place to visit. It has the charming character of the town. Definitely worth a spin around the store. It is a store for many trade. 

Hoping from station to station and you will see different thing is displayed. They do have some maze and narrow walkway may be rubbing shoulders with fellow shoppers. 

Great to visit.

I always enjoy Fred's Market. This is my second Fred's Market I have visited. We were here for the Father's Day. At 6:30 pm, the hostess tell us the wait is 25 minutes at Sunday. About 12 minutes, pur names already call.   

Compare the Fred's Market here to the one I'm Riverview, this one is cleaner and nicer. However, I think the one in Riverview has larger buffet table and more selection. I love southern food here. Especially the fried catfish. It also has good bake chicken and ribs. The southern fried chicken here is delicious. The collar green is my favorite. 

At the end of meal, they have dessert station for you to request any assembly. I got the bread pudding at below top with the butter pecan ice cream and finish the touch with the strawberry. Yummy tummy. Service was great. Definitely recommend to visit.

Doug Nation is part of the Metropolitan Ministry. I am applause to their mission to do good for the community. It is unique in a way they have the ice cream concept to attract people. I like it when they have taken something simple to add on other thing and create something new. 

This ice cream store combine the cookie dough and the ice cream and create something new. The best thing is not just have different ice cream flavor but also include the different flavors of cookie dough. I have the s'more cookie dough with marshmallow. My ice cream is pecan with caramel ice cream. I like the combination. The only thing is after you have through with the ice cream, you have to work on the cookie dough. The entire combination is very sweet. Good for the sweet tooth person. 

The clerks are very friendly. I like the taste try. You choose any flavor to try. Since it is located on the downtown, parking is a challenge. Parking after 6n pm is free. However they close at 8 pm which did not give you much time to have it after work.

This Grain Berry is open. But the seating area is limited due to pandemic. They layout their existing chair to form line with one way entrance with six feet social distancing. Worker wear mask and gloves. They keep the customers safe. 

I got the Vacation Smoothie. It is mango, banana, and pineapple smoothie. The smoothie is expensive than normal smoothie place but it give you a large cup. It was delicious. The store clerk recommended this choice and I not disappointed.

My revisit is much better. It still has kink on the tuna protein. May still need to make sure the tuna is good to serve. All other proteins are excellent. This restaurant is improving to better. Management is paying attention to the customers suggestion. 

We went through the as it has stated beyond this line is 8 minutes to eat. It is accurate to keep the line moving and limiting number of bowls per person. This is a successful operation on the line que to sit down. 

The bowl was improving from my last visit which I can see the bottom of the bowl. This time they fill up the bowl with food. The quantity has been met. 

I like the steak and the BBQ chicken. The glass noodle is the best if you choose the base. The add on is great too such as the guacamole and the plum tomato.

Coffee is good. Have a lot of flavor. I like they making cinnamon bun in front of the customers. I love the cinnamon sticks. It easy snack. If you are sugar cravings, they have a lot. Don't get use to it, because 5 sticks may not enough. They do have the classic roll or the mini roll for small bite. 

Their ready to pour drink is what you going for. Try their cinnamon pack. It come with many types. Good luck.

Beef O Brady is local love. I see a lot customers come here for affordable drink. They do have attractive cocktails. Unfortunately the cocktails alcohol level is not enough in the level of cocktails drink at nearby bar. I think this restaurant is about 3.5 stars. 

I start with Pineapple Express Cocktails. It is good looking drink. May need to have more alcohol in it. We order the blackened dry rub wings. Wing size has small to average size. It was good. The main entree is the Friday special. Surf and turf. At these this is affordable dish and special of the night. It is sirloin steak cook to order temperature and grilled or fried shrimp. This dish only on Friday. I think this is the dish to get. 

Service is good. Nothing fancy. Food come out at right time. I would said 3.5 stars but rounded up to 4.

Tampa do not has many documented history. In 14 century the Spanish does touch down at Tampa. They discover the safe harbor in this area. 

Then the Cuban cigar factory thrive. A lot of building turn to cigar manufacturing. Today we can find them around the downtown and YBOR city. Cigar rolling bring a lot of business. You can find some of the cigar rolling in YBOR for live demonstration. 

Then the McDills Air Force just celebrate the 75 year anniversary. Which make this museum with another milestone. 

The entrance have a symbolize restaurant Columbia Restaurant which the original store open at 1905. This one located in the museum has a nice decoration.

Ichiban is an oldest sushi restaurant before any other sushi restaurant around USF. They have been here very long time ago. The owner is a Taiwanese. They start the restaurant by wrapping their own sushi. 

This restaurant has three major part of menu - the tempura, sushi sashimi, and teriyaki. They also have the rice and noodles bowl section. They have offers the variety of sushi. I always like their bento boxes and the boxes are the best values. They have teriyaki, sashimi, and tempura bento boxes. 

Today I have the sashimi bento box with added shrimp tempura for extra $3. I love shrimp tempura. The correct way is slight dip the shrimp in wet bread and deep fried. Then drip a bit of tempura next to shrimp and create the crispy effect. However, this process needs to finish in less than 3 minute before over cook the shrimp. This restaurant has the technique for it. The box came with 9 pieces sashimi, cucumber salad, tuna roll, California roll, and imitations crab salad. The sashimi is fresh. Love the shrimp tempura. The shrimp tempura has to eat there. This is not a takeout food. 

The customer make out from local businesses and students since it is close to the USF. The service is good and the food come out quick since they have enough sushi chefs.

Yummy chain has extended to the south Tampa area. The new building is beautiful and nice. However, the parking is a nightmare. It take a lot of time to circle the neighborhood before find a spot to park. 

The food is very similar to the chain menu. Since they just open, not all items may be served due to availability of the ingredients. We were there for duck raisins fried rice, but they are not available. We got the Hong Kong style sweet and sour pork and the scallops fried rice. The dried scallops need a bit crispy. However, the taste is there. 

The portion is normally match the chain standard may be a bit smaller. The service need to pick up. We have to wave to get attention. They are still new and try to work out their bump. May be give them another month.

For Brandon area, this is good enough Italian restaurant. Local like this restaurant because of the cuisine and affordable. I see many regular of the restaurant because the waitress know them. 

The special of the day usually listed on the black board. I got special Julienne Cocotte. It is sautéed chicken, mushroom, in creamy sauce in a hot clay pot. It come with garlic butter bread. It is a light dish to have. The second dish oven roasted chicken. This dish is a half chicken with lemon and spice. The chicken was well prepared. Seasoning is great. 

This restaurant to my book is 3.5 stars. Main is the the wait staff need to be more patient and polite. This is the area that the restaurant need constant improvement.

It is a real studio. It is. In fact, it is the music studio, dance studio, art studio, music instruments store and a cafe. I like this concept. It is almost like one stop for the parent. This kid go to practice dance lesson, this one go to music lesson and the other go to painting practice. And the mom go to drink a coffee in the studio cafe while waiting for the kid.

In fact, the patents can drop off the kid and go shopping. The studio has some music instruments for sale. With internet ordering that is so convenient, not many people want to make a deal through actual music store anymore. I would encourage you visit them and keep the store open. This studio has other edge with the bistro cafe, music lesson, art class, dance lesson to attract more people. It has it way to thrive their business without all egg in one basket. I applause the new concept.

Umai Sushi has great deal at lunch time. Their lunch special stop at 3 pm. The lunch special included hibachi and tempura under $10. They also have roll lunch special with $7 for two selected rolls or $10 for three rolls. They also has happy hour beer 3 to 6 pm with domestic beer for $1.99 and $2.99 for imported beer. 

I got a piece of surf clam sushi, one escolar roll and one chef special roll Fantastic Spicy Tuna roll. The surf clam is big and cover the entire rice ball. The escolar roll is still feel a bit frozen. The Fantastic Spicy Tuna is good. It is spicy tuna deep fried then add the special mayo and ell sauce. Then top with shredded imitation crab meat. This is good.  

Service is very attentive. Food is good. I like the decorations but can improve.

The festival is big at the park. It does get a lot of attention since there is so many people showing up. Generally the festival has a lot of food truck. But I did not try anything. 

The artists are from many place. Some of the art displays were very interesting. Can you imagine put all the shopping cart in pattern and took a top down picture. The hanging motion plate showing the moving animals or human when the wind blow. 

There were an artist make famous people painting at the skate board. Many welder create their art pieces. Some even put Crome on it.

We were here for their Tuesday special. Their Tuesday is value day. I recommend you joint in. I like to sit at the bar. Because they have good service. If you need anything, there is a person in front of you can help. 

The Tuesday special includes a bunch of list at slider and tacos section. We got the the blackened grouper taco. The grouper is big piece with good blackened. The second item is the poppy meatloaf slider. I think this slider is interesting. The third item is the carne Asada taco. I think this one is good. The fourth dish is three little pig slider. Good BBQ pork. I like the Tuesday special because each item is fractions of the price. 

The happy hour also includes the $2 beer and more. Service at the bar is great. Love to be there.

Munchie is good ice cream at the mall. It has a lot topping choices. That is the major reason they are solid 4 stars. It is love by Wesley Chapel residents. Many have come here. I feel that 1 clerk is not enough. 

The soft serve is by weight. But the toppings are impressive. They include hot fudge, strawberry dip chocolate, sweeten cherry, sprinkles, . Since it is by weight, the toppings become burden to weight in for additional cost. However, since they have good topping, customers don't mind.

There is positive outcome for good or popular soft serve flavor. I will encourage them to continue to strive for the best interest of customers for this matter.

This BBQ place is busy event is 3 pm in the afternoon. A lot of people are here to pickup. If you don't want to wait, you can call ahead. 

They have chop pork, rib, chicken and sausage. The best is their special sauce on the BBQ. Their sauce is orange tangy taste. It got some flavor on it. I have the four meat special for $16. The pack all the meat at on box almost cannot close the lid. Plenty of food. 

This is neighborhood BBQ. They only have a few table. Many come to have the take out. The also serve pineapple ice tea. It something different than most of the BBQ place.

This newly open restaurant is serving Japanese street food. Basically the name of the restaurant is alcohol house. Many come here not just have good beer and cocktails, they enjoy the time here. 

We start with seafood sunomono. The seafood is assorted. It has imitation crab stick, octopus, and shrimp. I think this dish is over price. For the amount of food is little, too much of cucumber. The chicken gizzards skew was nice. It is the food to go with sake. We also has the yellowtail collar. This collar is good not the best but good enough. 

We also has the tonkutsu ramen. The ramen most value is having a good soup base which they got it. The charshu is good also. The veggies they have is just the bamboo shoot. I wish they have more stuff to attract the customers. Service is good and attentive. They did give out the surprise gift at the end to loot back the customers.

A lot people visited this place after church. This restaurant seem like a popular place for after church gatherings. One thing notice these restaurants mainly white people. So you know their food is American taco.  However they have the way to attract these type of customers. 

I like some of the Taco but my wife love the cracked corn. I got the chimichuri steak taco and my wife got the blacken fish taco. The steak taco may need to be improved but the fish taco is very good. The cracked corn is top with spice and cheese that make this corn very desirable. 

I would said this is Baja type taco place. It has it specialty. I like the interior design to show the beach look. You may choose one of the flint stone car booth to eat you taco. It is almost like movie.

B's Caribbean food is love by local. They only have one table. This is a take out place have a lot of customers. During my visit, at least 4 customers ahead me with multiple orders. You can see the popularity of local. 

They jerk chicken and some traditional Caribbean dish like Ackee with salty fish. The selection includes large or small portion. I got their popular dish. The oxtail. The marinated sauce went into the bone. The meat is soft but have not fall off the bone yet. I prefer fall off the bone cooking. My dish come with good bean rice and braise cabbage. Both side are great. 

The wait for the food is not bad. I got my food 15 minutes after order. It is considered fast with so many order ahead of me. Parking is free with lot in front of plaza.

Definitely pop if you put your popsicle and sit for some time. It great summer to visit this place to cool off. We were going to try their waffles but their waffles machine was down. So we go for the popsicle instead. The price is about a bit above average. Not much of selection. But the selection is good enough to try. 

We have the watermelon citrus and salty chocolate Elvis. The watermelon citrus I have tasted some chop up fruit remains. It is refreshing. The salty chocolate Elvis is something good feeling. Soft to bite and easy let it melt. I can hear some Elvis music now from Graceland. Put some sun glasses I will be Elvis myself. 

They also offer dip or sprinkle. Dip it is $1, roll and drizzle is $0.75. Like I said they have waffles on the stick but machine was not operate that day. They also have grilled cheese, coffee and regular ice cream.

I like the name Sailing. It is almost sailing to island to have poke. This restaurant is rather new. It has a lot potential. They have poke and ice cream. I would go for the poke.

The poke dish has two protein in regular size or three protein with larger size. The difference is 6" bowl and 10" bowl. I would go for the large. The other thing I need to mention is their unlimited topping of you choice. I also like their protein choice. The have more choices on the protein and different than other poke place. It has the grilled eel option. Other things that attract you is their sauce is thicker and not watery. Which make this poke location a win win choice. 

We like the larger size with larger diameter to contain more toppings. Above three reasosn will be the driving force for repeat customer.

The restaurant observed the CDC guideline of mask and social distancing for each party. Temperature check was on the entrance. The bar style is open patio with roof covering. I would say they save cost on AC room. 

I was here for the taco take over Tampa Bay. However, the counter behind the bar area do not know this promotion. In fact, they run out the Alto Margarita. They point to us they do have a food truck in the compound serve the taco. They also can order those food at the counter. 

The food truck is kind tuck away in the corner. The order only take about 7 minutes. We got the blackened fish taco. I think it is a good deal with taco take over. The fish is fresh with nice blackened I want. The three taco provided in good quantity. The accompanying taco material and sauce is delicious.

I usually can get what I need in this store. Although they are not carry over million selection, but they do have enough to go by. 

The store just located at the Fletcher Ave. this may be the closer ABC near USF. Store is very clean and well sign for each category. They do have cigar section in the temperature control room. The have beer in the cold section that you can have a cold one immediately. 

The store clerk is friendly. Not the best but is not bad either for consider wine and spirits store.

This is my first visit to this Jeremiah Italian Ice. Not many customers in front of the building except 4 police officers. They have finished up their Italian ice and remain conversations. This time of year is still considered cold night and not many customers. 

I like Jeremiah because they have Italian ice and soft serve as a layer to separate the flavor. I got cotton candy, banana and sea salt caramel. Those are my favorite choices. I love the presentation of the ice with different color. The ice is tasty and playful.

It was difficult to find the medium range price for Brazilian Grilled. Most of them are very expensive. But this restaurant offer a way out with affordable price if you want a Brazilian Grilled buffet. Their rotisserie grilled meat is good and beat the chain restaurant because they are less salty. 

Rotisserie included the sausage, top sirloin, kabab, chicken drum stick, fillet mignon with bacon, garlic steak, sausage, Pork rib. Those are good selection. On top of the grilled meat, the hot food, salad and dessert also available for the taste. I like their egg plant salad. Food is delicious, it good to go as group and not cost too much. 

They close at Monday,  but Tuesday to Friday their web site has a $2 off coupon to save you further. I like the food there.

I have been to the St. Petersburg and this restaurant. Both of them are excellent restaurants. The lure has been successful due to their Tapas dishes. It has more incentive during the the happy hours. During the happy hour, they have selected drink for $5. At menu, they have $5 sushi and Taco. 

I was here celebrating a friend birthday. Our waiter was on point today even we have our big party. I got the Miller which is the seared duck breast over string green bean top with bacon piece. It serve with sweet potatoes mash. I like this dish better in St. Pete. The chef there has better skill than this restaurant. I also got spicy tuna and yellowtail sushi. Both of them has excellent taste. For the taco, I have Texas and Action Joe taco. The Texas taco is the sweetened marinated steak and portobello mushrooms. This a good taco. The Action Joe is seared tuna taco. 

I like the layout as a bar and some game for the customers to enjoy. The outside seating is available.

This is about 3.5 stars restaurant. This restaurant locate in the Quality Inn. It use to be a Italian restaurant. I like the new look and interior design of the new Japanese Restaurant. It has quite an open space with the bar in the middle. 

We order two ramen. One is the King of Ramen Noodle Soup and the other one is Ramen Pork Noodle Soup. This two Ramen is similar with broth. The broth is similar to Japanese Tonkutsu Ramen Broth with pork bone base. I have to give them high praise on the broth, egg, and the bamboo shoots. The broth was top with sesame oil which increases the flavor. I like the charshu Pork. It has a bit marinated pork meat. The let down is the noodle. The noodle was glue together. Obviously the noodle did not go through the clean cold water that cause this to happen. This need major improvement. For a restaurant serve the ramen main ingredients did not done correctly is not acceptable. 

Overall. The service was slow in the beginning. But it was pick up. Price is in the medium range. Just ok for my standards.

This review leads me to think about Rachel's dog. I call it Mocha Chocolate. It looks yummy and beautiful to be as a pal. This park has a beach dog park where the dog can run wild and jump into the bay water to bath. I saw a lot of dog there. They have fence quit a beach area just for the dog. Many brought the dogs and they play with each other. The park also has a station with fresh water to rinse away the salt sea water and sand. Very thoughtful. I bet Rachel will bring her dog one day. 

The park is like a finger tip next to McDill Air Force base on the map. You have to pass through some of the industry area before you get into the park including concrete prefabrication plant. 

The park offer Frisbee golf, children play yard, pavilion with BBQ grilled and more. The area is surrounding by mangrove. They have beach area and boat ramp to lunch the boat. People are using the pier to fish. The natural beauty makes the park for outdoor activities.

It is good all you can eat sushi place. Now I can said Pinellas has two restaurants delicate the sushi all you can eat. This will be one of them. I like the interior decoration of the restaurant. I also like about the order all you can eat from menu. Basically it is not a pick up your own food. You order and they will bring it to you. It is good ideal during pandemic. 

The food includes the sushi, hibachi, dessert, tempura, and more. I like the the summer roll, yummy roll, dragon roll, monster roll. This roll are chef special roll. For sushi a la cart, I like escolar, salmon, tuna and masago. The appetizers, I would go for the pepper sear tuna. It also has regular sear tuna, tilapia slice. In addition we got the spring roll, goyoza, and steamed shiu mai. Those are good choices. We also have the shrimp tempura and chicken Karage. I would not recommend chicken Karage. 

Service is good. Very attentive. Taste are on some, some need work. It is a mixed.

Solid 4 stars restaurant. It s close to 4.5 stars. If the dining open, I would consider to dine here. During the pandemic, they only allow take out. There a few review indicated if you dine in, the food take some time to come out. I think it is a easy fix. 

We started with the Garlic Parmesan Chicken Wing. We don't like the fry and get the wing a la cart. The wing was perfectly done. I like the parmesan with oil on wing. It is delicious. We got the chicken waffle to star also. I thing the fried chicken strip is nothing special. But it do have good fried. The waffle is soft. May because I have it take home. 

Our entree is the smothered pork chop. It has good smothered gravy sauce on top. We also got the oxtail. The meat is fall off the bone. The oxtail was cook for sometime and soft to eat. Very good dish. 

From order to pick up is about 20 minutes. Not bad. Considering it is a good southern dishes.

I was here for the end of prohibition anniversary. This day celebrate that alcohol is finally legalized. Bubba has several cocktails in low price to celebrate the day. It also includes some drinks too. 

I got the Long Island ice tea, burger, and two different boneless wings. I spend less than $15 because of the special celebration reduced price. The burger has good bacon and meat. The boneless is nice without bone. The sauce is accompanied well with the wing. 

Overall is a good experience. This place is definitely a great place for budget drink. During the celebration, the t-shirt was give out as a prize.

I would said the best Italian restaurant for my list.  Please read on why they did not get 5 stars. Do I come back. Hack yes. Hopefully I can give them a 5 stars next time. 

Before you come to this restaurant, you need to know a few thing. 1. Do not just show up. Make a reservation. Even though they said is highly recommended, I said is a must. Almost every day for people just walk in they have to wait for 2.5 hours at dinner time. If you don't have reservation,come at the time they open. 2. Go for the menu items. They are match the value of the food. 3. Be patient. They really don't have much help on the kitchen since it always back up on the order. 

Today we show up with reservation and we still have to wait for our table to be ready. Not a long wait. While waiting there is a special of the day on the board for your choices. We have appetizer and pre-meal item that come with the entree. The first course is about 30 minutes. But the entree is about an hour wait. I did ask the waiter why. They have accommodated with addition wine and dessert no charge for our situation. 

We begin our appetizer with Vongole Marechiara. It is the baby pasta clams sautéed with garlic, basil, and white wine sauce. The sauce is great. Please ask a loaf of bread to go with it. It is excellent dipping the bread in this sauce. The baby clam is about 25 to 30 count. But they are small portion in the big bowl. They taste very good. 

My entree is the special on the board. Pan seared blacken Scottish Salmon on top of roasted slice potato with house cure pork belly. The salmon cook just right and the fish is fresh. The cure pork belly is awesome. It is a bit pricy for this dish. The entree come with the soup or salad of your choice. 

The restaurant only have the wine and beer for alcohol. We were accommodated with great dessert for the time lost while waiting. Seem like they have a smaller kitchen. This may be the only area they need to improve. Increase the speed of food preparation or bigger kitchen. Don't let the customer wait. 

The dessert is magnificent. They brought out the Tiramisu, Cannoli, Lemon Cake, and pyramid chocolate. It look awesome when they are in one big plate. I applause they accommodated the customer long wait time.

This taco is number three in my list. My list is base on the authenticity, price range, taste of food and quantity of the food. This taco place has make all check marks I have set. 

This is a food truck at SR 60 and the Lithia Pinecrest. The location is located on the northeast quadrant of the intersection. Easy to fine. The hour is odd. Only weekend has longer hour. So check the time before visit. During the lunch and dinner time, many people call ahead so you need to be patient to wait for the food because of the take out. 

We got the shrimp, Campechano (Steak and Mexican sausage), Babarcoa (BBQ), carnitas, pastor, chicharon. The six Taco was prepared in giant quantity. Roughly $2 each. But their taco meat is enough for two taco in normal taco place. I like the babarcoa and the shrimp taco. Those are very good. 

Our wait is close to 30 minutes because it was dinner time. But it was worthwhile. Food is real good.

Better Byrd is unique restaurant and part of the Fresh Kitchen group. I think their menu is interesting in a way to enjoy variety of the food. The menu selection from dessert, sandwiches, bowls, to taco and wings. It more interesting than the mother Fresh Kitchen which is boring after 4 or 5 visit. 

We got the fried Byrd. This sandwich includes Peruvian slaw, fried buttermilk chicken with cluck sauce. The chicken is crispy. The sauce is great. The entire assembly is harmony. We also hot the charcoal soft serve with peanut jam, coconut flakes, and banana slice. The charcoal soft serve is the best we have. Food is great here especially you look for snack. They also has pork bun which match Asian flavor. 

Overall we like it. But in winter raining day, the inside seating is impossible due low temperature AC unit. Too cold to seat inside.

This may be third ramen place near New Tampa and Wesley Chapel. It is great to see the mall has this chain in working. More choices to people of the area. The only thing I would said, they need to work on the quantity of the food for the price paid. 

We started with the two drink. My wife have the cocoa slush with boba. It is good. But I like my Caramel Macchiato Slush better. Rich in flavor. 

Our appetizers is the ninja nuggets. This Taiwanese street food is delicious. My wife have Mega Pork Ramen. There are charshu pork and charshu pulled pork. This may be the best value. The broth is pork bone base. I have the grilled shrimp ramen. It come with 8 pieces pan seared grilled shrimp. Both our broth is added black garlic. Extra $1 for black garlic to be added. 

Food is great. Measure the price to value and quantity is 4 stars.

May be it is still new store, all qualities of the food are good. Hopefully they will keep it up. We like lunch box. They do have other selections in the menu such as Kimbob and bibimbob. 

We got bulgogi chicken and beef lunch box. The side dish is changed on different visit. We saw side like chicken nuggets, seaweed salad, slice scrambled egg, fried whole egg, imitation crab meat, goyoza, kimchi, and more. The bulgogi spicy chicken and beef is good. I like the beef better. 

One other thing is the fish cake soup. My wife like this item. If you eat it immediately, it is delicious. If you left overnight, the fish cake is a bit soggy. Definitely is to eat at the same time you order.

I don't think they are 4 stars. The most is 3.5 stars. The soup base is a bit blend. Their best dish is Tonkutsu black garlic lover. After that all dish are just average. I give them half stars additional due to pandemic and at least reasonable pricing. 

The soup base is not total pork bone base. The soup is at the light side now t too creamy. The meat just ok for their charshu. Veggie is not heavily use. The porch egg probably the item worthy. I would give their ramen C grade. 

The appetizers fried shiu mai is good enough even they are not in the great category. The fried calamari is just average. Food at least is fresh to have. 

The place is big enough for hosting a lot of customers. Service is good may be we are the only customer. I would said they are like the take out restaurant quality. If I am hungry a bowl of soup during winter, I may think to visit. There are a lot can improve on the ramen.

This cafe is busy during the Friday lunch. I found a place at the bar since I am solo during lunch. The bar area is where they keep all the sauces. So I can pick any sauce I want for my sushi. I am here because of my yelp friend Mel said lunch here has deal and they are good.

Friday lunch is busy. I got their lunch special sashimi. It has 12 pieces slide. The tuna and salmon slice is thick pieces. The yellow tail is thinner but at lease they provide it with masago. The white fish I don't know. These slices lay on white radish. It is actually good deal for $12. It come with choice of side with miso soup or salad. 

The sushi chef is very fast paste. They can roll out the sushi is great speed. The have 4 people in the small space counter but able to work on the tight place. Talking space management, they have good one plus a lot servant.

King of the Coop open in Wesley Chapel is convenient and closer to me at New Tampa. Since I have their chicken, they don't have bone in chicken. Mostly the tender. 

We got the tender basket with Nashville Hot coating. It is really good hot and spicy chicken. Love the sweat hot taste. It is a bit spicy sweet taste which ok challenge for a Malaysian who use to eat spicy food. The basket come with tree pieces. Love the spicy of the coating.

This Caribbean Cuisine wine Caribbean attitude. The restaurant menu do not have much to select but I do like their Oxtail. According to their name they are Haitian cuisine. 

I have the Oxtail and my wife has fried chicken. Their chicken is fried to very crispy. The chicken tasty. It can come with island spice stew. 

I am the fan of oxtail. It cook with island spice in slow braise. The meat is separated from the bone. I like the island marinated sauce. It must has a lot ingredient in it. 

This dishes has a choice of side. It come with plantain and I also choose the mushroom rice. It has dark long grain rice. I like this rice very much. 

If you come to Caribbean, the time is not matter. As a result, you need to wait for your food to be ready. As I said before. The Caribbean attitude slow and easy.

Solid 4 stars and most affordable in the street. With the competition of many restaurant at the same street, they have some edge because of their affordability. One thing definitely can improve is their menu. The letter size of the menu is too tiny. May be need to increase the font size to 14. 

We start with the Chimichurri Parmesan six wings. The wing was fried, grilled, to with cheese and Chimichurri sauce. I believe this is their best appetizer. 

Our entree are Basic and Lima plates and combo. For the basic we have Ropa Vieja and shredded chicken. This combo also come with yellow rice and sweet plantain. The Lima has better rice. It is Peruvian green rice, plum tomatoes and onion. The protein are Chimichurri pork, and mojo pork. 

Service just average. But but and price are good. The happy hour is before 6:30 pm. We were there 7pm and many of the happy hour customers left about 7:15 pm. So if you want to enjoy more quiet setting, come at 7:30 pm.

This food truck has some unique item we are going to try. I have or seen many place have it. This food truck is popular among the community. Price is a bit in the high side. 

They carry chicken and beef shawarma, lamb gyro, ad chicken wings for the choice of protein. The made of food can be wrap, over rice, quesadilla, over salad or a la cart. The do have interesting item like Italian pie. We didn't get that. They are unique due to their chicken shawarma. I have not see one restaurant like they put the chicken in the grilled. Most restaurants chop in slice and stir fry for you. This one I the gyro grilled like what I have in Jordan. They slice it when you need it. It is good. 

The price is not like Jordan street food 1.5 euro. They are American price. But I don't mind it because it really taste like that country.

I like this brewery. It has good beer hall, stage, decoration, art and ambient. Please check their calendar for event and special. I encourage them to continue to do it to attract the customers. 

I got their watermelon mint wheat ale. It was interesting to have because of the watermelon flavor. Price is in the median. The stage has good three D decoration with the eyes look at you no matter where you seat. It has projected the fish aquarium on the wall. The art gallery is another way for me to stroll. 

We were here for the Asian food truck rally. There people at the bar serving are nice to customers.

This is the most completed oriental market. I have seen Atlanta Hong Kong market, super h, ranch 99, this market cannot be compete with that but hold their own ground. They have carried many variety dry food can food and fresh food. 

There six major departments. The Fresh vegetable. The frozen section, imperishable food, deli, fresh seafood, and meat. The deli have the roast duck, crispy pork, BBQ pork, braise pig stomach, pig ear, pig tongue, and soy chicken in the BBQ section in deli. The deli have regular dish like salt and pepper pork chop or shrimp, general tau chicken, sweet and sour chicken, Buddha delight, seafood mix vege, kungpao chicken, fried rice, and noodle. 

The meat department you can get special cut such pork belly, short rib cut, beef Shane. I like the most is they allow for smaller piece flank steak less than half pound. The sea food department have live fish, lobster, vancouver crab. 

The frozen section have Sahbu Sahbu (hot pot) material that you can assemble. You can get thin slice pork, fish cake, shrimp or octopus ball, meat ball, thin slice beef. 

The center section has jasmine rice for various region. They also have the sticky rice, sushi rice, brown rice. The munch area have deferent type of biscuit, mochi, dry squid eat out from bag, fried shrimp chip.....  Got to check out yourself. 

The fresh vegetable that I like the most are the Chinese Kailan, hollow stem spinach, Bok choi, Yu choi. There is tropical fruit that you have never seen before like rambutan. 

Dessert are the coffee cake, coconut bun, sweet bun, sponge cake. More to offer. 

I can get most of the oriental spice here for Chinese cuisine.

Solid 4 star market. We know about this chain market when we travel to Seattle. Finally there is one in Wesley Chapel in the Bay Area. Joining the member ship is free. The benefit of the membership is big because of the discount. I would suggest join their membership before any purchase. There are special discount items for member. 

This store has furniture, interior decoration, toy, food, drink and more. My wife like hello kitty. She is a big fan for many year. This store carry many of the item. From candy to bowl. The items that provide in the store are import from foreign country. If you like those item, you may not get it next time because of foreign supply is different. 

They also carry some wine, beer, imported soft drink and more. Including many types of syrup. You will items you normally don't see in our daily shopping center.

It is a popular neighborhood BBQ. When I put my order in, I was number 15 in the wait list. The wait is more than 30 minutes. They did warn you it going to take long time before your turn. Since they use the parking lot of an commercial building, they have limited parking space. When they people are getting crowded, they stop taking order until the crowd reduced. 

I got the sausage sandwich. They do have a choice how spicy the sausage you want. I pick mild because my wife cannot handle too spicy food. The sausage was well prepared and pack. It was a big link. 

I also got the the tree meat combo dinner. You can choose the upgrade meat such as brisket and rib. The upgrade meat is adding $5 to the original cost which I feel is worth the money. I got pull pork, brisket, and rib. The side are baked bean and collard greens. Both side is good. I also like the sweetness of the bake bean. 

If they can improve the speed of the order, it will tremendously helping them.

Bargain! Bargain! Bargain!

If you look for something temporary and not cost a lot, this may be the place. Many of the item on sales. It is because of the flea. Certainly not. 

If you look for costume, they may have some choice. They do not have the vintage clothing, but they do have all other clothing. 

The flea market also have two Spanish booths. Food is reasonable. I did not try. There is a fruit vendor at the entrance. The rest of the store is under the roof.

We like the this restaurant and this is the third time we are here. The server is friendly, unfortunately they are not fluent in English. The food is very good. Their famous dish is the grill quail. Each order of the grill quail is coming with 10 pieces. They prepare with very tasty sweet blacken source. It is finger licking good. 

The dinner we have order is 7 courses of beef for two. The come with fresh beef slice wrap, beef cute, sesame beef, beef salad, beef congee, beef ball, beef desert. This is serious amount of food for two. The seven way to cook the beef in Vietnamese style open my eyes how it done differently. Of course, they afraid that you order this dis and share with more than three people. Be sure that you have order one more dish if you want to share. 

The restaurant is good with group  and couple. At the end the restaurant is in medium condition for the furniture. This is a place going for the taste not for look. The duck noodle soup is another dish that you may want to try if you don't mind the bone. I always like meat with bone because more tasty. If you are boneless food person this is not your dish.

No sure how long they going to run their lunch special lobster deal. But our experience here was good. This Red Lobster joint I have been visited many time. This time the service is good. Some other time is slow. 

I have been here for Shrimp festival and lobster festival. This time for their lobster lunch special. They will provide half Tail meal for below $10. I have the lobster roll with fried and Cesar salad with added grilled shrimp. The added shrimp is additional $2. Overall not a bad deal. I like the lobster roll. It has good mixture of flavor. The roll is cut out and toasted with grilled. The grilled shrimp is grilled and chilled in the salad make this cold dish which is good also. 

Overall I like the deal. I have been here for many venue and they are decent.

Rare Ethnic Food No. 15

Compare to many Caribbean Cuisine, they a bit above average. In fact, they are Jamaican cuisine. The culture for the Caribbean is more into relax and lay back type. The menu is not printed but on the board. When we were there, many of Jamaican families eat there. 

The oxtail is the popular item that people order. So we go with it. The food came out in about right timing. The oxtail is cook in the sweet side. It come with rice with pinto bean and salad. The oxtail can be pick out by the folk which the must cook this meat long time for it to fall off the bone. I have some other oxtail before. This one is in the middle of the standard. 

Service is good. This is a 3.5 stars restaurant to me. Since there is no half star. 4 stars was given in this review.

3.5 stars restaurant. However, they carry a dish that I haven't have before. Round up to 4 stars. 

This restaurant have sit down and serve. It carry some traditional dish. I have order their special beef pho. It has all the beef ingredients including tripe and tendon. A few things can be improved. The beef need to slice thinner. The pho base soup is at clear and light pho flavor. It may need a bit stronger. But if you like light pho taste, this is the one you can order. 

I have the crispy flat noodle. This dish I have not try before. The angels hair rice noodle was deep fried and flatten. It top with stir fry mixed of meat and seafood. The chef has good wok skill. This dish cook at high BTU flame. It bring out the good flavor. 

I also has a to go special Vietnamese sandwich. It is assorted cold cut meat assemble. The homemade sweet paste make this sandwich stand out from other sandwich. Service is good. Food come out quick.

This is a specialty store you can get the repair of your gadgets such tablet, cellphone, TV, MP3 and more. They have reasonable pricing for all repairs. 

We were here for my old broken phone repair. Since I got new IPhone 6, I decided to see we can repair the IPhone 5. The switch off button is broken. The cost of repairs is $55. Since we check in with yelp, there is a $5 coupon. We also have the factory unlock so we can switch the carrier. It only takes them 24 hour to switch for $49 dollars. We have tested at the store to make sure it has reception. I like local store to do it instead get internet store is I can go back to them if we have problems. 

They also sell cell phone case, refurbished TV, computer screen and more. It is good price. They have average service. Sometimes you need to call to check if the part is arrived to fix your gadgets.

Indian grill has been in my list to visit for some time. We know the best time to visit has to be lunch time all you can eat buffet. I have not have a weekday lunch time to do it until the Labor Day off. 

Parking of the restaurant are only a few adjacent to the restaurant. They do have additional parking at the back. The restaurant have a few seat on the outside and some at the inside. 

The buffet display great selection of meat which I like. I am not a vegetarian and this is fit my appetite. The stand out dish is the tandoori chicken and the curry chicken. The tandoori chickens is well marinated into the meat in comparison to many restaurant in the Bay Area. I like the curry chicken due to their heavy Indian spice like the one I have in Malaysia.

We have a quick dinner before the concert. When we walk into the restaurant, the food smell is over the entire dining room even they have high ceiling. 

Today special is the chicken Tawek with Biryani rice. The chicken is marinated with good flavor. The Biryani rice is good enough may be top five in the restaurant I have tried. We also order the falafel. The falafel did live up to the restaurant name. They have a good falafel. Not too dry and great mixture of flavors. The Mediterranean Mixed Grilled dish include all different grill meat of they serve. I believe they have pre-grill these items to reduce the wait time of the customers. However, the meat is a bit dry. This may be the area to improve. 

Overall the restaurant is counter order and will bring to the table. The interior design is very modern and contemporary. I like the comfortable furniture. They need to improve to ventilate the food smell that trap in the dining hall.

I have been to this Grill Smith when they just open. I don't like at that time because the chaos and un-organize. I have not been back at least few years. Tonight we have decided to go back to visit. Because our visit time is about 9:00 pm one hour before they close, there is no line. I wonder how this restaurant handles pressure when they have a lot customer. 

Tonight is Wednesday and they are Happy Hour all day. Only Sunday and Wednesday is all day Happy Hours. All other day Happy Hour is from 4 to 7 pm. During the happy hour the appetizers range from $5 to $7. It is almost 40% off from the original price. We have order 3 appetizers from happy hours menu and one appetizer from regular menu. They are Spicy Thai Chicken, Crispy Fish Taco, Fillet Tip Egg Roll and we add a Crab and Shrimp Cake from regular menu. After we have order we realize that all items are deep fried. They have their tasty side. I like the crab and shrimp cake the most. I also like the Spicy Thai Chicken dipping sauce with sweet tangy flavor. 

Since we have so many appetizers, we only order one entrée from their special - the Shrimp Diablo. It is spaghetti in red sauce with shrimp except they add a kid of spicy. I believe this dish is too plain and not exciting. I think this dish should not be served any more if they try to attract customer. The special is not special at all.

Overall the service is excellent; food came out very quick since there is no other customer this late. Enjoy watching the Hokey NHL game with the TV with Tampa Bay Lighting score a goal at the buzzer to win.

I was wondering why Chris W visited this place so often. This restaurant really match it name - Chicken Salad Chick. I would said it is huge chick magnet. Many ladies enjoy this restaurant more than guys. If you walk in, the girls are more than the boys. It is really ladies choice of food. 

Stacy Brown the founder and creator has her story of this restaurant of how it started. Interesting story was it. They have multiple selections of chicken salad type that will be some things for your plate. You also can sample the chicken salad before you make a choice of the ultimate salad you want. We have the jalapeño holly that day. It is tasty and good. We order chicken gourmet dish come with sandwich scoop, pasta salad and broccoli salad. I like the broccoli salad. 

The interior decoration certainly the best I seen for the fast food store. They also have the small room can hold 20 people if you like to have the meeting there. Food is definitely healthy side in my book. Service is really good. I will return to this restaurant sometime soon for the chick magnet.

It is close to 4.5 stars. 4 stars is given due the service is a bit slow. 

This place have good pricing for taco joint. I have been book mark this place for a while. With less $10 you can get a combo with drink. I have 5 taco combo for $7.50. But adding fish and shrimp taco is a dollar more. My favorite is the shrimp taco. It has very good spice for the shrimp. Very tasty for the bite. We have other tacos such as lingua, tripa, chicharon. 

It use to a taco truck. Now they have permanent place with sit down restaurant which very good for the customers. Now they serve margarita. I would said is ok. 

We also have fried whole fish. It is a perch fish. It is only $11. Come with two side. It was greatly fried to the bone. The edge and scorn area is crispy. The food is good. I will be back to check them out.

Fleming is an upscale restaurant with sticker price food. It is measure with the quality, service, chef skill and atmosphere. We are glad to try this restaurant to see what they can offer. 

We went to the restaurant without reservation and we got the table in 15 minutes. We were there at Sunday and they are not that busy and we have the table quickly. I wonder weekend and weekday is this situation. We also notice the crowd to eat here slowdown at 8:00 pm. 

Most of the entry is $40 and more. By the time you done for the night is about $70 per person with drink. They also have the three course prix fixe meal about $50

We started with the Ricotta Wild Mushroom Crostini with pesto and microgreens. I like the pesto and the balsamic vinaigrette dip on the side. We have our entry as the Prime New York Strip with the Scallops and the Bloomsdale Spinach - tomato, red onion, spiced bacon, almonds, fresh blueberries, cauliflower couscous, chopped egg, chevre fritter, and lemon-truffle dressing. The Bloomsdale spinach with the lemon-truffle dressing is delicious. The spiced bacon makes a twist to the spinach. The herb butter-roasted Brussels sprouts is a bit charcoal that was place below the steak. Seem like the chef did not watch the fire over the grilled. However, the herb spice work perfectly with the Brussels Sprout. The scallop also is a bit burn on the cumin-laced spice. The scallop is a great. Overall the chef needs to watch the burn food.
We ended with miniature Chocolate Au Crème with chocolate-dipped pistachio tuile cookie. The dessert is perfect. Overall the restaurant is together for the food. The service may need a bit of attention when customer is not look down and looking for them.

Good vibe. This restaurant is about 3.5 star in my book. Since there is no 1/2 stars, 4 is given. Restaurant is kind of short of staffs. Food has good marinated spice. At least they have good interior seat cushion. Table length may need to match the booth length. 

We have order the stew beef, oxtail, and jerk pork. The best is the oxtail. However, the jerk pork come in second. The meat of the food definitely stew for long time. It is separate from the bone. Good enough marinated to the meat. Price is about mid range about what we have paid for. The side includes rice and cabbage. 

As I have said, need more staff. One time the chef come to serve me. There are some take out order, but the food come out right time. Enough volume or size for a grown person.

This is Tampa own nice sandwich store. This is the area they generate a lot crowd during the lunch hour. It is pack most of the time. The sandwich is famous in this area. 

We have the Cuban Sandwich with hot press. We order all inclusive sandwich fully loaded. The sandwich is very thick nice cheese. The ham is very juicy. The mojo pork just a few slice in the center. The pork need to be more mojo marinated with better strong taste. Overall, this is a big sandwich for a hungry person.

A night of celebration for a friend birthday. The restaurant did take the reservation and make sure the surprise party is engaged correctly. They did a good job on reservation and the instruction that was given. 

Tonight is also the third Friday night that Safety Harbor is a music street night that bring a lot of traffic to the restaurant. When I walk in the restaurant they also have live guitar music. The ambient is very nice. This restaurant is almost many chambers. Each room has three to four tables. Sometimes you feel like private dining when our party is the only table in that room. 

The food is great there. Our started are the saganaki - Greek Kefalograviera Cheese. The cheese is well roasted. Harold's Shrooms- Portobello mushrooms cap with red pepper, fresh basil and olive in cheese. It has a mixture of garlic in it and makes it pleasant. My entrée is the Bison Chop Steak with grill onion. It sees with mush potatoes and roast veges. I will prefer this dish not chop or ground bison meat. I will prefer it to be cube pieces that make this dish desirable. 

Overall the services are great. The owner is very welcoming. Like the set up of the restaurant.

Cool festival for third Friday night for musical festival. The Main Street of downtown Safety Harbor is close for the festival. The street musician, bars and restaurants musicians performing make the street is fun to walk. 

There are a lot vendors out there put the good or services they have provided. One of the vendors sells the old lid metal signs that were discarded and fixed it up as an art for decoration. The street is flood of people that are curious or music listener. There also some food vendors that you can get food on the street instead of restaurant. 

I like city or the chamber of commerce bring business for the local restaurants with event. It also provides people to enjoy the evening. I like one musical band "voice of Jazz". They have multi level talent in the group. The musical night also has saxophone and harmonica musician.

This is very much healthy local bar. The outwardly of the restaurant is nice. It allow the bar to serve outwardly and inwardly. You can choose either side. The have many selection on the cocktail. One particular I like is the smoked old fashioned. They use Bulleit Bourbon, Demerara brown sugar and walnut bitter with a twist of orange peel. It add the smoke essence. They burn the wood and capture the smoke. You also can ask them to smoke your wine glass before they pour it for you. 

I have order the Korean Grilled Flat Bread. This bread has 8 big pieces. This flatbread top with fried chicken pieces, mozzarella peppers jack cheese, cucumber, jalapeño and slaw. The slaw is pickle and has Asian cuisine taste. The combination of the ingredients has make this flatbread desirable. 

Service is good. Not spectacular. Food prices is medium acceptable. Ambient is nice.

One of the best BBQ at Central Avenue. This restaurant is close to 4.5 stars about 4.3. This is one of the URBAN restaurants along the same street. Setting is unique, one side is bar and other side is restaurant. 

The BBQ is best to be eat here. The pork belly is amazing. It has sweet and tangy taste. We got the baby back half rack. The meat is smoke more than three hours. The meat is fall of the bone easily. Marinated sauce deep into the meat with dry rub technique. Love the food taste. It come with three different house BBQ sauces. One of them is a bit spicy but all accompanying well with the ribs. We also have a side with collar green. It is good too with the slow cook break down fiber type. 

I got the Sound Czech Pilsner. The beer is good to wash down the BBQ. Service is good and friendly.

I like this theater because of easy access. The rooftop parking has the direct access to the cinema. It has long cover walkway that help you at the raining time. 

We were here for the previews of King Arthur. We have a chance to watch this movie 4 day ahead of the actual showings. The movie is certainly a interesting way telling about King Arthur with mystical and magic. 

The staff of the theater was very nice. The emergency exit is well lid event at the theater. I like the seat. I hate movie theater with reclining seat. Most of the recliner seat alway bounce back and your back uncomfortable. This theater has fix back seat with good slope back support. It do not require me to fight the spring of the recliner for good back support angle. 

Only thing I would said is the bathroom stalls is a bit less. It need to be more. Also, I like someone to sell tickets instead of I walk to automated machine.

It is great to have the friend birthday at a restaurant that I have not been before. I like a sense of adventure for the food. I am not a Laos expert but I am grew up from Southeast Asia and i have some familiarity with the food for the region. 

We have Hale Mary Salad, Laab Chicken, Nam Khao and Khao Boon. Khao Boon- a dish in my name. I need a cut from every customer who eat the dish for using my name :). Khao Boon is a out of taste experience from typical American food. It has chicken feet, pig blood jello, fried pork belly fat, mince pork or chicken and sherrard cabbage. It serve with coconut curry. 

Chicken Laab is a mixture of stir fried chicken, skin and liver over the lettuce and cucumber. This is a interesting dish. It is a national dish of Laos and go with sticky rice. 

This restaurant serve food that not seen often in USA town and city. If you want to try some thing different, come to check it out. The service is slow compared to normal restaurant. This may be the area to improve.
