The accompanying can have a choice white rice, brown rice or fried rice. Their fried rice is a better choice. It also come with a choice of soup and we got the egg drop. The pepper beef is just like most take out Chinese food. Good beef. 

One thing for sure they did it correctly is their packaging. It is air tight and not spilling out. Good container system. The restaurant is about 3.75 stars. It can survive for long time certainty has it client tail.

I have been to this Wawa many time when I on my way to my badminton game to west side of Progress Blvd. this Wawa has good price in the Riverview area. It has plenty gas pump when there is many car pull in. The only thing I don't like is single roll gas pumps. 

It has Wawa drinks for $1.99 special. The convenience store and sub restaurants is great for grab something and go. Area is clean.

I was here when they were different restaurant. I can believe the new owner change this place for good. The food is looking more interesting. They still kept it as wine bar. The seating is more open. Their food has Asian fusion and some french influence. 

We were immediately seat. After order, we noticed several table has not received their food yet. I kind expecting a wait. If the food is good, I don't mind waiting. We have order the charred octopus and Tuscan mussels. The wait is about 25 minutes. However, it worth the wait. The chef do have some skill. The Tuscan mussels is cook at Saffron Tomato Broth. It good with the company grilled bread to dip. The best is the chargrilled octopus. I like the end piece of of the tentacles. It has the most flavor. This octopus was marinated good. I like the octopus ink that was cook at below. Well done dish. 

The service is good. The speed of the food delivery need to be faster.

Coachman Park is Clearwater most celebrate park. It locate next to the Clearwater Memorial Causeway. This bridge become the monument of the park and pleasant to look at. The July Fourth celebration is huge here. It drawn thousands of people in this park and the security is step up for the event goer. 

Clearwater Pierce Street Market also drawn people gather in this area. Music venue is often conduct here. It is good city park make the Clearwater to celebrate. The park is at the Harbor Bluff Water Front. They are shield from the Gulf Mexico. Which is make the water taxi from the beach to the city is very smooth accessible. The water taxi also connect the Clearwater Marine Aquarium from the famous Winter dolphin. If you feel not to drive more, you can park there and take the water taxi then take the trolley back to aquarium. You can enjoy the water ride. 

I love to come to this place to enjoy my time with friends. Many concert hold here. Enjoy the open sky and the music is a treat

Decent restaurant at the island. The outside sitting area can view the boat dock. You can reach here with the boat or car. The restaurant has modern look interior design. The bar area connect inside and outside with circular bar. 

We have order the lunch menu with lobster roll, salad, and grilled grouper sandwich. The lobster roll looks good with three bun height roll. The grouper come with one side. I have the french fried as a side. The grouper is firm and fresh but the grilled technique need to be improved. It need slightly burn to bring out the meat taste. 

The food came out in very quick time. They must have good kitchen help. I like this way. The service is very good compared to many restaurant. The management of this restaurant is reach the customers goal.

Near Pinellas Park for economic food. It is a Mexican place but has some good enough tacos. Space is very small. Not much of seat but it has the good food. 

I have the Lamb, steak and pastor tacos. They are tasty and quick. It take me less than 30 minutes from order to finished the food and paying. It is fast paced food compared to any fast food restaurant. Price is reasonable and average among the taco joint. 

Service is good and precise. They do have the tamales, steak, grilled shrimp or fried whole fish if you want to spend a little more.

J C has good Caribbean flavor with spicy twist. This restaurant opened during pandemic. It need local love to support them. The restaurant now only accept 14 customers at a time during pandemic. Limited seating. I got a to go order. 

I got the jerk chicken and the oxtail. The jerk chicken has good spicy kick on it. The chicken skin is delicious. The marinated it into the bone. I like that way. The oxtail has thick soupy marinated outside. The meat is fall off the bone. Both dishes come with coconut flavor bean rice. It was delicious. They do have choices on salad or cook cabbage. I would suggest you go for the cabbage. 

From order to pick up is about 15 minutes. Call ahead will be needed. The lunch menu only for weekday. The weekend price same as dinner which I said they are at the high side.

It is a local favorite Italian food. It is definitely one of the kind Italian food near Wesley Chapel. Very delicious and authentic. Family own and only store. 

With that said. Let get inside the food. We started with the garlic knots. It has eight of them. It has garlic butter sauce. I would suggest take two of the knots out and look into bottom of the plate for garlic. That is the best part of these knots. You will need to dig to the garlic itself. 

Our entrees is Cioppino. This is a seafood dish. This dish enough to feed minimum three may four. It is seafood combination with pasta in red tomato sauce. The dish is homemade Linguine with baby clam, mussels, shrimp and top with fried calamari. It is like appetizers on top of the meal. I would the shrimp is not bouncy fresh but good hard meat. I believe this is the area they can be easily improved. As a result they are not really solid 4 stars. Since they give a lot of food. It remains 4 stars.

Tonight experience is about 4 stars. We have a reservation on upstairs. The food is as good as last time I have remembered. After first plate 60% of the food is gone. I have enough but some of my friends went down the floor to get the food and they are kind of clean out. I would not call this as buffet. I only can call it as a feast.

Following Coty review and try this place out. Very Good Vietnamese sandwich cafe. It has the local flavor. It located almost like a little Vietnamese town. It near the Vietnamese supermarket. 

Other than the sandwich, they also serve boba cold smoothie. I have the avocado slush. No bad at all. I also order the BBQ pork and the ham sandwich. The BBQ pork is typical char siew pork. But their own type BBQ sauce. It is ok. 

Overall they are good taste. You can get everything under $10 for quick snack. Since is order fro counter, tip is up to you.

About 3.5 stars. The drive through can be faster. It take some time to clear the line due to single window. The recent new addition is the smoke house chicken. This bourbon black pepper flavor. It was delicious especially the coating. Definitely you need to give a try for the new recipe. 

The chicken skin is crispy. Brown sugar and pepper coated. It is a good delicious chicken with capture the juiciness. It come with gravy mash potatoes and a sweet top coated biscuit. I have not been to church chicken for long time. But this is a recipe to keep.

This is a Spain cuisine restaurant with music venue at weekend. You can book a private event. It is quite a busy booking. Sometimes the booking is a wedding rehearsal or baby shower. 

The food of the restaurant is average for Spain cuisine. But I would say try their tapas. It is great to enjoy their tapas at the weekend and have some wine with live flamenco guitar music. They have the music every week end. Please check their calendar. 

The reason they are four stars is they have the flamenco dance and dinner show on every month. The show team has three female dancers and one male dancer. Man oh man! They are good. Very move is a posture of art. The flamenco guitar add the twist of the show. It almost like a whole band. I would said this is the best flamenco show in the Bay Area.

Good healthy choice. I would recommend this place. They are USF student and faculty favorite. The food is just like it Name. Fresh and good for you. 

We have an office lunch and we have a group order of 8. I got the Power Bowl and the Ahi Tuna. The power bowl is saute'ed carrots, kale slaw, brown rice and quinoa mixed with almonds, raisins, goat cheese and homemade kale-basil pesto. I am ok with the kale basil pesto sauce. But the salad bowl is great because it has the pre mix sauce in it. 

The Ahi tuna was seared correctly. I believe the outside is coated with spice that very close to all bay seasoning. The seafood is good since the tuna is sushi grade. If you feel like to cut down your protein, this is your good place. The eight orders we got was correct per the order.

Previously this location was occupied by the other taco food truck call El Charrito. Now it is new food truck for this place and also serve taco. I got here before the rain. Thanks goodness they have overhead cover to allow the customer to stay dry next the the food truck. It has about three table under the tent if you decide to eat there. 

Today I have the steak, pastor, carnitas, and lengua taco. All tacos are $2 except lengua is $2.50. All taco come with 2 corn tortillas in case you break one and the other can be addition protection from the meat to fall apart. The pastor pork has a lot of flavor. It is the different way to marinate the pork I have seen for all my taco experience. The taco is tasty and good for snack or quick lunch. Food delivery is quick. Don't need to wait long.

This hospital is clean and good facilities. Usually at the January and March I have the high allergy sensitive with my breathing system. I usually take zertec 10 mg to prevent my running noise. But I still sneezing due to sensitive pollen condition. When I came to this hospital the sneezing stop. The hospital must has some kind of allergen filter system that allow me to breath better. I always joking about go away vacation from Florida or any part of United State during pollen season that save me suffering from pollen. But I think I found the place that close to home without pollen-the hospital. Ha!ha!  

This hospital have great facilities. Their ER room is well staff with veteran nurses. The cardiac care unit (CCU) is great with modern equipment. Their ICU is not as beautiful as the CCU. The Peppin building has a nice entrance.  This is a great hospital to visit. Don't take vacation here, the room of all hospital is expensive compare to any hotel. :)

If you like coffee, hips, music, express yourself, listen to other, this may be your place. Every Monday they have blue jam then open mic. You can go express your self. 

They have ton of coffee mix here. I would said the menu is thick. I am not sure I will able to finish all. They have coffee name after TV series like banshee, TV movie Beowulf, Queen Mary and more. This may be the only coffee place that my wife can drink the decafe and able to sleep at night past 12 pm. 

Some night, you can practice joke telling to see it work. The place has very interesting furniture and chair. The center stage is locate very center in the shop. They also music live performance at some night. Pretty much every seat is good. There are book you can pick from the shelf. It is very strange coffee shop that is opened after 6 pm.

About 4.5 stars restaurant. Close to 5. I like the food here. This restaurant really have a charm in Tampa Bay Area. A long history that survived for that long should have they secret of success. They do have one of the best court yards and party room. 

They cuisine is Mexico St Miguel region food. I got the Enchiladas Miguel. This dish top with St Miguel Enchiladas sauce is really good. Not sure where they mixed this sauce. But is really good. The grilled beef is great beef and good marinated in the Enchiladas. I would definitely recommend this dish at lunch. 

My wife have the Chile Relleno. This dish is interesting. It is Poblano Pepper fill with spicy pork. Basically you have to open up the pepper to see the spicy pork inside. Great presentation. 

For the appetizers we have the ceviche. Mexican ceviche is different than most Latin ceviche. It is shrimp and scallops toss with avocado, olives, cilantro with their homemade cocktails sauce. It does not use lime. Very interesting. 

Service just good. May be need more attentive. My waiter is too busy on other table. Sign of area need improvement.

This is Chicago style fried chicken and fish. One of the kind in Tampa Bay Area. It is located on Northview Hills neighborhood. Just 1/2 miles south of Hillsborough Avenue on N 34 street. The actual address an street is actually on the Orsborne Ave. next to beauty salon. 

I would said call ahead and order. They fried their food after you have ordered it. It take at least 15 minutes wait. Worth a while to get the fresh fried food. We got the two pieces leg and thigh meal. The coating is special. You can request hard fried which mean longer. The chicken is juicy. I like the coating. That is something different. 

Other than chicken, they have gizzards, catfish, basa, whiting, shrimp and nuggets. This choice has side items or you can choose their side items.

We were here for the burger week. My wife look up the burger week special and feel that Birch and Vine is best on the list. So we have decided to paid them visit. 

The restaurant is part of the Birchwood hotel. The restaurant is at the ground floor. The interior design is beautiful with 6 partial circle booth. The wine display is impressive. At least thousand bottles of wine in temperature control room attached to the dining hall wall. 

My wife got the burger week surf and turf. This burger top with big pieces of lobster and bottom with high grade burger beef patty. This is an impressive dish. I got the grill lamb chop. It was good flavor. 

Overall they are measured up with chef skill on the food. If their service can be better, they probably 5 stars. The service is a bit slow. The ambiance is nice to have romantic dinner.

TBD is not to be determined. It is Tea Bowls and Desserts. Get it. This kind of Filipino food with boba tea and nice dessert. Certainly is worth a visit for your money. Imagine you can get a bowls with boba tea for $10. Not many place has that kind of price. If you order a bowls of food, the drinks is $2 extra. Each bowl roughly $8. Great deal. 

My Friend Mark was here make me book mark this place. We got the chicken Adobo and the beef Kaldereta bowls. The chicken adobo has good flavor. Especially the rice is very good. My wife like it. The beef is no bad either. I would said for the price is good enough. We also order the combo with drinks. Only $2 extra. I got the Fancy Fruit Basket herbal tea with boba and added honey for sweetness. It is good and the boba is soft. My wife got the Berry Hibiscus tea with boba. I like that one too. Next definitely try their lychee dragon pearl tea. This is a ball shall Tea leave. Must be interesting to sip. 

The owner was very friendly.

It is about 3.5 stars. Yama is newly open. As a new restaurant, they will try to give something more to keep the customers come back. So far they are doing that now. At least keep a good quantity of the fish meat. While they doing that, it is the best time to visit. 

The reason I have them 3.5 stars is due to one of the sushi give stomach problem. Overall they are very good. One comment for the sushi is the chef special roll have too many choices with imitation crab meat. I would suggest removing some crab and put fish meat or two types of fish meat. 

I do like the crawfish hand roll, crazy California roll, dragon roll, king Kai roll, red dragon roll. The US 41 roll if they can change out the crab meat to fish will improve the roll a lot.

This a cafe and restaurant. This is different restaurant who has the similar name. We like to give it a try. They have good Cuban sandwich. Other than that, the Cuban cuisine is good here also. I would start to say this is very affordable restaurant. I can get meal same price like Mc Donald and is full cook meal. Go figure.

I have ordered the Vaca Frita with two side of sweet plantains and the collar white bean soup. The soup is really excellent. The plantains did not over burn. Perfectly prepared. I have order my Vaca Frita extra crispy which mean burn a bit. When the flank steak burn, it taste better. 

Our time here is great. This was the second restaurant stop of the night. We are not really hungry but to see what they have. Good service. The only thing I can say is only one server entire night. I think is overloaded for her. But she got it and very good on handling it.

Cute restaurant with good sushi and ok Thai food. This sum the restaurant for the food. To me I would go for the sushi. Restaurant is not busy during lunch. But a lot of take out. 

I have the Pad Kee Mao (drunken noodle) and my friend has the Pad Thai. I specify ask my noodle to to very dry which mean on the wok longer. But the kitchen doesn't do it. The waiter only tell may be next time I am here they will try again. But when is the next time. My friend like his pad Thai. We also have the Chirashi. The chirashi is better than than their Thai food. The sushi rice at the bottom was well marinated. The serve with nine pieces of sashimi and very thick cut. They masago and dry seaweed leave sprinkles over it. 

Service is good. But I think the instructions to the kitchen can be better.

The food truck was sold to different owner. The current food truck place about a block north of old location. Since this is the new owner, please disregard the Yelp deal in Yelp website since the last owner did not take it down. 

The only complaint I have is the wait for the food is 40 minutes. There were three people in front of me. But the wait is not good for just third order. This is the area they have to improve. 

We may be the last person they honor the Yelp deal. The mofongo is excellent. Cannot say the same for the rest. I have the steak mofongo. The steak is average. However I would said the Tripleta meat is tasty. But my wife said she is thirsty after having the Tripleta sandwich. Not sure is the MSG or not. 

This is 3.5 stars not 4 stars food truck. Price is decent for the item we have order.

La Dulce is interesting Mexican dessert store. Finally we have one like this kind dessert store in Tampa. I saw this kind of dessert store in Lakeland. They serve different kind of fresh fruit dessert. One thing they definitely can improve on is to put a picture of the item in menu. By reading most of it, I kind of lost in translation. 

We got the mangonada. This fruit mix is common on many Mexican dessert store. This one just regular mangonada without enhancements. But still good. I got chocolate coated strawberry popsicles. I like the coating with coconut flakes. It is good to have during summer time. We also got sweet corn with cheese. 

Overall is good. Not in great level. They do got a lot attention to local. They are at the side street of the MLK Blvd below the bridge.

To locates this taco place, you have to look at the back alley way. They do not have the store front facing the street side. It is within the Hillsborough Ave Farmers Market. It is open air taco place with a roof over the taco trailer. Good thing that many open air taco place do not have it is a place to wash your hand before handle the taco. They have the running water sink you can wash your hand. 

We have ordered three tacos - Pastor, Carnitas, and the Steak taco. The best is the steak taco. It come with seasoning and pan grilled. The carnitas is tasty also. Their shredded pork was marinated. They have single corn tortillas which may break easily. The bottle opener affix the the trailer need to replace since it is rusted. 

Overall our experience here is good. They have some room to improve. Their green hot sauce that go with the taco stand out.

Poke LuLu has fresh seafood on poke and good quality. This restaurant is a vendor in the food court. During the weekend they got a lot of attention. Line build up during lunch time. The customer are here to get poke and boba drink. 

We got their House Poke. If you like different protein with two or more, this preset bowl may be your choice. The poke has salmon, shrimp, and spicy tuna. Which make this bowl good combo. My with have create your own bowl. She pitch the eel. It come with two big pieces of eel. The bowl is bigger than the House poke and better price. 

We like both of our poke. Good quality and quantity. We also got the Thai tea boba. It is tall and skinny cup. Which usually don't fit well with cup holder. But it look good. The drink is good.

This restaurant name like we need to eat like a cat and left the fish with bone and head. Fortunately, the chef is kind enough to fillet for all the customers. Personally, I like whole fish to eat and left only the bone. With that said, their brand is to have good seafood. I always have good respect for this restaurant. 

We start with corn chowder with lump crabmeat. The chowder is great. However I would suggest sautéed the crab meat which will make this soup more superior. 

Our entrée are the grilled red fish. This very good dish. It is not in the regular menu. Redfish is bit harder to catch. The meat definitely is nice and good. It is accompanied the string green bean and crawfish etouffee. This is very excellent dish. 

Our next entrée is sirloin and crab cake. I like the crab cake but the sirloin is average. It come with two side and I have crab fried rice. Again, the crab meat need to include in the fried rice while they stir fry. Not added with broil lumb crab meat. 

The service is great. It has seamless coordination.

Authentic Cuisine # 58. Moroccan Cuisine. 

First Moroccan food in Tampa Bay Area that I have. The Moroccan restaurant is located near USF area which has a lot of Muslim residents is good choice to support the restaurant. Their cuisine is unique. I will try this food here and will compare them when I travel to Morocco in two months. 

We got the couscous with meat and veggies. This dish only serve at Friday and Sunday. It is a special dish. The dish cost is $16, I think this is a higher than average around this area with not much of meat. The couscous is amazing. The meat is so so. But the veggies is really good. May be I am hungry. 

My wife got a traditional dish with chicken tagine. This chicken serve with olive sauce. The sauce is wonderful. I like this dish better. It serve with pita. The sauce and pita go together. Lovely dish. 

Overall our experience is great. People are nice here. My recommendation is the chicken tagine.

It is about 3.5 stars. This is my third Liquid Nitrogen ice cream store I have visit. This one considering is on higher than average pricing. Many other store already including one topping in one price. Here topping is additional 65 cents. 

I like liquid nitrogen ice cream because I can select any flavor or combination of the flavor to mixed the flavor that you have never thought off. We got the tiger blood and pistachio flavor mixed in. This is different ice cream that mad scientist can made. 

I like it very much for the flavor. It is cool to see the liquid nitrogen smoke under the blue light. Make this alien encounter.

This restaurant has good authentic use of Indian spice along with fresh ingredients to prepare the food. This very sum up of this review. It is close to 4.5 stars for the way they have prepared the food. I like is very much. The reason they are 4 stars is the quantity they have served in the dinner time. Their portion is small for the dinner. But some people just eat a lot of rice with curry sauce. 

If I come to the buffet, I may have rate them 5 stars. We have the Fish Molee and the Beef Malabar Curry. The fish is Basa and fried first before the curry. Love the turmeric, green chili, ginger and coconut milk. This is a good dish to enjoy because the coconut curry is out of the wold. 

The beef malabar is good spice. We east the meat and take the sauce home. It is still good to enjoy with the rice. The spice is deep touch with nice medium spicy curry.

Alvarez has a good affordable food. Highly recommended. This is actually their second store. It actually a good restaurant even they have second store. Many restaurant has second restaurant will not be able to keep up on the second place. I hope they continue to strive for the best for both store. 

I got the steak quesadilla. Normally they don't serve steak quesadilla, they only serve ground beef quesadilla. Because of my request, they make a special steak quesadilla from chop steak. It was quite good. The other dish is ground beef burrito. It is fat burrito and big enough for hungry person. The last dish is the Plátanos Rellenos. It use sweet plantain as base. Top with cook ground beef, lettuce and Mexicano cheese. Delicious. 

I order the dish then come back to pick up. It is still good when eat at home.

Post office may be past technology for communication since email, social media, web base advertising is very convenient. We like to support our post office as much as possible to keep the door open. 

This post office has walk in counter for mailing, packaging, registered mail, money order and more. When the line get longer, the window of the counter open. There is automated counter outside that you can buy stamp and mail. This self service station is easy to use. It also have paid copy machine if you need a photo copy. 

I hope this post office keep open and serve the people here.

Solid 4 stars restaurant. The restaurant located on the south of Bush very close to Bush and Armenia. It has good Peruvian stir fried. Stir fried technique here definitely has the Chinese cuisine secrets. 

We have order the Anticicho de Corazon. The grilled beef heart. This is not the best in the bay but very close. One good thing is they give you a lot quantity in the dish. Definitely the quantity will be count into more stars. It come with two side. The Peruvian golden corn and the slice potatoes. It is the dish I would recommend. 

Our second dish is Lomo Saltado. This typical Peruvian stir fried dish. It come with two side. We have order the yuca and the white rice. The stir fried technique is in high BTU wok like Chinese cuisine. It is one of the best in the bay. 

Service here is attentive. It you looking for good Peruvian. This may be an option for you.

The museum is certainly established and has an old house and garden. Please plan at least 3 hours. One of other tip. They close early beginning November. Don't paid attention to the door entrance hour. It said close at 8 pm but actually close at 4 pm at November. I wish they can notify us before I bought the tickets at 2:30 pm. So check their schedule before buying the tickets. 

The garden section is very nice. It cover wide area of walking. But each section has it beauty. I like it when the decorated for winter light. You can see extra things. The main old house is call the Lily house. It beautiful Lawn in front. It is picture worthy place. 

The museum 3 good floor of art work. Unfortunately the time we have visit is only for one floor. The display has European, African, Asian, Americans, and contemporary art. Each floor may require minimum 45 minutes to finish. The art collection is wide range.

This 3.5 stars restaurant is correct from my fellow Yelper. It is above average for the rating. A few things I like about this restaurant is about their choices on the burger and services to bring the food and clean the table quick enough.

We have been here several time. But this is my first time order the Number 12 burger - The Ahi Tuna. I like their mixed of sauce that on the burger. It has the caramel soy sauce with a bit of sweetness on it. The fish is sushi grade with Panko crusted on the coating and lightly fried. It come with avocado which accommodate well in the burger. We also has the OMG burger number 10. It is double patty close to half pound meat. It has two big pieces of smoke bacon on top. Love it. 

Food is good here. What make them no much competitive is price. Burger range from $7 to $10. Add other side can get you to $14. It is regular restaurant price. I still consider this is a fast food joint but not quite with twist of different in table service. I do like the Gourmet part of the burger.

I like a restaurant has optional by items section. This is a bakery and restaurant combo. Allow you to have a Bakery baked good and food. The seating space is limited. During the pandemic not many people are dining in anyhow. Most of the customers had to go orders.

We also have some takeout orders. We saw some bakeries displays on a glass container. It has a good cheese bake goods. We got some of them. One thing interesting is they sell the food by pieces. We got some Chicharrón, blood sausage, regular sausage, in and empanada.

They also serve some cooked meals like bistec, fry pork, Carne Asada. Overall Our experience is very good. Definitely come back for dinner.

Beirut Cafe was bookmarking forever. Because it was too far for me to reach. I am seldom come this way for food. It was a rare occasion I was here to try. The atmosphere of the restaurant is nice. They have two big table for larger parties. The restaurant capacity is not much, they do utilize the sidewalk sitting. 

I like their sweet. It is definitely similar to middle eastern dessert. We got bird nest pistachio baklava.  Very similar to the one famous Hallab 1881 from Lebanon. Our main dish is the we have the chicken kabab. It is big dish. Since we have previous meal, we only order one dish. The chicken has good marinated spice. It has good grilled technique with maintaining the juicy of the meat. 

We were there at 4 pm. I was going to select the big table because we know no one will come in that time. But they no allow me even no one in the restaurant. May be some leeway is best.

The pub is previously arepa restaurant location. Tonight the pub received a lot of patron due first preseason football games with Jamie Winston. A lot people come to watch Winston first day at Buc. His debut does bring some screaming fans into this pub. 

I was looking if they serve food in this pub. When we asking for the menu, they said they only serve beer. This is original a pub set up. They do have a lot of TV and computerize music jukebox. The jukebox allows selecting the music and playing to all patrons. This is an Irish pub. With that said, Guinness definitely serves here. 

One positive note is the girl at the bar said no food serve here but you can bring your own food to eat here. That is not bad. I see people order pizza and drink beer here. The outdoor sitting is like a beer garden. This is an interesting place that you can bring your own food and party here.

Today I am using their drive through for ordering. It was rain cat and dog. I am happy to see the kiosk order cover section at their drive through without get wet while order. It was without delay at the pick up window to paid and received the order. 

I order the half chicken special. It was well cook with good marinated sauce. The marinated went to skin deep. But flavorful. The rice and bean also good to have. The order was well conducted. Food is good for the drive through and accurate with the order.

The food compare to actual urban area of Tampa is budgetary. It is lesser than Tampa. It become affordable. This restaurant located at US 301 make it easy to access. Everything in historical downtown Zephyrhills is walking distance. So does this restaurant. 

The menu is extensive and all items are under $10. The category divided to appetizer, combo plate, beef noodle, rice platter, fried rice, noodle bowls, egg noodle soup. The selection of protein included grilled pork, grilled shrimp, grilled chicken, grilled beef, fried fish, grilled pork chop, grilled fish and veggies. We got the today special fried frog leg. It come with 8 drum frog leg. This leg is massive. The coating and accompanying sauce are flavorful. 

Our other dish is grilled pork chop rice. It has good enough seasoning. It come with rice, pickle veggies and spring roll. It has large enough portion for a person. Service is good and attentive. Seating is comfortable.

Sam Ash music store should be look like regular music store. However, this music store is way different than any music store. You can see the roman column, vaulted ceiling, statutes, and beautiful chandelier. It is good environment for a music store. Classy look.

If you need a music equipment, you won't be less here. I have been here several time to visit of enjoy my strolling. The classical guitar room is great. Always see someone hold a guitar and play the music there. Free concert. Love the sound of it. The unique thing is they have the drum room with a hanging chandelier. Flex your muscle on the drum set and freely express yourself. Try it out to see what you make off.

The music store provide lesson for the young one and musician to be. Many parent waited at the learning center for their kid. Live performances have been done here. They have open mic night or music performance night too. Check their schedule. Come to check them out and check the next door player school of music.

Are we tired of most of the national chain coffee shop. It is nice to to have a chance in brand name. This local coffee shop located at downtown that serve northern part of the downtown area. They do Catering and provide sandwich and munch. The place is trendy. I like vibrant atmosphere. 

Today I am going for the mocha ice coffee. It is a bit chocolatier but have all the mojo. Good tasty coffee. Just to let all you know, caffeine never affects me. Most of the time I drink coffee is for the flavor and pleasure. They do have good flavor.

Very good burger place. It is very close to 4.5 stars. It has many choices. There are may choices of Black Angus burger. They have good list of burger. 

The restaurant outside seating make it convenience for the dog owners in downtown area. Especially this restaurant is close to Curtis Hixon dog park. I got the glass of beer with burger. Good local beer. For the burger, I got the Franklin Street burger. This burger come with Kaiser Roll bun. I like the bun. The burger has angus beef patty, pull pork, smoke brisket, and bacon. Very complicated combination. By it work and very tasty. Excellent burger. 

Service is good. The turn on light on the outside side so we don't eat at the dark. I also like the skinny fries. Very good fried.

This is the biggest Land and Sea I been to. The area is big. They carry a lot of items including the baked goods. Non to say they have a lot kind of seafood, their meat department has some good selection. 

We were here at Friday searching for boneless beef short rib. We could not find this item in many grocery stores but Land and Sea carry it. When we visited this place they run the special on Friday. BOGO with one pound get one pound free for the short rib. Good deal. I would suggest checking up their special of the day. We also got the mini crab cake for good deal. Some of the special is reduce in price from their regular price. 

They have pre-seasoning food too. You can take home and follow the label instructions to cook. It is convenient. If want some wild caught fish, they also carry it. This store not only carry meat and seafood, they also carry veggies for one stop shopping.

This place holding a lot of young people heart. I can see the average age who visited here is about 30 or below. Somehow this place feel young. The DJ play it music at the bar area. This may be the major attraction. 

We were here for the taco week. It have some deal. But the taco is one of the best quality. We got the three blackened shrimp taco. It come with top as cabbage, pico, avocado, queso fresco, sour cream, sweet thai chili, and cilantro. The shrimp is blackened with southern style. The flavor is good and desirable. 

The margarita is part of the deal with three taco. It is ok not to kill for. Overall our service is great. I would recommend if you come to downtown for light snack and drinks.

I was surprised my credit card company put this store as grocery. It the same way, they sell bread and sandwiches. Not sure the actual category need to be. We were here for their promotion of the buy one sandwich and get sourdough cinnamon bun free. The free bun is actually a sourdough material. Interesting. 

We have two sandwiches. My wife have the Italian sandwich. She start Tampa Sandwich Bread. The selection she got is Italian that come with ham, salami, pepperoni. It is quit good. I have the BST which is come with bacon, tomato, and spinach. My bread is roasted red pepper. The sandwich is good. 

We only need to wait a little while for the preparation. Not bad. I do like the sourdough cinnamon bun. It is quite interesting.

Very interesting brewery. Good thing they have a permanent food truck to keep door open during pandemic. The people who go there are very friendly. Their space is big enough to have many patrons. The put side seating have good setup with plenty of seat. I am not sure they allow dog on the outside. But worth a try. 

The selection of beer is good. I like the Diddy. It is a German Pilsner. The selection includes other like Lager, Stout, Cider, sour beer, wheat beer, bock, IPA, and Ale.  It has good collection. The size is just good.

3.5 stars food truck. This is Puerto Rican food served here. They have mofongo, tostones o papitas. They have good wide selection. This food truck is kind of tuck away from the road. If miss the entrance, you may have to U turn. 

We were here first time to buy a bowl of Carrucho. The marinated conch. It is big pieces. But we feel that taste like chicken. Not sure is the best since we are not best judge of the Puerto Rican cuisine. 

When come to second visit, we got the pulpo. It is the octopus. This one is much better. It does come in good chop amount of the octopus. The marinated sauce accompanying well with octopus. Great small dish with wine at home with football games. 

Overall is good. Definitely will go for the pulpo. Food here is a bit pricey for food truck.

Zephyrhills start to has their own brewery. This one is located at downtown prime location. They have the outside beer garden and street view seat. Many people has use this advantage for the viewing of Christmas parade.

I have try their Belgium Blonde. This is light beer with good taste. The brewery is busy and the patrons are sharing the table with each other and have good conversations. They have table order service is you don't want to go to counter to get your beer. 

The indoor is nice and well lid. Plenty of seat to host big party. I bring my food there while enjoying a glass.

Solid 4 stars. It is because the cost vs value of the food. There a few positive thing about this place. The service is excellent. The store provide the complimentary brownie cake with coconut flakes. Love it. It good promotion to get the restaurant going. 

We three taco combo. The taco is divided to classic and specialty. Any in the specialty taco add $0.50 each taco. We got the campechano, grilled grouper, and grilled shrimp tacos. I paid extra dollars for the specialty taco. Which worth it. The combo plate come with chip, salsa, and a drink. Not bad at all. My wife got the steak quesadilla. The steak is well grilled. 

I would recommend the campechano and grilled shrimp tacos. It was delicious. Food come out quick with not much wait. Seating is limited but enough for the dine in conditions.

Rock and roll in food sum the restaurant. One of the founder is Gene who is KISS group. They restaurant is very popular at weekends. As a result, we pick a weekday to avoid the crowds. I like the set up with rock and roll music videos at the background. High ceilings open dining hall. Choices of inside or outside dining. Love the set up. 

We start with the Mango Habanero wings. It come with 9 wings with $1.4 per wings is in the high price side. The wings did a good job with ghost pepper. My entree is the Blackened Redfish. This dish come with vegetables medley and rice. It top with crawfish sauce. Crawfish also taste good like Cajun. A very rare dish to have. My wife have the Carolina Slow Roasted Pork. The sauce is honey mustard sauce which is very similar to the BBQ we have when we travel to North Carolina. It come with steam veggies and we upgraded to sweet potatoes fried. 

I like the happy hour drinks. I got the house Margaritas and it is big for me. Please keep it up. It is the reason customers coming back.

If you have two thousands people and need a lot rooms for classes, this is the place in St. Louis. I was here for a national steel conference. And the facility is perfect to accommodate so many people. 

The exhibition hall is big to fit the steel cutting machine, demonstration and more with indoor hall. There also room to accommodate lunch and cocktails for many people. The hallway is wide with minimum 30 to 40 feet for registration, walking. Bathrooms can be found in many corner of the center for convenient. 

The entrance has two locations with drive by drop off. One at the back of 7th street and the other at the other is at Washington Avenue.

This restaurant has good Thai taste. The only thing is they didn't turn the spicy heat up when I ask them for Thai hot. Overall they are good restaurant. 

We start with the Kai Tod Had Yai the blacken chicken wing. The wing has some marinated spice. This is southern Thai dish. Blacken wings with deep fried. The spice is above average. It come enough wing to share. 

The entrée are Grouper Chu Chee and curry pork. The curry pork dish is good. But the the Grouper Chu Chee is my flavor. The grouper was slightly fried with crispy coating. It top with their homemade curry. According to the menu is a mix of coconut milk and soy sauce. It is great and healthy fish to have. 

During our visit, the traffic of the Christmas Day is low. But they may be the few restaurants that open for that day. The service is good and attentive.

It is about 4.25 stars. I like their new location in Tampa. I have been to their St. Pete location but this Tampa location is much better. I like the high ceilings open space. It brings value and comfort level to the customers. The ambiance and decoration is very nice. An open space with kitchen viewing available. 

We got the Housemade Sausage and Roasted Pepper pizza. It is good size pizza. The ingredients is very nice. But the the cheese and ingredients are not spread to outer edge of pizza which creates a lot of crust area. This area they need improvement. 

I also got the Wood Grilled Marinated Skirt Steak. This is my favorite steak. It has good qualities and quality of the skirt steak. It is marinated with sweet sauce. It was cook to requested temperature. It also come with broccolini and mash potatoes. I also like the herd green sauce the have on the steak. I hope they don't reduce the steak quantity in the future. 

Service is good. Seating is comfortable, spacious and good lighting in compare to St Pete location.

The Green Fairy Is our Mayor of Tampa Bob Buckhorn. He is the one who sprinkle the green dust all over the Curtis Hixon Park. Thanks to this event, we can enjoy the Saints Patrick Day with the city special touch. River O Green definitely brings people out and provide green river in the mixed celebrate green event. 

The count down started 11:00 am from five. The police, vendor and coast guard boat join in for paint the Hillsborough River green. Green dye was drop from the back of boat engines. Soon entire river changed to bright green color. The US coast guard boat shooting the green water out to create green fountain in the middle of the river. 

The entire park has vendor display their item including the food and drinks truck. The amphitheater has musical show on schedule. Kid running and so do the dog.

The memory and story of this is museum is told by our Bay Area Jews. It is close to our heart. These stories is definitely part of our living testimony for our residents here. 

The museum is split by two part. The downstair mainly have the most telling to the holocaust incident during the German World War. Poland got hit hard then the most in Europe. There were 3 million Jewish population before the war. After the war, only 80,000 survived. It is a lot of killing and displacement of the Jewish people. It is a lesson of sad human race history. I hope it is never again in the world. I like the display of shoes and clothing, who died in the holocaust. There was s also memory for hero who save people and fight against the war. 

The second floor is very much special edition to remember the great music producer Bill Graham. You can see the sixty how the music concert was done. Some great music was play then. The billboard has some interesting design. I was never guest Mick Jagger, Tina Turner, Madonna, and Bob Dylan were play the music in one concert. It is interesting.

Jin China is a fast food American style. I have been many Chinese fast foods and I never like any of it. However, this one is the most welcome among all Chinese fast food. My review is only base on the lunch. 

I usually like to stop on the newly opened restaurant and decided to try this one. The lunch special is really worth the value. You are here not for the great taste of Chinese food but for the something quick and fresh. The special is $5.50 with lunch cook at the spot and a soft drink. Very good deal. I have the schezuan pork with fried rice. The veggies in the pork are crispy which mean very fresh. Like it that way. Some restaurants don't have the controls of the material. This restaurant is next to MD oriental market and they can get fresh produce immediately.  

Please call ahead because needs 10 minutes to prepare.

If you looking for healthy food, Luv Fresh offer hot meal, Açaí Bowl, Wrap and Salad. It is good for food conscious customers. Their item is also good for the older generation. It has the smoothie too for quick diet. 

We try this restaurant to see what they can offer. I think the restaurant is about 3.5 stars. We were here for the hot bowl. Since they provide a good quantity of food, I would said is a good start. I also like the variety of the grains and veggies that add into it. We have the Heart Healthy and Power Luv bowl. I like a good piece of salmon there. The power luv has goat cheese which I don't like. Goat cheese need to be optional because not all people like it. 

A few things they can improve. A free water station will help. The food need to have more flavor. I think their food is too flavorless. Sauce should be a selection instead of pair with each bowl. Let customers choose the sauce. Square box is difficult to nix the food at corner of box. However I like the presentation of food in square box. Food has less salt or sweetness. Most customers like a better taste bud. I think they have potential. But they need to think how to compete in this area with the existing restaurant.

We were expect bar food before we arrive at this place. The restaurant look like normal bar. Not many customers during weekdays. We look at the menu and feel the items are very interesting. Not many place serve hog fish, this is one of the few I can count. 

I got the main dish as grilled blackened hog fish. It come with fried and the coleslaw. The portion of fish is big enough. Fish is fresh. It has good blackened taste. 

Our appetizers are the the Irish Stew and Aran Island Shepherd's Pie. The Irish stew serve in the sourdough bread bowl. The stew meat was slow cook in red wine and Guinness beer. It is delicious. The Shepherd pie is different than most shepherd pie I have. It serve on potatoes skin. 

As you can see, this is not you typical bar food. The chef has good skill. Definitely a different type of food with great restaurant standard. I will definitely come back for the hog fish.

This ice cream store opened during pandemic. That was the time that the pandemic just began. I glad that they still operate and serving the community. We wish they hang on the business and continue. Their story includes good ice cream flavor, sandwiches and empanadas. 

The flavor is very interesting. It includes mint chocolate chip, mermaid (cotton Candy), beach bum ( coconut, caramel, chocolate and almond), sea salt kisses and more. My wife have the Santa Letter - it is a lot of stuff including brownie, mint and other stuff. It is interesting. I have the eggnog. I love the taste of seasonal flavors. 

We got beef empanadas. It is good snack for the night. They fried the empanadas fresh from order. We did not go for the the Nutella empanadas. It must be interesting. May be next time we will try it. Overall the store allow taste try. Which is good for the customers.

Big area for dog park where the city set aside for downtown living. The area was fence for big dog and small dog. My friend come to this place a lot with his dog. 

This park has a rule to keep it clean and safe. The rule such as dog owner clean up and vaccinated plate. It also said the dog must under voice comments train .

I always a fan for Jersey Mike. They are just few sandwich store has the capicola ham. This is a spicy ham that has some kick of spiciness in it. I usually have them add extra meat with the ham. Then top with lettuce and tomato. I have the mikes way spice including salt, pepper, red vinegar and oil. Lastly have them top with two strips of bacon. That will be my lunch. 

Their sandwich is the best that I like. Although the local Cuban sandwich is great, but I pick over Jersey Mike's sandwich. 

You can get a combo with drink and chip. I like their southern sweet tea. You can cumulate point for free sandwich with your home phone. The service is quick here. They also has numerous hot sub to select including the Philly Cheese Steak. This location is a bit small compare to the one that Bruce b Down near USF.

Boca mean mouth in Spanish. Which is the restaurant goal to create yummy food into mouth. The restaurant self parking is actually a block away on the west. 

Today lunch we have order the 7-spice yellow fin tuna and cilantro Florida grouper sandwich. The grouper sandwich comes with lettuce tomato for the sandwich and the side is the French fried with Parmesan cheese. The grouper is fresh but the fish is smaller portion compare to typical grouper sandwich in Florida restaurant. 

The 7-spices yellow fin tuna is impressive. They have seared the tuna outwardly. The inside raw tuna is dark red. The dark red color indicates the high grade tuna. The tuna spice is well balance with the seared outward meat. It came with two sides. The baby Bok Choy and black sticky rice. My mom use to cook the dark sticky rice in the process of porridge and add the coconut extract. The chef here cooks the black sticky rice with kimchi. The taste is very sophisticate. The Bok Choy was stir fry and grill it is good. The tuna actually go well with the sweet soy sauce reduction. I have asked for more since the sauce only drizzling a few on the plate. 

This is urban herb concept restaurant. You can select you own vegetable that is display in the restaurant. Good concept, but I prefer they are in the control environment. I mean out of customer contact. Because you never know who actually sneeze on it.

Overall the service is good, but the lunch needs to serve faster. When we receive our food it takes close to 25 minutes. There is no pre-meal item like bread or munch.

I have a gift card can be use and we are happen to be close to this store. The Parking lot looks empty at 2:30 during that time. The store may be only three customers including us. May be this is the best time to shop since they are not busy. 

This is the biggest and nicer ABC that I have been through. I like the high ceiling that make the store elegant. They have many sections like wine, beer, spirit, imports and more. I am surprised that they have a big section of the hand roll cigar section. The display is very nice. Some of them is our local hand roll cigar. 

I use my gift card get some of the import beer and American brew. I got the Blonde Guinness the American Lager. The taste is average like regular American beer. Guinness usually has stouts which is very good when you age it. But this Blonde is just average. I was surprised that Guinness has a brewery in U.S. I also have the Innis and Gunn from Scotland.  This is the rum oak aged beer. This is very interesting beer for winer (wine enthusiastic) like me. The experience has oak flavor and in beer. Nice taste. 

The beer price is average compare to other wine and spirits store. I like this store that is well presented, nice parking lot, clear label section.

Fishing Man's haven. My wife jokes about this place. She said this is a men's world. A lot of man here. It is a good place for single women; this is the land of opportunity that they can find the future boyfriend. Be the Fisher of Man! Funny, I kind of agree with her.  

I have been to the biggest Bass Pro Shop in U.S. at Springfield Missouri with 500,000 square feet. I have seen the best of Pro Shop there. In comparison, this is a small one but it has the best need for outdoor activities. They are selling the larger item such as boat to waders. Any kind of fishing needs, they have the largest selection. They also have hunting, clothing, camping, shoe section. 

I always get exciting about pro shop is the fresh water fish tank. The fish here is a bit tiny compare to other pro shop. The reason behind is they need to have room to grow. 

Today is the day after the opening and they already run out the size of the waders I want. I am buying this wader for bridge inspection when I need to walk to shallow water bridge. I have to order online. I see they display better recreation boat in Missouri store and they are cheaper there. The Tahoe recreation boat here does not have nice color design. Not as attractive as other store. (I am not talking about fishing boat). 

The hunting section is interesting. You can see gun display for hunting. You also can find the chair strap to tree trunk high up for bow and arrows hunting. 

Overall I like this store. Same as all the Pro Shop, they have a restaurant section for the food. I was told by the server is an hour and 40 minutes wait at 6:30. We did not try it yet. The salt water tank is still under pH balance. No Fish. I will be back to try the restaurant later.

Bloody day in English expression is a bad day. However, we are in the Bloody Mary festival and the party is on. Thanks to a friend provide the tickets that we can attend this festival. We are excited to attend this event with a group of yelpers. 

The event certainly have many vendors some of them try to impress, some doing the right thing and some just have plain Bloody Mary. The ticket include one free drinks and all sample. Music playing at the big stage and all the food trucks are hugging along the area. I like the setting in Curtis Hixon Park to hold the event with Hillsborough River in the Back Drop. I certainly have too many Bloody Mary in one day. I have tried them all and I like the Ella's, Datz, Acropolis, and Roux. Some of them are spicy for my wife.

At the end of the day I have wonderful time since we have a group went to this event. Love the event when you have a wonderful time. We went on the riverwalk with solo musician playing at the background.

Little restaurant and family own Peruvian cuisine has many local come here to enjoy the food. It has large enough influence that close to Chinese side of cooking in the menu.  I usually do not paid attention to those. However, they also have many choices in the menu in Peruvian side. 

We have order the Ceviche de Pescado to start. It was good Ceviche with raw fish in lemon juice. Not too sour. Our entrees are the Bisteck a la Parrilla (Grilled Steak) and the Arroz con mariscos (Seafood in creole rice). The steak is just ok average. The seafood is something. It has the shrimp, squid, octopus, mussels. It is good when they are together. 

Food is good and the service is on point. I have the cicha moranda for the drink. You can feel is home made not from the can. Good enough sweetness. I like this purple corn drink.

A dollar sandwich day is the time we visited them. It is a good deal during May 2 special sale. The sub list fro 1 to 6 has $1 sale during that day. Although they are filling but after two sub is enough. 

The promotion is from 4pm to 8 pm  that day. I applaud to them even there is a sale, they did run out of material. The sales item include ham , tuna, roast beef, Italian, veggies sandwich. They also did slow down because of sales. The line build up to outside of the door with 20 to 30 people at the line but the wait is less than 10 minutes. 

Roast beef is ok but the Italian sub is bit above averages. This is about 3.5 stars. But because they did not deny people at the door or make you wait, I gave them additional half star round up. The people behind the counter always smiling. Good customer service.

Fuku is very nicely cute restaurant. The owners are the chef and manager husband and wife team. This restaurant has some characters that is pleasant to gather here. We have a group of 7 was easily seated comfortable. 

Our food is came out rather quick. We have a spicy ramen to share. I like miso soup base ramen here. It is not too salty. The ramen is cook perfectly. The garnish is nice and they have fish cake in this ramen other than thin slice of pork. We have order the spicy tuna, sashimi and sushi combination, shumai, and the softshell crab bento box. Some good some average. 

I like my experience here, the food is good value in downtown area. The service is good. I like this mom and pop shop that show the local color. This is good restaurant to have in this area.

Good sushi can be found here. The lunch special give you few buck different compare to dinner. With that said, their sushi price is reasonable also at dinner. I have book mark this place due several of my fellow Yelper friends check in. 

They have good interior work pleasant to customers. We were here for lunch. The items we have try are spicy tuna, lobster roll, jaguar roll, hibachi combination with selection of salmon and scallops. Their sushi chef prepared correctly. Spicy tuna has good mixed of ingredients and taste. This is my first time with the fried eel roll - Jaguar roll. It is good to try it. The lobster roll has real lobster inside. 

The hibachi combo is good way to enjoy. The scallops are sea scallops compared to most of the places give you bay scallops. The salmon was sear with outside crispy. The combo come with fried rice, noodle, veggies, ginger salad and soup. 

Service is good. Sushi rice a bit soft.

Unexpected boat dock with a restaurant next to it. It is a favorite place for many boaters if they dock this place for a drink or dinner. I have to warn you this place close at 8 pm and they may be run out of food to serve after 7 pm. Come early. 

This place is pack when we arrive at 6:10 pm. We lucky to share a table with the other couples while watching the sunset. We order the oyster and a moment later the waiter tell us they run out. They were generous to give us a corn fritters on the house. The fritters is very nice with chunky meat of clam. It is very good. We order blackened grouper platter. They are very thick and blackened well. 

The food is good, unfortunately they run out their catch and have no much things for your choice. It is nice place to watch sunset if you are here before 6 pm. Great dock for boater with direct access.

I have night work last night and I am free to lunch anyway today. We choose to come to this Koizi location instead of the Tampa Palm location. The chef here is better than the Tampa Palm Koizi. They must learn their lesson from the older Koizi. The restaurant is bigger and the food comes out faster. 

At Tampa Palm the line and wait is longer. Here I was seated immediately. Like it. Interior is well decorated and spacious. We have order many thing from the menu. This is our first time we order the QQ ball-Chicken and Beef grounded ball. It serves with sweet sauce. I like their habachi with Sirloin. The meat is soft and tender. 

We also have the Mt. Fuji Roll looks like lava flows from the top. I always order my favorite spicy tuna roll. It did not disappoint me. The rainbow roll interior crab meat is marinated with flavor. Compare to Bay Area endless sushi, Koizi has better flavor.

Cold Stone was our second choice tonight since other desert place is long line due to graduation. But we happy to be here with no line. They have out side sitting but the night is cold to sit outside. 

Cold Stone Is a decent ice cream store. The R & D of the ice cream did very good job to create the standard ice cream flavor. Good choice of ingredients for your selection to be mixed. The ice cream certainly mix it correctly over the frozen stone on the counter. Clerks very friendly on this this store they also very polite. 

I have the banana caramel. It has nut and bananas in the mixed. The only downside is melt quickly after mixed. Probably the cold Stone counter need to have the the temperature drop to the desired cold or chilled. However, it doesn't hide the great flavor.

Great restaurant. Lately they did not gets lot of traffic during lunch. It is easy to get seat if you have big party.  The food is good. They have a lot of promotion. Please visit their web site and sign up. They will send you deal such 1/2 price wine.

We were going to a different restaurant but the other restaurant is stopping the thali plate. As result I am chose this restaurant that mention by one of my friend. 

I am a fan for the Biryani rice that cooks properly. They are too many recipes for the Biryani rice. I like the one with saffron and screw pine. This rice need to slowly cook. Today not many restaurants have the time to cook it over long period of time. Actually the longer you cook, the spice embedded deeper. 

The Biryani rice here is above average, not on the top. But they are one of the items that I like in this buffet. The buffet is $9.95. It is a good deal when you have the chicken and the goat dish in the selection.  If you like meat dish, they have more selection compare to most Indian buffet are gear to the veggie material. 

The restaurant is good. The buffet never runs out. The food of the buffet is ready before 12 noon. Like this place. I will be back.

Jackson Square. Artist! Artist! Artist!  There are many artists show case their creation around the square. If you love art, you almost can spend hours to talk to each artist of their way of create each piece. The art there is from contemporary to statute art. Each creation tells their own story and they are hanging on the iron fence. 

The Jackson square is a park and garden. It got the name from the bronze statue that at the center of the square which display the general Andrew Jackson who won the battle of New Orleans in 1812. The statue shows Andrew Jackson tipping the hat while the hose rise in two feet. A sign of winning for the Battle of New Orleans. 

This square surround by famous land mark such as Cathedral of St. Louis, Cafe du Monde, Cabildo, and the amphi theater. Many performances such Jazz Festival, Dragon master showcase have happened in this open air theater. This is an famous square that attract of the most tourist.

1-21-2017 was the first day of business opening. This will be their third store in Tampa area. We were just in time when we walk in there and no customers after the parade. Immediately after our order, the store was jam pack. 

Popsicle is suddenly back to fashionable ice cream. Hyppo has many flavors to choose. They have many fruits flavor. I already like the jack fruit. But that night I chose the pistachio coconut with a dip in chocolate. I never have a popsicle dip in chocolate before. The chocolate form a thin crust that make it more interesting. I like the flavor. 

The sitting area is small. I like the window sitting. The wall painting is nice with "There are so many ways to eat a pop".  The hours is friendly to about 10 pm on week day and 11 pm at weekend.

Some of my Yelpiest friends have their regular visit this place a lot. The ice cream store give out the dog treat and the outside sitting is suitable for the dog. 

Some Bruster's Real Ice Cream has inside sitting, but this one is all outside sitting only. It is great during May and November when the weather is mild. Florida has too hot sun that beat up the pavement which preserve the heat will not play well for the outside sitting. The ice cream melts faster if you are not hurry. As a result I got my ice cream and sit in the car to enjoy it longer. Other reason is fighting with mosquito while you eating the ice cream outdoor. Other than that, I like the Bruster's Ice Cream. 

Bruster's ice cream has many offers. Sometime they have buy one waffle cone get one free, Flag Day $1 ice cream, coupon to purchase, frequent visit punch card and more. Please check their web site for the offer.

Don't get me wrong, this is a good ice cream joint. I visit a lot to this place then any other place.

I have been to this restaurant several time. I like the outback at this particular location due to their service, material control, chef skill are top of their own chain restaurant. Tonight is special new year eve night. My wife call ahead for on system reservation. When we get there, there are already a lot of people waiting. The hoster said it need 1.5 hour of wait. We tell them our reservation and we waited for 20 minutes. 

We sat down at 6:15 and the line is still building up after we have left at 7:40 pm. We came here today is not about the new year eve. It is about the Wednesday special 3 course meal $12 and up. It came with soup or salad and desert at entree price. I have chicken totier soup with 12 oz prime rib and my wife have the Parmesan chicken. The  totier soup is tomato base with spicy flavor and chicken chunk. The cheese melt in the soup make the spoon feed with dragging line of cheese from the bowl. The prime rib is an open grilled cooking and it is about a inch thick. It marinate with pepper corn and salt. They grilled to folk tender medium rare. It came with grill asparagus. My wife Parmesan chicken have the cheese on top and lite spice of garlic and salt. This make the Parmesan crispy when it oven baked. The crispy crush make the food more flavor to eat. 

The overall service tonight is a bit slow due to crowded condition. The line still build up.

There are two BBQ near this exist of I-75. This one is only 0.6 mile from I-75. I am thinking to give a try this afternoon. This restaurant have unique selection of the rib. St. Louis style with dry rubbed; sticky bone is St. Louis style with caramelized; meaty back rib is tradition with selection of oversize meaty area of rib; of course there is traditional back rib. 

I have the tradition baby back with sweet potatoes fried and BBQ baked bean. The full rack of the rib with one side is $11.99 and two sides is $13.49. What a price. Enough said, time to get your hand dirty. The best part to eat and enjoy the rib is by hand. The rib is dry rubbed and top with hickory smoke BBQ source. The meat juicy and pink. Because this is a dry rubbed, the meat is tendency to stick with bone a little bit. 

With the yelp help, I was able to find this place. Thanks for those who have yelp before me. The rib at my plate is more than 12" long. Mmmmm!  This good.

Butcher or BBQ. Both. I like BBQ side better. Their menu has included slice brisket, pull pork, chicken, St. Louis rib, kicking Wang (wing). Other than the typical menu, they also have chicken in biscuits, Korean Philly, burger, fried bologna sandwich. One thing catch my that I did not order is their side item watermelon salad. May be next time. 

I got the brisket a la carte. The brisket is juicy and carry very minor fat to make it tender and juicy. The minor fat is the best way for the brisket to be grilled. The meat is well marinated. May be I will try their burn end next time. This dish serve with choice of BBQ sauce. I got the spicy honey and sweet BBQ sauce. Both are good. 

The only downside is you have to wait there for your food to be made. I would prefer some system to inform the customers when the food is ready for pickup.

This seafood place do not have table to eat in the store. Mainly you have to order to go. If you thinking a picnic or lunch to go, this is a good place for seafood items. This isn't hole in the wall place but in a rough neighborhood. 

When you walk into the store, the live blue crab is crawling in the glass counter display container. It shows you they cook these crab live. They have live seafood and the fresh catch of the day. The choice of seafood is a lot. Blue crab is their special. It can come with garlic butter or deep fried with coating. They also have fried scallops, Asian Cajun style live cook crawfish, fried shrimp and more. 

We have the captain trio $10.99 - fried blue crab, shrimp and fish. If you substitute the fish to grouper add $2. The deep fried shrimp is very good. This dish also give two big pieces of fish, 4 blue crabs. Out of the four blue crabs, 3 of them have a very good blue crab with very tender smooth meat. I think this dish is the best value. However their best seller is the garlic butter blue crab.

Previous I have miss the UYE that Anna has. As a result I have book mark this place for trying. If you like popsicle this place offer many flavor.

It is located right on the Centro YBOR first floor. Easy to find. There was many patron have their popsicle there. The flavor is crazy. It include jalapeño, persimmon, jackfruit, carrot ginger, mamey, cucumber and more. These are the flavor that you may not think off. Very strange. 

I have jackfruit and it has strong good jackfruit flavor. That was making them successful. My wife has a watermelon hibiscus. It is a bit watery. Very minor hibiscus taste and more to watermelon taste. 

The popsicle price is in the high side. But I don't mind if they did a good job. The restroom in the store is for the customers.

To America - the Mexico style street vendor is here. This is very unique ice cream store that can be found in Tampa Bay. Most of the food and drink here are home made.

They made their own ice cream with various flavor. Most of the names of ice cream are in Spanish. Who care, they just need to be delicious. They also have ice cream in the stick or Popsicle. You can see the real fruit sticking out. Again, they have many flavors. Each one is in very reasonable pricing. In the store they also have the specialty drink. Non alcohol. But it is similar to street sweet treat in Mexico. I have sample for the pinacoloda, mango, tuna. Tuna drink??? It is actually cactus drink. In Mexico they call it tuna. Strange name. The drink is two dollars each. 

The store items are affordable below $. It is great experience to go to ice treat store like this.

This music store we have visited if we are interested in a new music instrument. It has wide range selection. The most I like about this store is the clerk are very helpful compare to many music store. In compare with other Sam Ash in Bay Area, they are the better one. 

We got our small scale base guitar here. The store has the tan color guitar on display. They has better color choice online. We were able to order online and test the floor sample if we like it. At the end we selected a shining blue color that we want. This guitar is light weight with smaller board and easy to be handle with smaller hand for the court control. 

Price is at the medium. But ultimately the service we received is good and we were able to pick up from the store with no additional charges early than promised date.

This is a restaurant that hit and misses on their main menu dishes. Consistency is not there. The dim sum is consistent now compare to the period they run special. During special price period the dim sum is not in the right temperature. But currently, they do improve on their dim sum temperature. 

The restaurant serves traditional Chinese dishes. Sometimes they are really good and sometime they are not measure to the standard. Today we are here for the dim sum. We have 8 people and we made our order and the first group of food came out in 5 minutes. Then the rest are following. Each item is at their right temperature. I like the most is the fried shrimp ball. The shrimp is ground and cornstarch and coated with slice wonton skin. 

Since we have the big group, the bill is included the tip which make our life easy since they figure the tip for us. We over order a lot of item since only seven of us go for dim sum. Good dim sum number is 3, 4, 6, 8 or 9 people. 7 is an odd number out not easy to satisfy each one if you order less or you have to over order them.

They took an old Honduras restaurant space that was here before. They have the outside and little inside sitting. The inside AC area is only hold 10 people. But their outside sitting do have the bar area open for party. I did not go the bar AC area. 

We got the Lechon Plate and the Pollo Asado Plate. This two plate has meat. Definitely like the lechon. It was well pack to the box for two go. It come with rice and bean, sweet plantain and red chili. I like lechon. Not sure they serve the skin. If they do, I will ask them to include it. The pollo on the other hand is just ok. 

With that said. The wait is about 10 minutes at 3:30 pm. I wonder what will be the wait during lunch. However, they have take out call in availability, this will cut down the wait. The price and quantity is measured up. I would go for lechon.

Simply Pho has the right location to start the restaurant. The restaurant interior design is attractive and eye pleasing to customers. The restaurant have small capacity for the sitting, I can predicts they are going to get busy due to the affordable pricing and good food. Try it now while you can get sit easily. 

Today we only try a very little section of the menu. The menu has two pages. They have offer the pho, Hu Tieu southern Vietnam noodle soup, stir fry noodle, vermicelli, fried rice, and the special. They also have variety of appetizers. 

We have order the pork skin roll, pork sausage roll, roasted quails and southern Vietnam combination (Hu Tieu). The pork skin roll is wrapping like a fresh roll with peanuts and pork skin. This is a blend taste fresh roll. The pork sausage roll is also a fresh roll with charbroil pork sausage. The pork is well grilled and has a wonderful taste. I like this roll. 

The roast quails are not the best in the Bay Area but they are excellent dish. The dish come with salt and pepper on the side which I think you can eat without it. The quail smell good and I always eat with my fingers. 

The southern combination noodle soup is in clear broth. This is not pho but it is wonderful dish and very light. It is good for people who are in weight watching. The noodle is the medium size egg noodle. The soup come with combination seafood and slices pork. 

Overall the experience is good. The service is good also. The waiter and waitress are still learning the menu. I will be back for the second page menu.

I like this restaurant a lot because they serve Philippino Street Food. This Asian fusion restaurant make a good stand in the loop neighborhood of St. Louis. I would recommend you give them a visit. I cannot a non Philippine chef can perform well on those cuisine. I did communicate with the chef and he has spent some time in Philippine. 

Our first dish is the sisig taco and qwek qwek. The sisig is braise pork belly and shoulder. The qwek qwek is the quail eggs battered and fried. The put three in the skew. Very interesting food. 

Our main dish is the Bicol Express. This dish is dice pork shoulder stew coconut milk and shrimp paste. The sauce very similar to adobo. Our second dish is the flying pig. I would recommend this dish. This dish has 12 hour braise pork and top with sriracha sauce. The best thing is the the 63 degree egg on top. Very good. 

The restaurant is like cafeteria type. Order at counter and bring it to the table.

This restaurant is in my list to visit after I have seen the Anthony Bourdain No Reservation CNN show. During the show, Anthony visited New Orleans after hurricane Katrina. It shows case the hard hit recover and the good southern food. 

This restaurant can be reached by car or Taxi. This restaurant is busy sometime that the owner put a sign not to block the door during the high traffic. Today they did not have seafood. So we have order the famous fried chicken and the smothered veal. The veal came with gravy and bone in beef and a choice of side - the fried okra. The veal is braised to folk tender. The taste is amazing. The fried Chicken is the southern style. The side that we chose is the green bean gravy rice. The chicken is fried to crispy with paper thin coating. It is not like other thick coating fried chicken. The race green bean gravy is a bit spicy and it is family recipe that cannot get elsewhere. This is the side to try.

Willie Mae original owner is 93 years old and past this family business to her granddaughter. Now the kitchen and the restaurant is run by Mike the current owner husband. This restaurant attract of a lot tourist visit by Taxi. When I am there, I see at least three taxis unload their customer to the restaurant. This is the place to visit if you visit New Orleans.

Record, CD, Book. What a combination. It is close the USF where you find your music in the pass. This kind store is getting harder to find. Although this not the future technology, but it has a goodie of the old song that you never think of. 

The store is very cute. Sometime they have live show or music. If you need a LP, they have plenty. Book every way. Store like this alway have a coffee shop inside. I have the Mexican Mocha. It is a spicy coffee. Mmmm. SPICY. 

They also have Japanese Yama Coffee. This coffee suppose to be the high caffeine coffee for Japanese. The distillery is display on the side. Funny looking.

This is about 4.5 stars restaurant. Iron Oak has good skill BBQ. Especially the smoke technique. I like their BBQ. This is a BBQ sport bar. You love to have the local breweries beer here. 

We started with the devil eggs. This devil egg come in three pieces with bacon on top. My entree is the Porker. This is a half pound beef patty with pull pork and crispy bacon on top. BACON!!!! It stack up with fried onions and claw slaw on top. Try to fit it into your mouth. 

The best is their smoked chicken wings. These wing is smoked till the skin are crispy. They sell by weight. They have good seasoning. Each wing is about $1.20. I would recommend this dish. 

The service is great. Very attentive. The price is at medium to high side. It has open air seating with TV.

During the pandemic, the store observed the CDC guideline. Face mask is required. They set up the paid screen and information screen 6 feet from the clerk desk if you buy the appliance. Service need to be improved. When we reach the sale area of appliances, only one agent helping, and he said just go to the front to get another agent to help since he is helping other customers. We did but the new agent did not show up. We wait till the current agent finishes with the current customer and continue. This area they need improvement.
