We got the Galbi and Bulgogi lunch box. The bulgogi (slice beef) is stir fry. It come with potatoes and broccoli salad, goyoza, kimchi, spicy pickle cucumber, California roll and white rice. The Galbi is the best. This is grilled short rib. I counted is about 10 pieces. Good marinated sauce. The short rib is delicious. 

Service is good since it is only three tables when we visit. I like their lunch special. I will encourage you to try it too. It is delicious. They serve many other traditional Korean dish. Next time I will have the mackerel fish again.

I am happened to be near the Air Force Base, and we decided to visit this restaurant. Usually I don't make a trip here.  I decided to clear my book mark since I am here. 

Big Ray Fish Camp has in my book mark for a while. I saw Nick and Tina review and wanted to visit this place. We have order their signature dish lobster corn dog and the blacken grouper sandwich. The lobster corn dog come with mince garlic cheese fried that is impressive. The lobster corn dog is special with a lot of the lobster meat. No cheap. I believe their fried  is more tasty than the lobster meat. 

The grouper sandwich is just average. I have better than this place. Overall their price is at the high side. Not many of indoor seats. When iris rain outside, the seat is limited since the outside seating is wet. This place is busy. Good but no wow factor. This is a 3.5 stars restaurant.

It is about 4.5 stars. For assembly food, they did it very well. The use of material is great. The process of material also great. The assembly is really nice. This may be their success of the restaurant. They do have ice cream, waffles, milkshakes, energy drinks and more. It is a Restaurant not required vegetable oil. Healthy choices also in sweet side. Guilty pleasure. 

We got the classic waffle. It has different chop and slide fruits. You can tell they process their fruit to sweetness (may be dipping syrup or sugar). So you will not find sour fruit. I like this way very well. That why you paid the money for assembly fruit and waffle. The topping and ingredients is harmony melt together. 

Each plate they serve has some writing. We have our name on it.

Lolita has high rating. Food is good by reading the reviews. This restaurant open not long ago. It is local favorite. When we visited the restaurant, there was a lot of take out before us. 

We got the carne Asada quesadilla, Birria taco, and grilled fish tacos. The carne Asada quesadilla is nice and well pack for the meat. The grilled fish is just ok. Feel the fish is tiny. The Birria taco is the best on quantity, quantity, and price. Recommended. 

We also 24 oz special boba tea. This boba tea has earl grey tea with peach, strawberry, raspberry flavor. The popping boba is the pomegranate popping boba. It was delicious. Fist time has pomegranate boba. 

Overall is good. The wait for the food is long. 30 minutes. Same as all walking customers to wait. If they can improve on kitchen speed, it will help.

The restaurant is the best of the Apollo Beach. This restaurant was recommended by three people when we indicated we want to visit the manatee viewing center. My son teacher when he has the math competition at East Bay High School, Our neighbor and Rachel M. This must be good restaurant to visit.
 
The restaurant has the harbor view that out look to the gulf. We were having the choice of the inside or outside seating. This time of the year with 74 degree outside temperature, the outside sitting is comfortable. Our waiter is quick on the feet to show us the favorite dish in the menu. We have order the Cajun Salmon and the Tuna Tokyo that was recommended by the waiter. The food came in about 15 minutes. My dish is the Cajun Salmon that come with rice and zucchini. The zucchini is stir fry and lightly grilled over the open flame. This is the technique of the chef uses stir fry with the right seasoning and grilled it to add the flavor of the open flame. The Cajun spice on the salmon is almost like the blacken preparation.  The fish is prepared superbly to dine. The Tuna Tokyo is delicious too. The Sashimi grade tuna is grilled outwardly and slice in the ¼" piece and spread over the rice and steam green bean. Most of the restaurant sear the tuna with peppercorn but this restaurant use the grilled technique for the tuna. The inside is still like sashimi and great to eat. This is a know how to handle the material and maintain the high grade for the taste. The tuna is drizzle with sweet wasabi sweet soy sauce. The balance of the drizzle sauce to be contacted with the freshly grilled outward meat make sense. Well done by the chef.

The lunch price is very reasonable for fine dining.  We were happy to be here to enjoy the great weather and accompany with great food. This is definite a place to go. We will be back for more. The service is good and quick. The host also seat us quick.

Another chain restaurant that has good chef in the kitchen. You can feel it when the food comes out. They also has Wednesday night special for limited time. They are running a $9.95 6 oz sirlion with fried and beer. Such a good deal. 

I got special of the night. The selection of the meat has good quality. I have ask for medium rare. The outside is completely cook but the inside still see red less pink. This is very good skill from the chef. The middle of the did not feel cool too which make this well prepared over the grille. 

I also got sheared Ahi tuna. This is favorite from this restaurant. I like that overlay over Asian dressing slaw. It has every good thing with about the appetizer. I would recommend this dish to start. Overall the bar is good but only one person in the bar area make the attentive service is lack off.

Great food here. Especially if you have little money. You can enjoy a great meal. The restaurant was a Caribbean restaurant before. Now is tropical cuisine with a bit Caribbean taste. The restaurant is displayed with trays of food for your choice of combination. 

I got a plate of Mofongo as a base and cucumber salad as side. My main dish are the oxtail. The oxtail is soft and fall of the bone. Very good. My friend dish is the king fish with rice. He like his dish because not many restaurant serve king fish. 

This is the place to go if you want to get in and out for lunch in 30 minutes. This restaurant will be the best choice. We also got the guava juice for refreshing drink. Our experience is great. I will be back for their king fish. They also has dessert I have not try yet.

Great come back for the facility manager. It is getting better. The communication is getting better for the sport team. They have more ideal to communicate to each weekly sport team. At least the badminton. Now with have the text message if the gym is use or rental for other entities. Our sport team players get notice in time. Especially the last minutes notice help not to drive a long distance to play. 

Assignment for responsibility of the front desk also alert. Once the notice was given for the problem area, the items were taking care.

French Quarter established around 1700 which is the older section in the city. It is celebrating 300 year in making. The tricentennial did bring a lot history including the Hurricane Katrina. 

The quarter found in 1718 make exactly 300 years old. It make of the Jackson Square, Washington Artillery Park, French Market, Bourbon Street, Royal Street, St. Louis Cathedral, and more. This quarter is the most fun. 

Many of the major Mardi Gras parades were happen here. The celebration brings it to the streets. It has a lot of french influence. Food is enormous and many choices. I would recommend creole, southern or fusion. In the quarter has several choices of restaurants. ACME, Mr B, Tableau, and more. 

Horse carriage around the quarter or cafe Du Monde are famous activists.

Decent Louisiana cuisine in town. Very good use of Cajun spice. They are actually on the Bayou and matching the name of the restaurant. Very unique building with outside and inside seating. The are netting at outside seating but the door wide open. It help reduce the insect invasion. 

The entrée included classic Louisiana dish. We got two app and an entree. First app is jambalaya bowl. The jambalaya is average to my opinion. The second app is fried frog leg. $10 you got three big pairs. It was one of the highlights. The frog leg is big and juicy. Very good quality. It go well with salt and pepper if you want to add them. 

Our entrée is the Lagniappe - Crawfish etouffee and fried catfish. This did is great to serve over rice. This is a large dish. We were sharing with each other. I also got Abita Root Beer with sugar cane sweetening. This is Louisiana root beer. 

Service is good because not many around when we have visit. I will definitely come back for some other items in the menu.

This not your typical pho place. The reason behind is they prepared according to their street side food vendors in Vietnam. If you come here, the pho soup base is very herbal taste. Typical American will not like it. But I love it.

I got the pho tai nam gan sach. It is combination beef noodle.  The four major meat ingredients are rare slice beef, flank marinated beef, tendon, beef tripe. Guess what, they don't use beef ball. The tendon and tripe cut method also different. The soup is darker colors with herbal taste. It is very good. 

I also got two bah mi one with special cold cut and the other is grill pork. $3.50. Good deal than most.  The other dish I got is the vermicelli with grilled pork, shrimp, and egg roll. My wife like this dish. 

The interior of the restaurant need work. However, the cost of the food make up the restaurant need for customers. The price is reasonable.

This is about 3.5 stars for restaurant but 4 stars for the meat market. The Mexican restaurant and grocery concept has been use in south Tampa. But for this area is the first. The reason they are 3.5 stars is their taco is not the cheapest. Food truck may be cheaper than them. In the same time, their overhead is higher too. 

I got the tripe soup, carnitas, pastor, lengua, and barbacoa tacos. The taco come with meat and tortilla. One positive thing is they bring the onion and cilantro for you to add your own. They also supply the lime to squeeze in. The green and red sauce is provided. I like their tripe soup because they are cook to soft. 

The meat choices is marinated and good for you to buy home and cook yourself. This is something new. They have the churrasco season with the spice. The price is great per pound since they did the work for you and ready to cook.

I have been to this pokeworks at least four time. I like their poke and they are one of the best poke around. During the pandemic, they take precautions for the food and customers. They allow you to come in or call in the order. They set the six feet boundary from the food counter. They did display each topping and protein with identification tag. So you can tell them what you want. 

We got the regular bowl with two protein. Their choice of base is great because the have variety. I alway like their sushi rice and kale noodle as base. The protein selection also large. I like to get scallops and the ahi tuna. The other protein include spicy salmon, salmon, albacore tuna, shrimp, chicken, tofu. The beauty is their have the mixed in, sauce selection and protein together mixed up before the put on top of the base then add topping. This is good practice. The sauce you can select different type. I like poke sauce and Thai sweet chili. 

Pokeworks has reward program. You might want to sign up.

This is the restaurant I have book mark for a while. We did not visit them sooner because we are far away to reach. It take 45 minutes to get here. Not sure it will be good to try. Until we saw a Groupon that worth a while for a visit. We were not disappointed for our visit. 

The main dish of the are the oven roasted duck breast and the pork osso buco. The chef do have some skill on cooking. The duck breast is seasoning and roast with crispy skin on top. The orange glazed was nicely accompanied the duck. The meat was lay over kale with bacon. The side is vegetable of the day stir fry Squash. This is a dish to order if you are here.

The second dish is the special of the night which may be work into menu. The osso buco is a shank meat with the center bone. It alway good to present this dish. The only thing the chef need to work on is sauce. Instead of tomato base sauce, use the wine or brown sugar sauce may be better for this dish. They are going to change it base on my conversation with the waiter. 

There a dish that is popular that I have not try since they run out. The cider glazed pork belly. I will visit them next time on this dish. Let me know if you have try it. Service is good. Speed for food delivery is slow. It need to pick up. Don't let customers wait too long for food.

Saigon Bay has been my go to restaurant before my Yelping day. They have been upgraded their restaurant interior to better open look since my first visit in 2002. Food  is still good, they do have some royal customers to keep the restaurant open is a testimonial. 

Today I have the grilled pork chop rice. It come with fried spring roll, rice and the pickle salad. The spring roll is crispy. The pork chop is marinated with sweet soy sauce. They have given two chop in the dish. Good quantity. Food is good. 

I have added the avocado boba Yogurt. The taste is good and the boba is chewy. We have table of seven. The food come out quick. Even one dish was mistaken too spicy, the replacement dish was on the move quickly. Service is good. My guest enjoy their fish.

This Outback is just me dale of the pack of the all the Outback I have been to. However, I still like the way they prepare the food. The service is good and we were seated immediately during lunch time. 

The food presentation and preparation are very good. The seared tuna is well seared outwardly and pink in the middle. The seasoning of the seared tuna has peppery taste in the way I like. The seared tuna was overlaid the delicious salad. 

The sirloin steak come in the temperature I have ask. Warm rare center and complete cook outwardly. The grilled mark make extra burn taste into it. 

We were in and out in 45 minutes just good for the lunch crowd who has less time to eat. The restaurant is clean and nice.  The only thing is need customers to visit. They have good food quality control which make it perfect to enjoy.

Sus Hi meaning sushi word was separated. During pandemic, only the Togo order is allow. They do have touch less system to be order online and pickup. It is convenient to operates their online system. The order was easy on their online platform. I got to chose many topping for my poke bowl. 

I got build your own regular poke bowl. The regular is three proteins. Some protein required additional cost. The topping can choose 18 items. It is convenient to select. We got two different bowl. The protein we recommended are the tuna, grilled steak and shrimp tempura. You also can choose three different sauce. Sauce to be on top of the bowl or side can be selected. 

I like the their beignets dessert. It taste like mochi. But it is great with condensed milk. The most I like is the pork dumplings. It has a good dipping sauce. 

They serve the sushi burrito, mini nori, sushi roll. It is simple food. They are good is because they have good flavor.

We were here for a dinner. I was not having a high expectations to come to diner. However, they prove me wrong. This American diner definitely has it place in the soho area. 

We got shrimp pop boy. It has 11 shrimps count and mid size shrimp. Good value. I also like the yellow sauce add on it. Our second dish is the De Rueben. This is roast corn beef in the sandwich. The Russian dressing with the grilled toasted bread made this dish savory. Great bite to have. We choose the cucumber salad on the side go well with the sandwich. 

Our last dish is tuna taco. The tuna was seared. But I think is over seared to cook the inside too. However, the bowl was good to have. It has sprinkles some tortilla chip on top. 

Our service is the best for the night. That the reason I said put them in the map of soho. The food came out quick. Our experience is good here.

This restaurant is hype at Lutz area. If you happen to visit Lutz, this is more affordable Italian restaurant with a lot to offer. Reservation is highly recommended because it alway full house in the restaurant. 

We started with the garlic knots and salad. The salad has good dressing. The garlic knots is a bit dry until you discover the butter sauce at the bottom. 

Our entree is the Nodina di Maiale. It is pork chop in honey mustard brandy sauce. It was delicious. It also accompanied with some veggies with artichoke and sun dried tomatoes. Our second entree is the Mare e Monti. Surf and turf. It has the scallops, shrimp and veal in lemon butter sauce. 

Our service is attentive. The price for the food is affordable. Atmosphere is good but I think the seating is a bit tight.

Nice set up for the place. However, missing customers. Need a serious advertising or offer to attract customers. I like the decorations and they are on their class. I think it is a discouragement for older people try to get to the top of the stair step. I wonder there is elevator to help. 

We enjoy our time there. There is some good dish and some average dish. We order the shredded duck and chimichurri steak frites. The shredded duck is average. It is crispy but I think I don't feel I am eating duck because is probably fried to crispy. The duck taste is cover. 

The chimichurri steak is well cook to my order. It is good piece of meat. The outside was well marinated. The accompanying frites is very good. The trick is to ask them to separate the meat from the frites so it is not soak my the meat juice and stay crispy. 

Service is a bit slow. It can be instantaneous. Overal experience is good.

Tampa Bay Area bridges provide vital connection between the counties. Howard Franklin Bridge is the major connection with interstate system compare to Courtney Campbell and Gandy. 

The Howard Franklin Bridge has seen with traffic backup for 25% of the service time. This due to the back up of Kennedy Blvd and the merge lane of the SR 60 to 275 connection. The FDOT is working on the major issue to smooth out the need of the people. A future toll system is planned for people who in hurry. The interchange on the malfunction junction will be corrected. 

In the meantime, the bridge is nice to to drive on and enjoy the water view. If you hit the right time, the sunset can be seen in this bridge for full sun drop into the water horizon since it take 7 minutes to drive across. It has to be right time on the bridge which I post 1 picture I have experience the beauty.

We have decided revisit again this food truck. They located very close to Hard Rock Casino. The food truck has it own lot next to the church. 

This time we have the Carne Frita, Churrasco, and Bistec  Encebollado. The carne frita has good pork. Outside crispy and inside moist. It good dish to have. The Bistec Encebollado is like broil meat with onions. I am ok with that dish. The Churrasco is the best dish. It has good quality meat with marinated sauce. It is definitely a dish to get. 

Food come out quick. Not much of wait. They know who we are and make the announcement in English so we know is our turn.

We have a grand dog who visiting us and we are looking for dog beach. Thanks to Rachel for letting us know the beaches accepting dog. The state park has an designated area for dog on beach without leash. We have been to the Honeymoon Island several time but never been to pet beach. 

The pet beach will be the first turn out from Causeway Blvd to main beach then make a left to ward the hurricane pass at the end of the parking. You will find a path to pet beach (Tip no1). The sign on the state park do not clearly mark the pet beach. There are plenty of room for pet to roam free at this beach. It extends to the hurricane pass. The beach is shallow, we can walk a long distance from the beach and the water is only a waist height. Since I have been here before. I know the beach has a lot of stone and shells. Wear the water shoes is a plus (tip no 2). This way you can protect yourself. 

The facility near the entrance pet beach path has a dog wash station to rinse off the salt water for your pet. There is no human shower near here. For people wash or rinse off, you need to get to the first turn to the main beach (tip no 3). There you rinse off the salt water. The entrance to the state park has a fees to enter. But I think it is worth with facilities after beach day.

I write this review base on the first encounter of the restaurant. 3.5 stars is about right for the first experience. The restaurant has unique way of Thai and Mexican cuisine. The also has some fusion of the two cuisine dish. I only have the experience on the Thai side. I will update when I try their fusion dish. 

This restaurant can heat it up the chili spiciness since they have the use of Mexican chili. If you like spicy food, look no further. It is sweaty hot. It also can go up a level to numb your lip. 

I have the basil spicy calamari. I have order the Thai hot. It did not disappoint me. This dish is wet sauce compare to some with dry sauce. It has good flavor. My friend ordered the fried rice. I think it need a bit hot oil burn and stir fried. 

Overall we like our time there. I like their watermelon boba. Close out is good and service is good.

We meet up friend here and try the sushi. Seem like all their waitresses are Siam. They are creative enough to attract customer for their sushi. 

They have out side sitting. It good for this time of year. We sit out side and we were able to see what people eating inside the dinning hall. Some of the table so close that only separate by grass window. 

This restaurant is Asian fusion with Thai and sushi. I have order the spicy tuna and Bahamas roll. The spicy tuna can be improved to make it dice cube to be more firm on the fish meat. The Bahamas roll is great. It is baked chop scallop with sherrard imitation crab meat over California roll. It is tasty for this roll. The sushi is added the eel sauce and make it more pleasant. 

The service average. There people smoking for little time than it was distinguished. We are glad that he did it.

Some fresh ideas. Hand roll ice cream has become popular and now in YBOR. I like the effort to keep the whole store in black light. When the customers walk in, the light already do the trick. Many has left their chalk memory at the wall that is cool color under the black light. 

We have ordered the one topping and the liquid nitrogen freeze sweets roll. They have three topping for about 8 dollars. But the one topping is about $5. I like the liquid nitrogen freeze items. This is not child play item. Because the liquid nitrogen can be hazardous if you did not handle carefully. They have written instructions how to dip and eat eat the frozen food. They also have to rule about handling and disposing the liquid nitrogen. 

Overall I think this is a hip place to try. Like the black light. It make you cool.

The sculpture garden display many modern arts. This is an open air garden has a lot of landscape.  The artist name and the name of each piece were presented on a stainless steel display plate. This garden is free to the public. The garden is part of the City Park and close to New Orleans museum of Art.

The art express in many way. There is giant safety pin overhang 15 feet in the air. It makes a Kodak moment snap shot. There is a Famous LOVE cut out art and we did not miss the opportunity to take a photo shot. The art pieces include a three side dog with different color, bronze statues with shooting arrow, the ladder to window in mid air, walking man bronze statues, wood branch shape to horse, seal with human hand. This art range from expression, ideal, imagination, Greek, South America native......

There are some moving art that is electric power in ever changing shape. The pieces that I like are the standing man holding a repeated squad man on top. The other one are the round hole silver piece with a strange man face reflect at the end of the hole.

The desert room is just a stroll from the Mykonos restaurant. It is easy walk and they have a few table on the outside and mostly inside. 

The display was wonderful and they have all kind of cake, baklava, chocolate item, cheese cake. Many to choose from. You almost want to have each of every one. Then you become a pig out. Fortunately we already have dinner, and we just want to have a taste. We order a chocolate blanket with chocolate mousse. The blanket is make from dark chocolate. Chocolate very likable thing especially my wife. 

The pricing is just right but a bit high. The out side sitting can be people watching or people watching what you have. The minutes we sat there has attract some tourist going to the store to buy the desert. We kind of outdoor advertising.

This is about 3.5 stars restaurant in my opinion. They are above average. Some dish is good and some may need to work on. But I applause their attitude to create new dishes on their special of the night. 

I was surprised the restaurant has good interior and seat. We were their fist customers when they just began to open on Monday. They usually close on Monday. We have order the chicken biryanis and the Mutton Masala with rice and naan. The biryanis to me need more heavy spice. Chicken may need more seasoning. On the other hand, the Mutton or goat meat is excellent. Masala is a mixed of many spice and create the base. It may varied from different restaurant due to the mystery of the spice use. But I can said I love this dish. The naan is blend. Not sure they make it by themselves. 

In order to attract more people, I think they need to change the way of business. They need to change the plastic ware for the plate and utensils to better presentable serving ware. Disposable ware shouldn't be used for the dine in condition.

Rare Ethnic Food 35

I have been to many Columbian and Venezuelan restaurant but never come across a Latin BBQ restaurant. In it own BBQ way, this is unique to experience it.  You can fill your stomach under $10.  

We have three dishes here. The De Carne Desmechada (Ropa Veja), Patacon, and the Pincho De Pollo. The Patacon is traditional dish of Columbia, the Patacon here is top with grilled chicken, Pork rinds. I say it is just ok. The reason I am here is to try their The De Carne Desmechada. They use two fried tostones with one on top and the other at bottom for a sandwich. The infill is Ropa veja which cook very well to accommodate the Latin style sandwich. Very tasty. We also have the Pincho with chicken kabab. It think it can use better seasoning. 

Overall experience is good. I definitely come back to try some other item in the menu.

The Court of the Two Sister is the start of the Krewe of Cork. This is one of the unique Mardi Gras Krewe. The parade takes the Royal Street and Bourbon Street through the French Quarter. This is one of the five parades in French Quarter. The parade theme is about the Vino. This is a wine parade route. People pouring wine along the route and drink the wine along the route. The beads are flying everywhere. You are not sure where the beads coming from. Along the route they have two story balconies building that people throwing the beads. The parade participants are also throwing the beads. Beads.........

This parade route people are dress in the French high society costume, they holding a glass of wine at one hand and throwing beads at the other hand. Sometime the parade participant women want the men to flash the chest in order to award the special bead to them. This is very interesting. I was having a opportunity to take picture with two young ladies with naked body painted art. I have seen this in the Freemont parade at Seattle with naked painted art parade but not expect in the Mardi Gras at Bourbon Street. I am guessing anything can be happen. What happen in New Orleans Stay in New Orleans.

Fun event !!!

This Gasp with a lot talented artists for dancer, monologue, and singer. They has put up a show that is very interesting. 

Gasp. Gasparilla Fringe Festival has two level of entrance ticket. The VIP include 4 drink and a tapas. The four drinks I have include bourbon with ginger ale, rum with ginger ale, and crane berry with bourbon as experience. The drink is great and easy to access. 

The tapas is not impressive. I thought if Mise En Place involve, it should be good. Not so. We have BBQ pull pork, chicken vegetable rice.  I wish they can strength this section for VIP. 

The shows are awesome. The modern dance include African dance, belly dancing, lyric dance. The monologue include the Tampa history in the funny way. We also have the puppet show in fringe details. The outside include the pole dance and the band. The singing is awesome. Include Broadway, Birdcage Show and more. 

I would say the show put the on the top.

I know about this place since I have pass by the brewery a lot when I visit my job site. I have been wanting to visit it for a long time. We have farewell gathering at the brewery to send off one of our own elite. I was thankful having this opportunity to visit. 

It will be fun to visit with a group of friend. There was many of us that make this trip for the farewell party. The AC area is a bit small but it have a lot of tables. After a long stand chatting, it good to find a chair to sit. The brewery has many boards games or fun games while you drink you beer. We have pick up the Jinga. The back of the brewery is non AC area also has larger item games. 

This was my first visit and I go for the flight. They allow you to do as many beer you like on the flight and each glass is $2. I have selected the Cascade Amber, Nitro Shooter Brown, Berliner Weisse and the Lowball Session IPA. I like the Cascade Amber and the Lowball. 

The atmosphere here is relaxing. We saw some brew bus make a stop here.

Bartaco is upscale taco place. This restaurant is better than the City of St. Pete upscale taco restaurants. They serve better taco if you consider upscale taco. 

The atmosphere of the restaurant is good. Since this place is rather new, the restaurant gets a lot of traffic. They do not take reservations but will take name down 45 minutes before arrival. However, the early call in not really work since they have too many customers. 

What I mean upscale taco place is the sit down restaurant place with creative taco preparation. They are some affordable taco places with typical taco preparation in the Bay Area; as a result I am not compared to that. 

Most of the taco is $2.5 or $3.5 a piece. I have ordered the Baja Fish, Pork Belly, Spicy Chorizo, Fried Oyster, Curry Shrimp, Sesame Ribeye, and Duck Taco. I like the oyster, duck and pork belly tacos. 

The service is great in the beginning but it takes too much time to close up for the check. I like them for quick snack in the future. I don't like the outside seating with tiny stool. I wish they can use the sofa.

I like this cafe has the unique character. The cafe display many local artists painting creation. The pieces that are display have a lot imagination.  If you like it, you can acquire it to take it home. 

We were there late in the evening. 30 minutes before closing. But we were able to sneak in for the last half hours. By then all the dessert is gone. I got a quiche and request to heat it up. The quiche "Keesh" is nice and good. I have look at their menu and they have affordable price small dish or sandwich. Their breakfast menu is also attractive. 

The selections of the latte are many in the coffee and tea menu. The only thing I don't like is the location of the restaurant in the crabby neighborhood. However, the area is getting makeover such as river walk and waterworks.

Open mic of the Thursday night is interesting. People performed and singing and playing music instruments.

Opening night. A lot of excitement. Free food until 9 pm tonight 11-6-2014. They have a 40 feet long of buffet table as a feast for the open night. They have cuisine of Indian, Chinese, Thai, Arabian.  The opening night party include belly dancer, hoopla hoop dancing. If you are not here, you are missing out. This restaurant locate below the  Ramada hotel. 

They restaurant menu include Kosher Meat. Catering and banquet is available. The food is excellent. The goat curry is cook perfectly. There is a long line of people on the buffet opening night. I also have the tandoori chicken. It is serve at the hot platform. I have a lot food and entertainment and it is free at opening night. 

They have outside sitting and full bar. Cannot said enough. This is a party. Great party.

Good music, good weather and the most are good food. I am enjoying this festival with a strong Cuban emphasis. This is more into the Latin cuisine then just Cuban food. I have seen Puerto Rican food there. This year Cuban sandwich winners are Aloha food truck (third place), the Floridian (second place), and the no 1 winner is Trias. Their secrets ingredient is salami. 

The Cuban community here is strong and they do hold this festival every year. Latin music playing at the background and people enjoy their afternoon off with family. 

We have try Sergio's Cuban sandwich from Miami. The line to get the sandwich is long. It takes me 30 minutes to line up to order. The price is cheap with whole sandwich for $7. I could have just order 10 of them and sell $10 to the people line up at the back. The drinks stand that next to the hot the benefits for the people who are in the line. The sandwich is ok. I have tasted better Cuban sandwich at Miami with better mojo pork. 

We also order the grilled steak meat from one of the food stand. It was juicy and nice. My wife gets the Puerto Rican food. It has the blood sausage, pig stomach soup, and bacalao fried dough. I like the fried bacalao and the pig stomach. It cooks with yellow bean base. Those are savory. 

Love the festival. The organizer pull a lot of heart include donation to the homeless to assemble the longest Cuban sandwich.

Yogurt Mountain is great place to spend some time with your friend and they close half later than most of the yogurt store during weekday.  This store locates at Dale Mabry. 

After dinner with a group of friend, we decided to have some desert. When we finish our dinner, it is already 9 PM. We search for many desert stores and most of them are close at 10 PM at week day. It means we only have less than 30 minute to enjoy the desert after we get there. We finally found one that will close at 10:30 which give us some time to chat. 

We have arrive, we were handed the sample cup to try the flavor in store. This is paid by ounce store. You mix of partition each flavor. They are plenty to chose and we have chosen the watermelon and the pomegranate flavor. Our toping is the blue berry pop. The yogurt is very pleasant for the hot day. Our friend who brought the selfie stick took a picture with the store server with our group. It was fun night.

Somehow the yogurt store along the Dale Mabry is cheaper than the yogurt store of Bruce B down. This store server is friendly and the decoration is warming. I may be back when I have a chance to visit Dale Mabry Carrollwood area.

I have a chance to visit this tavern with group of yelp friend for a UYE. I have been book mark this location for some time. This is good tavern with nice set up. This restaurant bar is converted from a corner house. It has unique set up for interior decoration. The outside and inside seating is comfy. 

Not many bar serve good food. This is one of good food bar. They cover the restaurant and the bar food well. You can order dinner for a nice eat out or snacks for bar items. 

This bar do have good selection of wine to choose from different country. It also has many local brewery favorite include several I like such as Coppertail. They also have the stout selection. Unfortunately they don't have Guinness. 

It has vegan options such as mushrooms hotpot, roast acorn squash, veggies burger. I would said got to try it yourself.

This is a two day long festival that was organized by multicultural or society. The events are fun and interesting. This event was organized along the the Tampa River Walk. There are several city parks were utilized and form several events along the walks.  The parks included Curtis Hixon, Waterworks, MacDill, Cotanchobee, Staz, and the Sail Pavilion. 

The biggest events were hosted at the Curtis Hixon park. It has wiener dog derby, hot dog festival, hot air ballon glow, numerous artists song performance. This year due to dry conditions of the ground, the fireworks was canceled. The concert is still good by the artist. Pepping host the VIP tent that very close to the orchestra concert stage.  

The crowd show up in number. Thanks to the city for organizing the such a very people event. It has everyone enjoy the free time.

The restaurant is interesting with the radio remote controller on the table. You can catch any tv screen and tune to that channel for the remote radio to listen in. Unfortunately our radio is too low on volume even we turn to the maximum. 

Tuesday the restaurant have daily special on the half slab on $9.99. However, I am going for the different special with rib and pull pork for $12.99. This is more worth than the daily special. With additional $3 you got extra meat and orange claw slaw. The rib is good. The pull pork is ok. Overall they are good portion for hungry person like me. Compare to many baby back rip, the are in the medium. No wow factor. May be the Cuisine R&D can improve this. 

Service is good and quick. I like their Skinny Acai Cucumber Spritzer. It is tasty for the cocktail.

Stay healthy better quality of life, this is a place to be. Even I not that conscious about the choice of material or ingredients of food, I shop at this place some time. 

The Earth Origins Market sound correctly and earthy for the product they have carry. From the organic produce to organic raise meat selections, provide variety of value food. It has all natural cookies- Mmmm yum. It has selection of salad bar if you just has one person portion for a night. 

The hot deli has good choice if you decide not to cook. For ice cream- ice cream? It has the talent I gelato. Not many place sell this this ice cream. The place is not packed in the morning and easy to shop. It almost like has the whole place for yourself. 

The fresh produce is great, the organic powder for cooking is better. It close to the beach and good for the vacationers stay at the hotel with kitchen want to cook themselves.

This is a fancy mall in the Bay Area. The mall is all enclose in the AC except the restaurant section. It has good selection of national recognized restaurant chains. Some of the restaurants are Cheese Cake Factory, Capitol Grille, Brio Tuscan Grill, California Pizza Kitchen.

The stores inside the mall include Apple Store I have frequent visit and learn new stuff. My wife likes the H&M. However, H&M report they have lost revenue in U.S. nationwide. She like this store due to the design is from Europe. I have time myself nonstop walking from one end to other end in 10 minutes walk. That is count from Nordstrom to Apple Store. 

I don't like the parking lot arrangement for this mall. Most malls have inner loop and outer loop. This mall cut off each section and only allows going to each section by outer loop. This is very inconvenient.

Cute little store along the central avenue. I have seen this place because my Yelp friend review. I cannot believe they are at the $ category. As a result I have try them out. 

Their price is at affordable range. Majority of the items are under $10. But I go for the most expensive in the menu. The mix grilled. It has chicken, steak and kefta (ground lamb). The dish come with basmati rice and two sides. We go for grilled veggies and the babaghanoush. You can feel chunks egg plant in the babaghanoush. We also add the falafel. The dish comes with good presentation. The steak is the best among all three types of meat. All meat was grilled very well not burn. 

It is almost like cafeteria style order at the counter and food bring to the table. Service is good.

We like this pawn shop because you can have some good deal here. We were here for the music instrument. We are looking for the amplified and the base electric guitar. We found one Music Man base guitar with five strings. We have check online for the model and price. It is about the range that we want to paid for the use base guitar. 

Clerk is friendly, easy to talk about. The guitar is well keep. We actually call ahead before we come. They were welling to provide a picture for us to look at it before our physical visit. 

The store has motorcycle like ninja Kawasaki. Gun. Good amount of hand gun. Tools and more. Music instrument include guitar and amplified.

Hillsborough system library that located at Carolwood. This library frequently host event to entertain the guess and library patrons. Book is alway on the move and circulation. 

The facility has glass enclosure room for children and storytelling. It has small meeting rooms for program, tutoring, or quiet study. It has a big conference room for special programs. We were there for a special program of toy piano festival. The demonstrators play and very baby babies piano. They show case the upright and grand toy piano. 

If you know about the library hive program, they sophisticated computer class. It has hand on special learning. Wifi is available but is slow. Good comfort area to sit and enjoy your reading. Do you know they have teen SAT club. This club can help your kid in preparation of SAT. They also has DVD you can bring hoe if you enjoy the movie.

Sunset is gold at 360 roof top. When the weather has a clear day, the roof top viewing is great. This bar is located on top of the Hotel Zamora. I like St. Pete for one of the reasons due to many roof top bar. 360 is one of them. 

If you come to restaurant or bar the valet is free. There is no street side parking near by. You will require to take two set of elevator to go to this bar. The bar has comfortable seating with couch over the roof top. It provide 180 degrees view on one end beach front view and the other 180 degrees view on the bay side view. 

The bar is very busy during the sunset hour. You can find more quite space at the bayside view. They also have the round couch to hold your party. Please check their calendar for special event and live entertainment. Happy hour and half price app are also available.

Tapas. Drink. Spanish Food. Place to hang out in classy way. This is the place. 

The Vizcaya is just like it name Tapas Bar Restaurant. The ambients display with a color full toro art at the entrance and some charcoal bull painting. It also has the toro bull fighters dress that is very colorful. It mimics the bull fighting in Spain. The dinning hall set up is very nice. Live piano music are at one of the night.  

We have ordered the Zarzuela de Mariscos and North Atlantic Lemon Sole with Jumbo Lump Crabmeat as entrees and Cazuelita de Conejo as tapas or appetizer. The appetizer is a braise rabbit meat in wine sauce. Like sauce very much. The Zarzuela is mix of seafood with fish, shrimp and scallops over rice with seafood sauce. Very similar to Puerto Rican mafungo seafood base sauce. The sole is top with tomato base crab meat. This dish may be can improve by pan seared the sole with light marinated spice. I have sole in Spain and they can prepare the sole better. 

Overall it is very good experience. Like the pre-meal bread dipping sauce.

This Bluegreen resort is fun place to be. This resort cover ground is big. You may get lost in the resort but you don't need to get out since the can provide anything you need. 

This is first time I have seen a resort with bar crawl fun exploring. They are over ten bars in the resort. Almost every corner has one. They even have 5 bar and 5 tapas deal too. Please check it out. 

This resort have several sections and building. You need to know where you are. The amenities include put put golf, oversized chest set, paddle boat, outpost hotel, touch tank, konk children center, pet play zone, pirate island.... Let play. On top of that, the owner of the time share has the pass for the water slide, shark riding, surfboard riding. That not include the swimming pool, sauna, hot tub, whirl pool, beach cabana, beach access, beach volleyball, tennis court, water sports. 

Food can range from Pizza Hut to candle light dinner in established restaurant. Activities after another one that can occupy your stay there. We enjoy live music at daytime next to the pool.

I would this store is good for any starter with their beginner guitar. You can find it below $500. May to start your own guitar garage band. They many type of guitars. Electrical guitar with acoustic or base. Their guitar has classical and ukulele. Other than guitar, they have the key board, amplified, semi hollow, foot change. 

The store clerk is helpful, they have special on sale and give away on the drawing if you sign up with your email. Other items they carry are stage use light, mic, sequencing light, electrical paddle, speaker and more. It show you can be one person band or multi people band. They also have guitar lessons. They carry item is not top of the line but definitely have what you want or they can order for you. The store space is big. You can try out their instruments at sound proof room.

This restaurant book mark for a while. I heard good good thing about them. The lunch special is affordable for the people. For short lunch, basically you can in and out the restaurant in 50 minutes. Great for the office people who work here. There were several tables are regular customers and I noticed them because they know the waitress here. 

I got the Yakitori to start. The yakitori is Japanese squid ball. The come with six balls. Good presentation and great taste. 

I got the lunch special come with soup. They have only choice for soup or salad. Many Tampa sushi lunch come with both. Not sure their dinner accompanying both option. 

I got spicy tuna and nitro eel. Each roll come at eight pieces. Good spicy tuna preparation and great marinated. So far the food is fresh. Good service.

I like Cake Girls mini cup cake. It has at least twenty flavor at any given day. They have mini cupcakes, wedding cake, cake all occasions, ice cream, regular size cupcakes, cake pop. They also has package deal. 

We were here for their special mini cupcakes and the ice cream. I have two flavors ice cream with strawberry and dulce de leche. This ice cream is creamy. It has good flavor. For the cup cake, I like the French toast, banana split, dream side and s'more love. 

The special includes the mini Monday - mini cup cake reduces price, two for Tuesday on ice cream, Friday four pack for $5. Wednesday and Thursday 3 pm to 5 pm is 10% off day. Those are good day if you visit. Since this is the only mini cupcakes not a chain franchise, the owner takes extra care of the business. It is up on quality for your visit.

City of Tampa is vibrant city. Especially for Yelpiest people. There are many Yelper in City of Tampa. I am one of them that Yelping this city now. Live it, love it, enjoy it. 

The city has many good mayors in the past including the current one. They have make good use of tax money include city park, city festival, city walk. The newest park is the waterworks park which attracts a lot of visitors. The city also have a lot of festival held here including the Shakespeare, food truck rally, movie night. Not to mention, the Curtis Hixon park just completed the riverfest that draw thousands of visitors. 

The city project includes world class river walk project that bind along the Hillsborough River with leisure walk that tie all the parks together. The city of Tampa have their area from downtown Tampa extended to the New Tampa area. This wide area of living has many good pocket to choose. 

Food is vibrant. The Seminole Heights, Hype Park, Palma Ceia, Historic YBOR, Gandy and Soho are good pocket for food. The city really has a lot to offer. It depends on the people who live there that create the dynamics effect for the good of the community.

Guy Harvey Outpost is part of the Tradewinds Resort. This resort is not link to the main building. It is about 900 feet with each other with a building in between of them.  The resort was name after a local artist Guy Harvey who draw the the local area marine wild life and fish. A lot of his drawings is on the wall or hang as a frame on the wall. 

This resort has several restaurants and bars. Rumfish Grill is one of them. The back of the resort is open to beach with pool and hot tub. If you stay there, you can use the facilities in the main resort which is 900 feet away. 

In the hotel they have the touch tank experience that allow you to touch the little see creature such as chocolate chip star fish. Sound yummy but nice little creature. They also has the tiny horseshoe crab with shell still soft. Other creatures are Hermit Crab, Sea Urchin, and Brittle Star. 

Come experience your self if you visit the Rumfish Grill. We have a drink at night at the beach front and enjoy the acoustic guitarist performed.

About 3.5 Stars. This store is grocery and serving food restaurant. It is interesting combination. Many customers was here to have the food dine in. I got my food to go. Please allow 20 minutes to order ahead before pickup. They need to prepare the food. 

We got the mixed grill. Cost is about $30. It is big enough for two people. In the mixed grill, accompanied rice, salad, and more. The meat has five types. These meats include shish kabab, chicken kabab, inegol kofte, Chicken gyro, lamb gyro. It was a lot of meat to have. Marinated sauce deep into the meat. Tasty for the food. 

The pickup is smooth, the payment is minimum the touch less during pandemic. Server wear mask.

Rare Ethnic Food 30. 

When they first open, I already book mark this place. I saw a lot of my Yelp friend has visited this place. Many good reviews on this place. I got to try it. It take me 7 months of wait to try this Portuguese restaurant. The wait is over, we are finally here. It take some convincing for long distance driving to reach here but no regrets. 

We order the duck fat pork belly, Karaken A Luanda and the special of the day is blacken sword fish in grit. The duck fat pork belly  is three layers of happiness pork that put together. It use the duck fat braise the pork. The sauce is awesome. Karaken sounds like deep sea monsters. However, I am eating it:) it is octopus and escargot at tamarind sauce serve with bread crackers. This is the best dish. 

The sword fish was perfectly blacken over the top to give the flavor. The bottom fillet was soft and good. It serve with grit and fried okra. This is a good entrée. 

Service is superb. The ambience is ok. The down stairs has open mic if you want to try out.

Newly open restaurant. Second day in business. Hip place with sushi bar. The surrounding has not fully open for business but this restaurant is ready. It is located at Causeway Blvd. it is easy to access from the I-75 exit SR 60 take Falkenburg South and right to Causeway and they are on the north side. 

The building is new and the so do all the interior is new too. The menu price is at medium range. We started Tako Yaki. It come with 5 pieces to share. Good coating and round as you seen in Japan street food. We also has six pieces of yellowtail scallions sushi. Good enough meat. The Chicken Karage is crispy. Good coating. May be a little salty may help. 

Our main course are the Kiwami Ramen - Tonkotsu Ramen. Good enough pieces of charshu. Very good porch egg with flavor. Their pork broth is at the light side. This is their style. I like the most is their Kiwami Torch. It is spicy king crab top with torch white tuna. Very flavorful. 

Food come out quick. Service is good. I give them an A for just open and paid attention to detail. It is about 4.5 stars restaurant. Since the quantity is is less for ramen and chicken Karage, it is 4 stars.

This is the place they open up after they close the Water Avenue store. It has a lot improvement from old place. Parking getting better. Food control also getting better. Sitting is better, more room for customers. But one thing is they are competed with established local taco restaurant. They have huge menu allow them to have more choices than other. Hopefully will bring more customers. 

I got the grilled grouper quesadilla. The grouper is blackened and grilled but I did not feel the flavor of blackened. It may need to be heavier spice. The quesadilla is average. My wife have the Carnitas burrito which is much better than my order. The carnitas was well marinated. They also pack a lot into the burrito with meat. It make the hungry people enjoy the meal. 

Overall our experience is good. Improvement has been made.

It is about 3.5 stars. The restaurant is a fast food chain. It has seat in the restaurant if you decide to dine in. This my first time have Peck. I like the selection of the side. This restaurant combines the flame broil chicken with Mediterranean food. You can said this is a chicken place. 

Somehow the chicken pieces are smaller. But the marinated sauce is into deep part of the meat. Good for the taste and likeness of the meat. The two side order we have is the collard greens and rice and bean. The collard greens was prepared well. 

The mixture of side make the restaurant attractive. The order only take 5 minutes to wait. Not bad at all.

This gas station has had 20 pumps. It is at least one available for the customers. Consider this is a plus. No wait is needed. The price is consider low in this area. Compared to entire Tampa Bay Area, their price is reasonable. The display price is credit or cash is same price which is I like. 

The gas station is clean outside. The security cameras every where in their compound. Some of the cameras to the pump which make this area secure at night.

This restaurant is tuck away and part of the plaza of gas service station. The restaurant has some inside seating area. During COVID-19 condition, dine in has not been allow. 

We got one of the jerk shrimp skew and one of the jerk chicken. They did not have oxtail during my visit. Jerk shrimp will need a longer wait which they have told me. The jerk shrimp skews were grilled with jerk sauce, I like this appetizer. The jerk chicken was BBQ with right amount of jerk marinated seasoning. It is marinated to the bone. 

Overall take out experience is good. Price is at the high side especially at Riverview area. Value to taste is about 3.5 stars.

Check point C mostly serve the Southwest Airline. When I arrive from the mono rail I always wait for center door to be opened instead of the side door open. The center door of the monorail is actually open for the people get into the train. The reason I use that door for quick access to the check point line and beat every one to the check point line. 

Check point C may be the easy check point I have been to. They move faster than check point A E and B. May be I hit the check point with less people.

This place need both of your hands to work the food. Not work for food :). We happen to pass by and try this place. It is a crab place. Many have come to here get take out. For a crab place, you need time and patience for little meat. But I like it. 

There is not many table in the restaurant. As a result their take out is popular. We got two snow crabs and 5 shrimp with garlic sauce. They do give a little more leg for us. The sauce really get inside the meat. Very juicy. The shrimp is fresh and easy peeling. It accompanied with potatoes and corn. The snow crab leg long enough and good chamber meat. 

We do not need to wait long. Food is at the high range but worth the money.

Ethnic Cuisine # 65. Dominican Food. 

This cafe is interesting. Less than $10 you can have your meal. Better than fast food choices. It is off Armenia side street. It is local cafe restaurant. They don't open at night and close after lunch service. 

I was attracted by one of the picture post about the the Pernil pork shoulder. I said I got to try that. I got my lunch with that choice. They give me a good portion with their gravy. I also added the fried pork belly. The skin is crispy. My second dish was the king fish. I saw they have cold fish on display. They immediately offer me if I want a hot piece not the chill fish. They fried a big piece while I am waiting. All lunch come with rice and choice of side. I got the cucumber salad and the sweet plantain. 

Food is delicious after 30 minutes drove home and eat. The store clerk was friendly. I like to try their juice and coffee next time. They do have sandwiches on the menu. But I like the display food.

I like the newest Grillsmith. It has very good open area in compare to many Grillsmith that I have been to. The decorations is nice and good atmosphere for dinner. Especially the restaurant week they have offer some good deal. The open dinning hall is pleasant to dine in. This location has a lot of TV which I watch my World Cup soccer games here. 

Somehow because this is new, the manager and chef pay a good attention to the food. We started with Napa Valley Salad. The mixed of green is good. The wonderful of the salad come from the dressing and additional ingredients such as nut, raisin, and cheese. Our main course is marsala chicken and Cajun pasta. Both plates are excellent. The Marsala chicken can taste the wine sauce in the dish. Our final dessert is the chocolate decadence and key lime pie. Both are well decorated. 

Service is good. Food come out very quick. We enjoy our time here.

The food stand just off exit number 17 of I-4. It is on the southeast side of the I-4. The store is selling some local farmers produce and imported fruit. We happen to pass by here before 6 pm and it still open. We decided to have a visit. 

The local mango is great and juicy. We got some of that. We also got the live basil, mint, and other herb still in the pot. Their price is 2 time less than Walmart. Your money can stretch a lot when you buy your veggies and fruit here. 

There are a lot of fresh different types tomato, veggies, and plants. You may want to consider a visit if you visit the Plant City.

Brand new restaurant. I saw Mark was there, spot I give them a try. This is probably the second store in the Tampa Bay Area. The restaurant is actually open now. As mark put the tip. The grand opening is 8/25. 1 to 5 pm they have the sample treat. 

I am here earlier before the grand opening. I have try their fried calamari and the matcha red bean slush. The fried calamari is very close to Taiwanese style batter coating. The coating is crispy. The calamari is great to dip into the sweet sauce. 

I like their matcha red bean slush because the red bean is savory. Matcha ice is well blend. It is great with the red bean. The food order came out quick enough for the take out. 

The restaurant divided into two sections. One side for sit down restaurant and the other side for the take out express. Price is reasonable.

I am living at Tampa over 15 year and this oriental grocery store has been here longer than 15 years. At then, this is the most popular oriental grocery ever. Since the competition catch up with them, they no longer hold the jewels of Tampa Bay. 

May be this place need a face lift or renovation. It feel old to walk into this store. I wonder are they the oldest or Din Ho is the oldest one. Cannot tell. 

It still carry the needs for most of oriental cuisine material. Now they are more like a downtown grocery store for the Tampa Heights. It has meat, shrimp, fish in the fresh meat and seafood section.

This restaurant take over a legendary restaurant Arco Iris. Now it is Caribbean cuisine with Latin flavor. This cuisine just match it name. I like the mixed cuisine who can serve the community. 

This restaurant is a cafeteria type food. You can select the food by looking at the tray they serve. God is warm. I prefer hot plate. However, the selection is great. It have variety from poultry to seafood. We have the oxtail with sweet plantain and tamal en cazuela cubano. Tamal en cazuela cubano is tamales are made by mixing savory cornmeal dough. It is special thing I first try. My wife have the goat curry with tostone and black bean rice. The goat is tender. Not dish meat item is a bit salty. Other than that. It is a good meal. 

The price is affordable especially dinner time. The place has an uplifting with new furniture and nicer environment compared to last restaurant.

Let get the bad things I can said for this restaurant. It is the temperature of the BBQ meat. Mainly they are just warm. Not feel like from fire pit hot. With that said, everything is good. 

The restaurant just newly opened and they are pack for line. They have table but just don't have enough waiter. So you wait.... we were lucky to have the bar area seat. It is much easy and you can watch what your neighbors eat. 

We started with watermelon Paloma cocktails. It is great watermelon juice cocktails with tequila. Chili salt rim make it nice to lick off. 

We have the Go-Chu-Jiang rib as a shareable. It come with three ribs. It is Korean BBQ sauce. For me this dish is just average. I would go for other items. 

We got the Texas two step. 2 meat and 2 side. We got the beef brisket and the pork brisket. The beef brisket is definitely done very well. The pork brisket is just so so. The two side are purple slaw and the tri color purple potatoes salad. Both are good. 

Service is really good at bar. Very personalized. Price is at the high side.

The restaurant name is "the fisherman" does reflect the freshly catch of the sea on the menu. The menu extended from Mexican food to different kinds of shell fish. Restaurant like this, I would go for the seafood side. Their menu included pineapple stuff with seafood which I have not try yet. 

What catch my eyes on the seafood is the fried whole Tilapia (Mojarra Frita). The dish presentation was very impressive. The fish size is almost two of my hand palm. It come with rice, crispy fries, and salad. The rice has added special pan fried item, very tasty. Fish is fresh and scored to fried. It is crispy whole fish. I like this way because I can see the fish eye for the freshness. 

If you know how to eat the whole fish, I recommend you ordering that way. Service is great. Food come out without too much of wait. The table is very limited but enough for the customers who visited.

North Star Eatery is part of the collaboration restaurant of Hall on Franklin. The cuisine and style is Asian Fusion. It is mixture of food from different Asia corner. The food serve including Chinese, Japanese, Vietnamese. The Vietnamese bah mi is in the high side in compare to many Vietnamese restaurant in Bay Area. But since have not try it yet not sure if the quality and taste is worth that price. 

The Bao section is nice for the amount of the charge. I like fried shrimp Bao. It is crisply fried with crunchy coating. I also the the slaw that accompanied the assembly. It work well. 

I would try their pork ramen. It look very on the picture. It my to do list. The Korean bento box and other sticky bun or Bao will be other good choice.

It is your burger spot. If you need good massive burger, here is the place. If you have less than $7 in your pocket, this is the place. If you want a good grilled burger with sizzling outward, this is the place. 

You will be surprised the best of the burger is not burger. It is the grilled grouper sandwich. The grouper is slightly grilled with sweet smoky flavor sauce. There are big pieces of grouper. It is worth the money for the sandwich and is less than $7. Great price. The burger has come with bacon. You can double triple the bacon. It is good hearty food. 

There are not many table there if you decide to eat there. Many of the customers have their food to go. There are a lot people waiting for their food since their pricing is better than the fast food join. Many local has ordered from there. Don't forget their donuts burger.

Our experience is good here. I like the Florida Pink Shrimp butterfly cut and lightly batter. The coating has some flavor. Big shrimp too. The dinner is more expensive than the lunch. During the lunch, they have $9.99 special for the shrimp. I have pass by this million time when I leaving YBOR city, but never visited. I make this special trip for second restaurant to visit that night. 

We have ordered the Pink Shrimp with spicy shrimp slaw and French fry. It has hush puppies to go with it. The shrimp is in good size. If you go with plater instead of basket, you will get more shrimp. 

We also order the mangle clam - little neck clam. It cook in shallots chili butter melt. The sauce is great. This is my first time have this type of sauce. Very creative. 

Service is good. Close out is good. Parking is available on street side or lot.

This is the second restaurant they have. The first one is at US 301. I think the one at US 301 has the edge over the latest one. The one at US 301 has king fish at Friday. This restaurant is more into typical Latin cuisine food. 

The day I have visited they have the lechon, oxtail, and many more to choose. The entree cook in the spot including the the carne Asada. I got the oxtail, lechon and the chicken. It come with choice of the base like yellow rice, white rice, rice with bean and a side. For the side I have cabbage and the sweet plantain since I have two order. The portion of the food is great. It will feed the hungry man. 

The restaurant has the sit down area. At least this restaurant has larger seating area than the first restaurant and it is a plus.

This taco place has many to offer. Start with fajitas, flautas, enchiladas. Follow by their quesadillas, burritos, chimichanga and more. The place has bar seat at the front and open area dining hall. 

I am here for their taco. I got three tacos. The Asada, Barbacoa, and Lengua. I like the most is the Asada Steak taco. They have good seasoning. The barbacoa is a little plain for grill lamb meat. I also like the lengua - beef tongue. It is great when they grilled the lengua to crispy. The natural flavor is good enough with add a bit of salt. By the way, the Taco topping is assemble by your own. This is a plus for the customer to choose which topping he like the most. The way I like my taco is only add cilantro. May be a bit of salsa. That is all which able to preserve the natural flavor of the meat. 

The service in this restaurant is attentive. The food came out quick. The only thing I would said is the chef may need to burn the outward meat a bit to bring out the burn taste.

For happy hour it is definitely a good experience. We were here at 5 pm and the place still empty. By 6 pm, it is pack with people. The happy hour is at the bar area. 

I got the steak sandwich. This sandwich is worth the value. It is slice filet with fries. The steak was well cook to the temperature that was order. The quality of the steak is high. We also got the spicy shrimp. This dish is big shrimp fried in butterfly style. It is delicious. We have the seared ahi tuna last. The outward was seared. The tuna is dark red color. The number of pieces also enough. 

Overall experience is good. Service is good in good restaurants. Food come out quick without much waiting. We enjoy our time here.

Sunday brunch is seldom in my calendar. But I was available that day. The restaurant is very contemporary decorated. The bar open early in Sunday morning. Many of the Bucs fan were here for the drinks before heading to the stadium for the game.

The first brunch dish is the Low and Slow Smoked Wings. This wing may need to smoke longer to get smoky flavor in the meat. The taste is good with the orange marmalade sauce. The second dish is the Devil's Egg. This egg is batter and fried then fill with  bacon. Love this southern style. 

Our main dish is the Southern BLT. The "B" standard for Pork belly in southern. This is Pork belly and fried green tomato burger. The house made sauce is delicious. The bun is craft beer bun. Very unique. Our final dish is the shrimp and grits. This dish has good size of shrimp. The grit was fried in triangles shape. Another creative dish and different way of cooking the grit. This is the dish to have in this restaurant. 

Services is good. Although our table is take by the bat tender. The service still keep in normal condition. Because they have big team.

It has been on my bookmark place for a while. We think the best time to visit is lunch. When the price of the food is more measured up to food is served. I like it they are across to the parking garage which make it easy to park. 

This restaurant chef do have good skill. The food that served is well thought out. Sauce and ingredients are well balanced to each other. We start with white asparagus soup. It has touch of aioli and bread crumb. It was good to have. My wife has the buttermilk fried chicken. The sesame bun that accompanied it has great taste. The honey sauce in the chicken is delicious. 

My entrée is the salmon with curry cous cous. It also has the sautéed shiitake mushrooms and the Brussels sprouts. This dish is amazing.  The service is a bit slow. Our waiter did not check on us regularly. However, other waiter did come to pick the empty plate quickly.

Kona Grill is great especially the happy hours. They are offered good discount during happy hour. The interior is contemporary. Cuisine is most likely American and Sushi. 

I started with happy hour drink old fashioned. It is ok. If they change a different sweeter bourbon, it may be better.

We got the chicken and shrimp lettuce wrap. I like they use a good lettuce. The chicken and shrimp meat was stir fried with good flavor. Great finger food. The next two are the crunchy spicy tuna and wave roll. This two sushi roll is my flavor here. We also got the chicken satay. It come 4 sticks. It overlay on the salad. It is good size of meat to share the plate. Our final dish is pepperoni flat bread. The pepperoni is huge circle. Total is 8 pieces. 

Our time here is good. During the happy hour, the bar is full. Seem like everyone got the same ideas.

Saturday they also have lunch special. It will be good deal. I would suggest try them at lunch for under $10 dish. Great deal. 

Benjarong is decorated very nicely inside. Actually not too many people here. I won't said they are authentic but they are good enough dish presented in menu. We have ordered the duck and salmon. The duck was deep fried with ginger sauce. I like this dish with good flavor. The second dish is the salmon in sweet chili sauce. The salmon come in good piece and they are pan seared before the chili sauce. This is a sweet dish may required more rice to go with it. 

At menu come with pre-meal item of the soup of the day and the choice of salad or egg roll. I like the compliments pre-meal items. It make more enjoyable. Less than $25 lunch for two is a steal.

The flooring company may be the best price. But you have to understand one cent of goods is one cent of quality. I would said it is about three and half star. Flooring selection is better deal than others with same thickness and mill of the plank. But if you have existing condition, they may not able to accommodate. Basically I said if you original concrete floor conditions has perfect elevation or you just need to change the carpet to plank, they are your people. 

What they offer. 
Some plank has life time warranty and some has limited warranty. They will offer to move large pieces furniture, installation, edging molding, and transition pieces. 

What not offer. 
Adjust due to existing condition, painting on molding. 

The contractor followed the guideline of COVID if they are too close to you. They help moving the large furniture which is convenient to the home owner. They do have good selection. However the call back for punch list item to finish off take too long and wait. Overall their value of the plank is good quality. We install the Nuvelle 20 mils 5.5 mm thick luxury vinyl plank. Our color was the seaside pecan. I like the plank has minor texture and not cold when you step on during winter. 

I would suggest any home owner before visit do their homework on the plank. You really don't want a plank holding at end edge and deflect a lot. Minimum mil need to be 12 mil and minimum thickness should be at least 5 mm. Most home bedroom is 5 mil surface and kitchen is 12 mil. Most commercial restaurants use 20 mil to avoid surface broken. I use the commercials grade. Pay a little more but easy maintain. 

Overall we like work done at our house. It was easy clean on our floor now.

It is about 4.5 star. I like the choices of grains and assemble bowl. It is a restaurant known how to simplify the assembly line and items. It is easy to manage. However, I would like to have more protein choices. 

The food here is delicious. The sauce is unique. However, they probably need to be adjusted generally liking and different from other. We got the salmon as our protein. The salmon was well cook with skins attached. Not many know how to cook salmon with skin. They probably one of the restaurant know how to cook it. The grain choice as base is nice. 

One thing for sure to get repeat customers need to have variety. To get the customers interest and come back.

Every third Sunday night this place have the Blue Jam. If you like the blue music, this is the place you want to be. The Jam is continue and non stop for three hours from 6 to 9 pm at the third Sunday. They switch out the musician time to time but the music is non stop. You will hear the harmonica, saxophone, electrical guitar, electric piano solo in the middle of the song. Sometime they have the one line joke with the band at the back. What a fun night!!!!!

We have order the frog leg and the fried clam during the visit. This is a free spirit location. It is great to have the flow of music and the food in the same time. They also have the bar with TV every place. You have to multi tasking three time -- hear the music, eat the food, and watch the football playoff. What can be better than that. The frog leg skin is removed and deep fried with dried breading coating. The leg have a lot of meat and soft to eat. The chef did a good job not to over fried and maintain the crispy of the coating. The clam is also coat with dry breading. This breading is a bit different then the frog leg. This is butter milk breading and increase the flavor of the taste. Most of the time we are unable to feel the meat of the clam. However the chef in this restaurant put a good chunk of the clam meat that you can taste it. Some of the cook over fried the clam and become rubbery. The chef here did a good job that the clam meat is good enough to bite and break it. 

The service is good. We find out that they also have band play 5 day a week. Please check their web site for schedule. We will definite back for more when they have the blue jam. The food price here is reasonable. The entertainment is free with encourage for tipping the musician.

Their everyday lunch special is the best deal. I give them an A for allow lunch special 7 day a week. The restaurant only allow takeout now. They protect themselves in the bubble wrap. In the sense they protect the customers by touch less. 

We got the teriyaki salmon and the chicken katsu. The teriyaki salmon was well prepared. The sauce on it is good. I like the stir fry veggies. It was delicious. Portion is good enough for lunch. Cannot complain for the price we paid. My wife like their katsu. The chicken was fried well. She like sauce that go with it. 

Overall it is good. We I'll try their Hawaiian BBQ next time.

The market is still have fresh produce and meat during pandemic. The only thing I would said is the the aisle may be make it single direction aisle until the restriction is relax. 

Today I was luck to see they have the cotton candy grape. But that is not cheap. I don't mind the price as long as the grape has the cotton candy flavor. In fact they also sweet. I got the premium prosciutto. I have it thin slice. They help me as much as possible to thin the slice. I like it they separate each cut with paper. 

I also got the MacMurray Pinot Noir. This 2016 has great fruity taste and also smooth medium body. I did not see much of this wine other alcohol store. This is from Russian River Valley which I like plus the good year of grape. 

The entrance has a lot of orchids. It is a welcome sign for me to pulse and admire.

It good pizza store in Tampa. Although I am not a good pizza differentiator, but I do like their pizza. Their pizza has good ingredients topping. We got the meat lover and it has good meat such as sausage, pepperoni, bacon, ham and meatball. The sausage is slice peel cut sausage. It enhances the taste. Many topping here is not your typical pizza store use ingredients. 

We got their specialty dish of the day. Baked Stuffed Shrimp with Crab Meat. The four big pieces of giant shrimp stuffed with a lot of crab meat. It come with garlic rice. This my first time have garlic rice. Very unique. It also come with mixed veggies. Price is affordable. 

The only thing is this restaurant do not have rest room access at the seating area. Not sure they have the restroom. Did not ask. The seating room has one kind of smell. Not sure what is it. Other than that. They are great restaurant.

Kung fu tea still have good ramen, tea, and appetizers. I still like them. The reason they drop a star due the recent take I have. At least three time they have changed from generous to stingy. The pop corn chicken I have is less than half of box. Very little in compare to other place for the same price. If they continue this way, I might as well not to have take out at all.

My revisit was satisfied. They were running the $8.99 deal during the weekday 3 to 5 pm. I got the chicken piccata. The chicken is grilled. The sauce has piccata and lemon base. It is delicious. It come with slide zucchini top with bread crumbs. 

Even thought the price is reduced, the service is top notch. The food also is great quality. They did not reduce the quality since the price of the dish was cut more than 40%. I have to tip my hat to the restaurant for such good quality.

This is the second location in Tampa. It is Mediterranean grille. This is their fir stand alone building with drive through. It is good use for the Coronavirus period. It created the less contact condition. 

We like their whole grilled chicken. The chicken is marinated with good spice. Chicken was butterfly opening to grilled. So it can completely grill inside the bone and outside surface. It also allow the marinated sauce with maximum exposure. The butterfly chicken is beautifully displayed. Our sides are the yellow rice and the baba ghanoush. All of them are delicious. The whole chicken is great deal all the time. 

Drive through is not most easy for this kind of food due to complicated order. Wait will be needed.

Rare Ethnic Food 52. Ethiopian cuisine 

It is close to 4.5 stars for my experience today. I kind agree some food need to tone up the spicy taste. However the spice and ingredients are there. With that said. Let me get into the experience.
