I like business owner make good classy decorations for the customers to enjoy. This Vietnamese restaurant has good decorations for date night and enjoy good Vietnamese cuisine. Price just right on the budget average customer and a good place to hang out. 

They have bar area with high stool with TV. They also has main dinning hall. The special section are the four corner couch area where dating make nicer. Outside seating is more casual for people want to watch people. 

We have ordered the Da Nang Style noodle and the Iron Pot. The Da Nang noodle included large flat noodle, shrimp, pork in Shrimp base soup. It is good soup which is very similar to Malaysian prawn me soup base. The difference is they are sweet side and the the Malaysian prawn mee is at the spicy and salty side. 

The iron pot include shrimp, beef, chicken, eggplant, mushrooms and clear rice vermicelli. I like the iron pot to keep food warm all time even after half hour of eating. 

The service is ok. Our waiter only take our order and disappear, but other waitress was available. Manager is very nice. The only thing of the downfall is not because of the restaurant. It is about the parking on the street is hard to find.

Rare Ethnic Food No. 14

A well represented Honduran restaurant in the Tampa Bay. Like Mark P has indicated, where is all the Yelper, no many has checkin and review. This small business is very good on their Honduran cuisine. Food is excellent. The look at the outside like a shack but it well established restaurant. 

We have the Carne Asada and the beef stew. Don't think the beef stew is a small think. It is big bowl of soup with beef and bone. It also has plantain, yuca corn inside. The stew is very good flavor and come with rice. The carne asada come with grounded bean and fried plantain chip. The side is impressive. I have not has a good bean paste like this. The plantain chip is excellent. The seasoning of the chip is great. 

The restaurant is like family own. The food is more like home cooking of Honduran. Service is good.

Usually pizza is not my first choice of selection for any dinner.  I prefer it to be lunch or something quick and get back to work. Wood Fire Pizza has prove me wrong.

We were here 9:30pm 30 minutes before they close. We call ahead to make sure they are open. Sometime some other restaurant close early if they don't have customers. 

We have order the Big Sexy, Carnivore and Raquel. My friend tell me the Raquel is the margarita pizza -  in drink this is favorite order item in the bar. The Carnivore has a lot of meat items. I am meat lover. This is the pizza of my kind. The surprise come from the Big Sexy. The pizza really match the name. It is sexy of the taste, sexy of the look, and sexy to enjoy for this pizza. The taste is sophisticated consider the twist of ingredients that were in it. 

We are thankful that the restaurant open late for us. The service is great may be we hit the right time. We got 10% off the large pizza with yelp check in.

Right Around the Corner is like neighborhood bar. It is just right at the the west side of I-275 of central avenue. This bar is walking distance to close by neighborhood restaurants. 

This bar is unique with some of the free video games. It also has the shuffle board. But the board may need maintenance. It slide to one side. Other game include foosball for two or four. Pool table is good when you have two with the drink. 

The bar has eight different craft beer from local or out of state. They also has dollars beers. The price is reasonable. One thing can be suggested is the flight of beers. Allow customers to taste different beers. 

Overall is very good. There are many bar there, but this bar may interest you for special price beer and fun games.

This restaurant located the rejuvenate area of the city of Temple Terrace. This area now is beautiful and pleasant. The Italian restaurant is locate at the south end of the plaza and park. 

The restaurant have the wine by the ounce for the high end wine. This is new concept for the restaurant to push more sell when one people is dining. Today, we have appetizer as roughneck clam and the salmon and shrimp cream soup. The clam cook with Bianca Wine source and the most delight dish in the evening. The soup is salty even we have ask kitchen to redo it since it use the shrimp stock that very salty. 

Our meal is a bargain coupon since they just open the restaurant. We have the two meals with salads is $19. We have the Caesar Salad and the meal is the pasta Bacco with sausage and the chicken wrap with ham. The sausage is good and tasty. The chicken wrap with ham is good but the source is ruin the dish. The grill vege that come with the chicken is great very flavor. 

After we have finish out dinner, we have couple if Gelato. My wife have the mango and I have the pistachio flavor. They are very good. 

I think this restaurant is try to figure out it identity. They seem like don't have set menu yet and they are try any cooking to see which item of the menu is the most welcome. I believe they can be very successful if the mixture of the taste is sophisticate and add some thing other Italian restaurant that was not done before.

Good coffee house in Seminole Height area. It has all the potential and groove to attract customers. Very nice setting inside. All the musical instruments are lay on the floor if you want freely express your artistic side.

The place is great to visit. It is part of the tourists spot to visit. The Cafe Borgia coffee is the signature drink for this store. It has the honey and orange blossom and top with orange peel. It has a choice of cold or hot coffee. The coffee certainly make a impact to the customer. We have order the cold and hot Cafe Borgia and concluded the hot is better due to smell of coffee. 

I order a sconewhich for breakfast. The scone has bacon and cheese and is delicious. It come with two eggs with sunny side up. I like their way of the bacon was added. The service is very friendly.

I dedicates this review to my Yelp elite friend that just past this year. I have bookmark this place due Mike review a year ago. I finally have a chance to visit and this place find it very affordable. This review for Mike M and Arlene. 

I know the restaurant is very close to my badminton gym. However, I was not able to visit after or before the games. I have to make a special trip for this restaurant. When arrive at this restaurant at 4:45, I was thinking we must be the first customer for the early arrival. I was surprised there were so many car in front already. Either I am really late or this is a popular place. Soon enough we founded out the early bird started from 2 to 5 pm daily. We beat the clock with 3 minutes to spare for the early bird. The early bird menu entrees are less than $9 except the steak dish for $14. What a steal. The people who dine there average age are at least 10 year older than me. I am just a young chicken when I was among them. 

We have ordered the coco loco tilapia and stuffed tilapia. Then we look at their regular menu, we have order the Rockefeller oyster of six for $9. I also spot a before 6 pm margarita for $3. Our total include tax an tip is less than $35. Wow. This food may not excited you but it had a awesome value. Oysters is great when came out from the grilled. Love it. I like the shredder coconut on the tilapia. It come with two side. The stuff tilapia is not bad at all. Although it do not have the wow factor, it is fresh and good. 

The margarita has full loaded alcohol. Usually if I got the discounted margarita, I fell dilute juice at the last melt drink. But the margarita here is strong. I will come to check them again since my wife also like it.

My favorite sandwich chain store. Definitely a Jersey taste. It is fresh, healthy, and good taste. I have been to many Jersey Mike sandwich stores include this one and they are not disappoint me. 

As usual, I order something that most of the sandwich store do not have items. Only Jersey Mike has it. The capacola ham with bacon, lecture, tomato and Mike way. Mike way is oil, spice, red vinegar, and pepper. The ham is spicy ham with a minor kick on it. I like it this way. 

The sandwich is prepared to my order. When you paid, set up phone number account with them. You can collect point along the way for a free sandwich in the future. I like their sweet tea which has the southern sweet. The combo include drink and chip. They also has hot sub such as the philly cheese steak.

Cool store with a cool down soft drink. This store sale a Godzilla types of soft drinks. It range from different countries. Minimum $2 as bottle. They have drink from Asia to end of world. I mean Asia that require 28 hours of flight. 

Their soda range from cream soda to sweet green tea. Basically this drink is out standing. Try a bottle a day will take a lot of months to try them all. Then you forgot which one is your favorite. 

Other than the soft drink, they have the munchies from giant kit Kat to hello kitty mush mellow. There are plenty to choose from. Good luck with your munchies. 

They also have the one line funny sign. Such as "the boob are real but the smile are fake". Sign that have political joke or daily interest. The signs are eyes catching.

Nordstrom is one of the high end departments store. Time to time they have sales item that is worth a look. The service is very attentive because you can sale person everywhere. The lay out is comfortable display with space to roam. Not like other store with shoulder to shoulder condition when we have a lot of customers. 

Their designer collection cloth is beautiful but in high prices range if you choose the designing clothes. They have online section you you want to shop at home. The store also has restaurant if you decided to shop here and dine here.

Mother day all the Tijuana Flat give free meal to all mother who visited. My child mom also got one free meal. This business model actually work and got many visitors of the night. It actually very thoughtful and they actually advertise their brand. Most of the family come to celebrate mother day at least 3 to 4 in a group. Some is more and actually bring business to the restaurant. 

I have order the steak quesadilla with cheese only. No veggies. My wife have the steak chimichanga. Did you notice their steak is good quality. Not tendon at all. Food was cool to right temperature with the cheese melt inside the quesadilla. If they have the steak grilled, I think they will attract more customers with correct marinated grilled steak. 

Overall. They are good food. Service is excellent. I did not try the grilled Mahi. May be next time.

I saw so many has post about the French Toast. As a result, we have ordered one to try. The toast is soft. Although they are all yellow out cover with scramble egg, I still cannot feel to much egg on the toast compare to the one I cook by my own. 

We ordered a piece of the Pistachio cherry Tart. We were debate to get this tart or the Apricot Flan. We were glad have tart. It has rich enough pistachio top with cherry. It is one of the best tart I have and it is special. 

I have the Egg Benedict for my close up. It come with choice of bacon or ham. I have pick the bacon. This is the best dish among the selection. The egg yolks is liquidity and the egg white just like jello. Now you know you have a good porch egg. 

The service is good, but our waiter for get our water initially. After that, the rest is on track.

The taste is very familiar. It seems one of the Bistro restaurants in Tampa. May be one of the main chefs there open this restaurant? The restaurant is one hour to get there from my house. It is equivalent I drove to any Pinellas Park restaurants with same amount of time. 

The restaurant locates deep in the plaza. I have to warn you the restaurant is new and the service may take long since they don't have enough servers. Good luck to call in for to go since they are busy taking the order in the floor. 

Since they don't have enough server, I suggest you get the menu yourself is faster. I saw our neighbors waited 10 minutes to wait for the menu. Get your order in once they check on you.

We have order the ginger frog leg, grouper asparagus with wine sauce, duck raisin fried rice and the wet beef chow fun. I like their frog leg and their fried rice. 

Since they just open and the service is not quite there yet, only 4 star for good food.  Good pricing.

We have two malls in the close proximity near west shore. I like the West Shore Plaza better due to the bargain. Try to come at weekday instead of weekend to check out the bargain. What we call it slow day for business and they are trying to get rid of the inventory.

I like the mall lay out in square shape. When you start at the same corner and end up in the same location in one loop. I hate mall go to one end and have to walk back to the starting point to get your car. West Shore Plaza more has many stores to offer. I like the restaurant there with P.F Chang, Season 52, Maggiano's Little Italy, Mitchell Fish Market, and the recent open Besito. 

The mall has three parking garages that allow for parking in the shade. It is easy access to the mall from and to I-275. It has four anchor stores - Macy, Dick Sport, Sears and JC Penny. Please go to their web site to look for deal at the time. They also have the AMC Theater with 14 screens. Please check them out.

Following Rachel many questions to the store clerk. I decided to take a picture of their menu for Rachel to study. It may require a PHD sturdy since they have ton of combination and topping selection. You think you have it all, not quite. As a statistical saying, I begin my quest with one Boba combination tonight. It is impossible and a tall task to try them all. 

I have been to many boba places; this place is the faster from order to deliver. May be they use the industry ice shave machine. No matter what, they are quick to deliver. The location is very tactical to be close to USF to attract students. The pricing is affordable compare to many Boba place. Tonight I have the Mango Snow with Boba. The boba cooks very soft. The mango snow is fruitier flavor. Many place you can feel the artificial fruit flavor but this place improve it to good tasting.  

Overall, I like their menu. A lot of speciality to try, fast service. One good trick, go there at 9 pm and sit out outside. Wait for the summer Bush Garden firework and enjoy a cup of boba. Cannot bit that with free firework with boba.

This is very nice hotel. Constantly is book for wedding, special anniversary celebration or meeting. They have the inside or outside gathering location for your choice. Include private garden for your outdoor for special function. 

The waterfall pool is beautiful and private at the hotel location. Many people has stay in this hotel due to access convenient. It get right to the Vinoy park that have many function such as art festival or blue festival. 

Every month they have special event with live music at their front court yard. Sometime is very interesting. The interior decoration is amazing. It has nice restaurant and bar. I would said this is a classic hotel in the heart of St. Pete. Easy walk to any restaurant of your choice.

Datz has few thing on their sleeve that attract the customer to come back. We were here at the Wednesday night, the place still pack at 9 pm. We have group of Yelpers gather here that night. The place is jam packed. 

Datz label themselves as a pokegym. You can score point for your team when you check in here for Pokemon catch. 

I have the beer with nitro  (forgot what name) and the Pork Shank Redemption. The beer come with right temperature not too chill but cold enough. The meal come out about correct timing. My dish is huge. It is a big Shank and decorated the Rosemary on top of the bone. It was braise properly with maple bourbon glaze out side. Very tasty on the exterior of the meat. Ii accompanied with the mash potatoes that make this dish filling. 

We have good time there,  food is good, service is good. Close out and paid bill is quick.

I went to gym in Largo (20 miles away from home) and found out I forgot my gym shoes. It is no way for me to go back and get it. I ask my friend which is the closer sport store I can get an emergency pair of shoes. They indicate to me there is no close by sport store. I should try the Largo mall which is 10 minutes away.  

I found Famous Footwear in Largo Mall. They have the high top gym shoes that I need to protect me from high ankle roll. I bought an usable cotton cloth shoe and try out in the gym. But after few games of badminton, I feel paint at the toe.  I took the shoes I bought that day and return on the following week when I return to the gym. They clerk of the store allow me to exchange. They are very friendly and helpful. I got the next exchange pair that fit me. Now I put this pair in the car for emergency.

I was surprised the chef of this restaurant has some skill for handling the material. The foods are delicious to my standard. The live band is performed at their front porch at the week end. 

We have order the Escargot Bourguignon, Porch Bouillabaisse and the Plain Ole Steak with au Poivre sauce. The escargot is a bit small size but it is still a very good deal. We got it for $5 happy hour. It came with aluminum six spots mold. The flavor of the herb and butter sauce did mix well with the escargot. We dip the bread into the butter sauce and it is delicious. 

My wife has the Porch Bouillabaisse with mixed seafood. It is sauté with white wine, olive oil and clam broth. Mmmm good. It also comes with penne pasta with the broth. My steak entree come with mash potato and sautéed squash. The au Poivre sauce is brandy cream sauce with mushroom. The brandy adds the enhancement and sweetens the sauce and brown the mushroom. It is very very good. The steak is the top Sirlion season with kosher salt and fresh ground pepper. It makes the exterior of the meat crispy. The steak company very well with the au Poivre sauce. The steak is well pick from the market and they are very tender. 

The restaurant certainly has the food with good pricing. The only thing they really need to improve is the interior. The table, chair, lamp, and interior need to have makeover. They are too old and some table side is sticky. The food is 5 stars but the interior only allow me to award 4 stars.

If you like to find you can be chef by knowing ingredients and spice, you can come to this place. You will know you can be chef immediately by choosing the right spice for your bowl. If it is not good, you will be the only one to be blamed :). 

There are many choices for the ingredients. I like the mix of scallops, squid, steak, chicken, pepperoni for the meat. For the veggies, I select the mushrooms if going with sweet sauce or bean sprouts and water chest nut with salty sauce. The snow peas is great with both sauce. 

Other ingredients will be the dice garlic and grind ginger. Add a bit pepper salt will be great. The selection spicy sauce is nice but you can add dried chili and jalapeño to make it more spicy. At the end I have ask them to add two egg. For the starch- the regular bowl have two choices. I select the udon and the pasta. 

Service is great. Food came out hot from the kitchen. I always select seat that can see the kitchen because sometime they light up big fire ball for the show on their grill plate.

Great chicken with mojo marinated sauce. I always like Pollo Tropical chicken. The chicken is marinated through and through. The season spice when into the chicken deep inside. I love the skin with rich mojo spice. It was so good. 

Sometime they run special item such as Tropichop. First step pick your meat - mojo pork, chicken pincho, Calypso Beef. Then add your base such as rice, lettuce or yellow rice. Then top with type of veggie, then added your sauce. Sound easy. This special is running now. I would go for typical grilled chicken with mojo spice. 

We have good coupon two order for $10. Can beat it. The salsa and spicy sauce can be pick up on the sauce island. In fortunately there was no Pollo Tropical in new Tampa area. I have travel far to get it if I am craving for it.

The SR 60 that connects the Pinellas and Hillsborough county is rename from Davis Causeway to Courtney Campbell Causeway in 1948. Mr Courtney Campbell is the proposer to beautify this Causeway and repair to the modern link to the two counties. His is a US house representative. 

Today it serve one of the three connection bridge for the two counties. Currently, the FDOT just finished a bridge for a bike trail to link the counties. The bridge is currently narrow no shoulders. But along the Causeway, there are plenty of stop you can enjoy and park next to beach area. During the New Year's Eve, many has park there and watch the firework or do the fireworks themselves. 

If you come in the right time, you can watch the sunset on the far side of Clearwater. The setting is beautiful. There are some boat ramp along the Causeway make water activities pleasant.

I have been many Old Navy store but none like this. This store interior set up is unique. This old navy has good front entrance wall set up. The store is two level but the second level is connected by switch back ramps. It becomes kid play ground to run around because of this set up. 

The fitting room below the frost switch back to best use of the space. The decorations is unique to see. It is not normal typical old navy look.

After dinner near the airport, we decided to look up the dessert store nearby. Mooberry seem like a good choice at this location. It actually closes to the Pho Quyen. 

The store sells the yogurt by ounce. Like most of the yogurt store we were provided the sample cup for the flavor. Seem like the current yogurt store like to ha salt caramel flavor. This is the four yogurt store we have encounter in a month with this flavor. 

The store lady in the front desk is nice and friendly. The only thing is if you buy below $5 and use the credit card there will be additional fees. Our group has seven and we occupied the 70% of the store chair. They do have the low elevation stool for sitting. It also has some outside sitting. 

We did play card there and enjoy out time there. The yogurt is $0.45 per ounce.

When my friend want to try this restaurant as part of the Latin Crawls. I check yelp that they have only 2 stars rating. I was skeptical to visit this restaurant.  Well, I was visit as out of curiosity and experiences he culture. We have some Ecuadorian restaurant in the Bay Area. This restaurant is above the average. 

One of the best dish will belong to one of my friends' order. He got the black clam rice. This dish I never have it before. It is quite unique in it own way. It is delicious. 

I got the carne asada with red bean soup. The steak is average but it has enough quantities of meat. We also got the corviche de pescado fish in plantain filling. It is good enough experience. We also got the lulo drinks which is great. 

Service is good for our big table. May be we come at the right moment when all the items were in the right place. They deserve 4 stars.

Hillsborough Community College (HCC ) provide the student with less fees to achieve the Associate Degree. I am way pass re learning stage. But some of the program may interest me in the future when I am retired. I come to campus a lot not for learning but for the food and the student government center. Thanks to the school have this event that I can enjoy the college without Learning 

HCC offer the culinary program. Each time the school have session, the HCC Gourmet room is open. We are the frequent visitor for this "restaurant". We can try the student skill with very good fees. $7 dollar per person. Man who can beat that. The cuisine range from French to Italian. Sometime they have the Ghana food. It is almost like 5 star restaurant and the service is really good. I always leave a good tips. 

The other venue is we often attend their student government musical events. The last event is the famous Ekachai Jearakul. He is 1st Prize of the Guitar Foundation of America International Concert Artist Competition. He is a first oriental who want this ultimate prize in well recognize America. He is from Thailand and have good skill in the classical guitar. The student government did a good job to place very high standard concertos in every event. My high congratulation to a success student government.

My friends want to have clean diet lunch near the USF area. I was able to locate one since I have been to the first watch near USF. 

My friend is a picky eater and he is not a vegan but he watches his diet carefully. It is challenging when one of your group people want a clean diet food. I only can think a few choices. We are great able to accommodate his need. I saw the first thing he has order is the kale tonic. It is kale, cucumber, lemon and Fuji Apple. Very healthy. No sugar added. The trick is always adding some type of fruit to sweeten it up. In this case is Fuji Apple. The lemon is to add the twist of the taste. Nice touch. 

This afternoon I have the smoke Salmon and Roasted Vegetable Frittata. It has the roasted shallots and tomatoes in the egg that create the sensation of the taste. Good touch. It also has some chive in there to enhance the taste. It serves with ciabatta toast and sweet jam. 

We have 5 people in our group but we are in and out the restaurant in 45 minutes. They are well prepare for the lunch crowd since their lunch time is short.

It is another good BBQ in Hillsborough County. This one located north of Mango. I like them because they have several good things happen to my visit. It is a food truck on the corner of CR 579 and US 92 Northwest corner. 

This smoke BBQ has smoke mullet. Their smoke mullet maintaining juicy condition and easy to pick the whole fish meat. Because the debone most of the fish. We also got their smoke brisket sandwich. It is good marinated. I like the carry a bit fat to beautify the entire taste. 

We got smoke rib which is also has meat fall off the bone. Easy to eat. The smoke chicken maintains it juicy meat. I have been to many smoke place but the meat is to dry. This place did a good job to keep the meat juicy. 

The side turkey rice is my favorite. The wait is a bit long. But I don't mind.

Solid four stars restaurant due to value, taste and unique. It is a fast food. No they are cool to your order. The food is good middle eastern food.  We have order the mix grill and tilapia pita. 

A lot people like to have the take out because it is easy. The only bad part I can find is the ventilation inside the restaurant. It need to ventilate more to keep the food smell out. 

Now the the good part. The mixed grill is delicious. Lamb and chicken are grilled better here. The juice and moisture of the food is kept inside. That is the different between them and most of the middle eastern food. 

The grilled tilapia is tasty. It has a lot of fish inside the pita. All this food come with the side of you choice. The pita is one choice and the mix plater is two choice. It is good experience here since the people are friendly.

I found this restaurant expensive for dinners. The dinner for two with drink, entrée, and appetizer is about $90. As the price is high the expectations also high. 

The entrance of the restaurant is somewhat unique. It is a side hallway entrance to the courtyard and host greet you there. This restaurant was book fully at night and we decided to sit at the bar. 

We started with chicken liver crostini. The liver was made into paste and spread over grilled toast. I like this dish because it is so southern. It was drizzle with dandelion vinegar. It add the taste to the liver. 

Our entrées are the seared hunger steak and the LA shrimp and little neck clam. The seafood dish is good. But the hunger steak is a bit too vinegary. I like the yellow split pea purée. The steak was well medium rare. Very good. The steak dish all is good but the taste or sauce is not impressive. 

Overall is good. The food come out in the right time. Not much to wait.

Bulla open door front basically is inviting setting for the prime Soho area. The bar setting is just like that. The bar area is busy. It is full of customers with one bar tender during weekday. I have waited at the bar area and not get my turn to serve and walk to the host to get a table to sit since sit down area has less people. It only happen at 6 pm that bar is more customers than the dining hall. 

I got the Churrasco for my main dish. This dish come with Mahon Cheese Grit at the bed and top with sautéed veggies on top with the skirt steak in the middle. This is one way they presented. I would separate all three items instead of lay them over each other. This way I can taste different taste. This is a good dish to recommend. I also got the churro at the end with caramel and chocolate dipping sauce. The chef here has good skill for the Churrasco made the meat tender. 

This is about 3.5 stars restaurant to my book. A few thing they can improve on. Since they have open air entrance, there is a lot food flight in the restaurant. It border me while I am eating. The bar area is too busy for just one person. May be need to look at how to improve the bar area when it is 80% capacity.

It is good solid 4 stars. Very close to 4.25 stars. I like the creative ideas to put waffle on stick. It is interesting. For the puffing waffle, it has been around for long time. But I like them to make to the order when you just order. It is fresh and nice. 

We got crunchy berries pop. It is come with the berries, corn flakes, milk chocolate and more. The waffle is crunchy and crispy. Very nice. Sauce is good and harmony with the topping. We did try the puffing waffle before. It is good with ice cream. 

Everything is good. But the price is in the high side to have this waffle. The value to taste is about 4 stars. But the waffle on the stick ideas is great.

Casa Tina is a unique restaurant located in downtown Dunedin. I have not try their food yet but I do love like the mixed drink here. 

The restaurant has the nice decorations. It has a lot to look at includes the different design of the crucifix cross. They also has painting, art craving, wall mirrors and Mexican art. The also have the areal performance art sometime. So go enjoy it. 

The bar has different type of the tequilas to mix in the margarita. They also has different year selection of tequilas with longer the year and less hangover. 

You always can get a fruit juice mixed with tequila to create your own drink. My friend said that the food average, one day I will try it myself. The seating has the bar seat, booth, table or you can select the more comfortable seat at the couch. 

Overall they are good. One thing they can improve is to have larger the mixed drink menu selection.

Rare Authentic Food No. 25

Thai cuisine in grocery store? This international grocery store has good Thai here. The restaurant dish order is located at the back and the seat at the front of the store. My first time experience was great. The second visit is average. I still like they have good wok technique. 

We have Pad Kee Mao, Larb Beef, Pad Se-ew, green curry chicken and wonton soup. I like the most is Pad Kee Mao. This is a flat noodle dish stir fried in high BTU wok with some strange veggies I have never have before. It was good and dry. The noodle has good combo with egg and veggies. 

The second visit red curry is the most interesting. We have good group and the food come out quick. The promotion in the Yelp allow one free drink with $15 purchase. The service is good. The food is great.

This first time I have PF Chang as lunch. My previous visits mainly dinner time. They have the lunch menu which is different than the dinner. I like the dinner choices of dish. But the lunch menu offer something I have not try before. Our visit to mall give us the chance to visit the restaurant. 

The space of the restaurant is nice and open. During the pandemic we were able to seat six feet apart. We order the fried we have shrimp hand made dumplings. They offer two types of finishes. You can choose the dumplings by steam or pan fried. I have not have a pan fried shrimp dumplings. We actually like the pan fried a lot. 

We also got the northern style pork spare rib. This is another dish we don't have before. The rib marinated by dry rub spice. It was tender and off the bone. Good technique. 

Overall our time there was very good. Lunch is way to go.

This Carrabba's do not open for lunch except weekend. In Temple Terrace, there are a lot of retirements people live nearby and they go to dinner early. As a result, the restaurant fills up quick before the actual dinner time. The best way is eat early or later. 

I have been to this restaurant many times. They have run many special for introduce the new dishes. Tonight we are here for new dish for special price promotion. The dish is prosciutto wrap pork lion special for $10.90. Regular price is $14.49. The dish is pork loin wrap by prosciutto and top with sweet red wine sauce. It also comes with choice of pasta or veggie. We choose the angel hair pasta with garlic olive oil. The dish is great and well balance. I can say that I order that dish again if I come back. The entree comes with soup. I have chosen the Sicilian Chicken Soup. 

Overall, our experience here is great and the service is on point.

This is a drive through coffee shop. You expect long car line during popular time such as after lunch hour, morning, some mid afternoon. The only improvement is they take order while you on the line. This will speed up the wait. All coffee will need order and make. We got the expresso toasted mush mellow as topping. The shake has good ice. 

Drink is good. If they can use two percent milk is better. My wife got the Yoguccino shake. This is yogurt, ice cream and coffee. This interesting mixed. In addition we also add the lavender flavor into it. 

Basically you can order a drink that no one have the flavor mixologist. It is base own your combine request. They also has the Italian soda which you can do the same thing.

This new location definitely have a lot of room for customers. Many customers are happy to have the bigger place than the original store. However one challenge is how you fill the restaurant in this remote area. It not close to university, major metropolitan area, at smaller sub division. 

I can said that their tamales is getting better. We order a to go tamale but it is still taste very good at home. We have try their shrimp, fish and lengua taco. My wife like the lengua because they have prepared it to very soft easy to bite. For me, I think they need to pan fried one more time with spice to make it interesting to paid for the price. I don't like the fish taco which the fish is fried. I prefer it grill since this is high pricing taco. I like shrimp the best. It is definitely worth the money. 

This is cafeteria style order at the counter. But the tip on the checkout ask medium to high percentage choice or custom tip. I really see the point if I walk to order for high tip situation.

This express place have some good wings. Other than wing, they also have the smoothie and combo of other comfort food. The comfort food include gyro, chicken sandwich, Philly cheese steak, cheeseburger, fried oyster. 

The selection of smoothie include mango banana, strawberry, berries and more. I like their mango smoothie. It refreshing during the summer season. 

The chicken wing include wet and dry coating. I like their Parmesan and lemon pepper dry chicken wing. I am not a wet coating wing guys. If you buy six wing is about a dollar a piece. If you buy 10 wing is $0.80 a piece. The cheapest is 100 wing with $0.75 a piece. 

Their side include fried mushroom, fried okra, Conch fritter and more. Although they call themselves wing express, you still need to give them time to cook. But the wing is crispy and good.

The airline is getting better from my past experience. The line getting shorter for check because it is automated. The pre-check in also help since the confirmation help that you are traveling in 24 hour. I have selected my seat long before at booking. It secure where I want to seat. 

The earlier boarding help customers to settle down in the cabin. It also help if everyone is already boarded and the take off can be earlier. I got my flight 30 early due to faster flight and fully boarded and ready to go. It is very efficient for my flight today. After boarding, when they have too many empty economic premium seat, they redistribution the seat and create many 2 person in 3 seat and flight more enjoyable. 

The drink and snack serve on the plane. They dim the light entire flight because we have the evening 7 to 9 pm flight. It make relaxing during the flight.

New name under new change. The menu also change from previous Thai restaurant that was here. I kind miss the old restaurant. But I welcome the new restaurant. I think the menu getting larger. More choices. I like they have some signature dish is very intriguing. The dish included Tornado Soft Shell Crab, Chu Chee Duck, Siam Chicken, Nuah Nam Tom, Yum Seafood. This are some good dishes listed. 

We have order the day special with soft shell crab and the Chu Chee Duck. Because they are still new in the area, the material of the food is very good quality and big. The soft shell crab come in two pieces with size larger than palm of my hand. The sauce is a bit sweet. 

The duck was fried and top with Chu Chee curry sauce. The kaffir lime leaves has good flavor. The duck was deboned. It come with good amount of pieces. It is "A" on ingredients.

Irish bar and eatery. May a leprechaun there. Let me know if you spot one. Please find the pot of gold too. 

James Joyce may be derived from famous persons in Ireland. But they do build a good bar at YBOR. We arrive at 6 pm and it is already some patrons already there for a glass of beer. Their tap include local, German , Irish beer. But the special of the day actually drawn us here today. It is very hard to find local restaurants serve broil live Crawfish. But this pub serve this dish. If you buy two beers, the Crawfish is $6.95. It is a deal. My wife went for the order and I enjoy the two beers. 

I have the Carlsberg and the IPA. Both are good draft beer.  I have the Guinness Beef Stew and the the Scott Egg. The beef stew cook with Guinness Stout as one of the ingredients. The stew is delicious Ireland comfort food. The Scott Egg is amazing. It coat with ground sausage outwardly. Very interesting. 

We enjoy our time there. Interesting bar.

Dunn River Fall and Park is a beautiful place in the northern Jamaica. The cascade of falls is the main attraction. This restaurant name after the beautiful place does represent the food and native cuisine. The restaurant has a lot seating and a stage for special events. Time to time they have special music event. 

I am surprised they did not receive high mark. This may be the service is slow. Other than that. They are 5 stars to my book. The price of the food is very reasonable. You have to understand stand why they successful is because their good Island spice marinated to the meat. 

I got jerk chicken that only cost $9. The chicken is marinated to the bone. Their spice is different than most of the Jamaican restaurant. This is their uniqueness. The lunch special during the weekdays is less than $6. They have good oxtail and jerk shrimp. Please check out their website for musical show.

This is the Krispy Creme that I have been visited frequently since the New Tampa location close many years ago. They have conveyor belt type of making the donuts in massive volume. The light for hot is almost lighted every time. Which mean they has fresh made donuts. 

They have many types of donuts. But the one I like is the sugar donut. Not event the glaze donut. When they have the hot donut or freshly made donut, I like to ask them get them from the conveyor belt. Sometimes I ask for naked donut. I will at sugar crystal by myself. 

During national donut day, this donut is free with one donut per person. Parking is not the most in this area. Very limited space. But drive through is available. They don't accept tip since there is camera behind the counter. Some one is monitor the employee behavior.

We have been to this bakery numerous time but none were at their anniversary. We finally came to their 105 year Anniversary celebration with rolling back 1912 price and item. It definitely a great success story for a store that has such history. I hope they can go for another 100 years. 

We got the coconut macaroons, eclairs, brownie, and devil crab. The roll back price was very attractive. Many item very affordable. The total we paid is less than $6. I cannot believe it. I like everything we got. The coconut was moist. The brownies are delicious. Sometimes you can get not fresh devil crab. But not in this place. The crab cake was perfect and not smelly. Have a lot of crab meat. Eclair is a sticky situation. It is slimy and sticky good. 

I alway like their Cuban pastry. Since it is anniversary celebration, I stay with their roll back item.  There were some other items we didn't get. But we did regret we did not get enough of the coconut macaroons. The celebration ballon and people line up make this event very festive.

Good restaurant. They have promising future. This restaurant is about 4.5 stars in my book. Not yet 5 stars. They have 5 dollar pho night. Service is good and attentive. We were here and find out many people waiting on the line try to get in. Very popular place. We were lucky to have two seat at the bar when two other just leaving. 

I read all my friend review. Many have visited them a year or two years ago. You can see the most drop of the star is due to service. During our visit, the service is perfect and you can see improvement. The reason they are four stars now is their regular price is a bit in the high side in compare to many Vietnamese restaurant. That is the main reason not round up to 5 stars. 

Food. The restaurant has good beef noodle soup. The sou is the best to my expectations in Bay Area. The papaya salad is one of the best. We also order the crispy duck and papaya tiger shrimp fresh roll. Their roll only come in one compare to many Vietnamese restaurant. But their roll is a lot bigger than other place to make up two quantities. 

My experience is good. I will visit them when they have five dollars deal.

I have been here many time including when they did not sold the orange grove next door. Now the grove area becomes the small family home community. The grove have good selection on orange. Now not sure they got the orange. The time we have visited, they have the honey bell. But the price is about $1 a honey bell orange. It is kind of expensive. 

They do have sugar cane soda if you look at the the refrigerator. They still carry many veggies items. I like that each items is clean and nicely displayed. They even have peel garlic if you want the convenience. I see huge carrot. It look like good food for horses. The also fresh portobello mushroom. Look big. You also can get some cactus to go and house indoors plants.

AJ is a cool store. They are close to the Raymond James Stadium. The store hour is very odd. No night hour or Sunday. As a result, no before or after Sunday football snack. 

They have several sandwiches are already famous. We have order two of the famous sandwiches - Beer Braised Brisket and the Crunchy Chicken. Both of them are pressed sandwiches. That give the name of the store. The crunchy is fried chicken with coating. I like their spice up coating. It make this sandwich desirable. The beer braised brisket is soft and very good. I like the veggies go with it. 

AJ are the two owners initials. They work well in coordination with each other. Food is good. Very close to 4.5 stars. Since is pressed system, it is a bit oily. But love the pressed food with this type of sandwich once a while.

After big explosion of opening, now the slow down is make sense if they worth for shop. Base of my opinion, they are more excited than the grocery next door. They have some organic produce offer. I like the ready to go and cook items. The seasoned meat and fish is easy to be selected and ready to cook. Is is easy for house wife to plan the meal of the day. 

I got the JC Pie Pop ice cream. This item on sale and it is non GMO ingredients ice cream. Good flavor. I also have some hard crust almond for my movie night. The organic item included the fruits and veggies with timing sprinkle to keep the veggies moisture to the fresh. They also have the precut veggies ready to cook at home. Same some processing time. 

Their organic juice or power juice are expensive for small bottles. Check is no line since it was 30 minutes to closed.

This is a market, convenient store, deli, food vendors, organic supermarket, or fast food has good offer for tourists or local residents are alike. It is many ideal stores in one market place. It is the grilled, wine bar, grocery, coffee bar, ice cream and bakery. It has many faces. 

I have visited this place many times when I come to Sundial. This time I have order a turkey burger from the grill. It has pepper jack cheese, guacamole, aioli, pickle. This burger is $12. And do not come with side. Consider this is high side for the price. For the location and gourmet, the price is just for the median rating. Good burger not great. But you paid for the organic and experience. 

I would said, I would not paid for daily eating here. Just once a while is fine.

If you looking for good craft coffee and you have not have a lot of coffee budget, this is your place. I always advocate that our country cup of coffee is too expensive. It is about 400 percent profit. Especially for those big chain coffee shop. This local own coffee place is just the right price. 

I have never seen food truck sell coffee and tea only until today. The coffee is great taste since they are fresh brew. If you need caffeine badly, you can go with espresso with double shot. They have cold brew and americano coffee. They also cafe con leche. The best part is to add the flavor into coffee. They have one flavor rarely seen. Lavender flavor. I would recommend that with fragrance smell. Other flavors include caramel, vanilla, hazelnut, mocha. 

The tea includes chai latte, mango fruit tea, London fog, mocha ice tea and more. I would stop here again for coffee.

Great restaurant to be at Tampa Palm. We need restaurant like this in our area. I understand why many people visit this place. It is for good taste, ingredients conscious healthy living, good price. Ciccio do have all the qualities above. 

We order three items to share. The first is the daily special island poke. This dish has seared rare tuna, blacken pineapple, edamame, mango over the sticky rice. Nice combination with sweet ginger sauce. It is good dish. The only thing I don't like is chop up seared Tuna. I will prefer is slice and better presentation with slice. 

Our second dish is Thai Grilled Steak Bowl. It has lettuce, cilantro, mango, carrots, fried wonton skin. I like the grilled steak. I don't like the hard raw carrot. It doesn't go with the dish. 

Our third dish is Spicy Thai chicken. I like this dish because it has mushrooms and stir fried noodle. The stir fried is good. Although it is American style but is still quite good.

The cheaper gas in Carrollwood. This Thorntons is not easy to access if you are on opposite site of Linebaugh. Since there is no left turn, you have to go straight and make a u-turn. This may be the reason they are 4 cents cheaper than most gas station around there. 

They have 20 pumps for gas. So there not much of waiting. There is plenty of room to maneuver you car around the pump station. The convenience store has hotdog, cold or hot drinks, quick snack and more. The outside of the building has security camera in case anything happens around the pump stations.

It is Christmas and you can get snow flakes at this place. In fact, you can eat them. This is a lot different than shave ice or fluffy shave ice. Somehow they able to create this snow flakes in the cup for your enjoyment. This is not the flakes they collect while it snow. Not happen in Tampa anyway. 

This store also has drink and some other munchies stuff. But the famous is snow flakes dessert. We have the mango and kiwi. The small portion flakes is $3.89. I like the mango toppings better because it has better blend with the flakes. I feel the kiwi lost the flavor. If you order the big bowl, you can have two kinds of fruit toppings. Each flake includes the topping and the sweet red bean paste. 

No wait since they just open not long ago. I like the new ideal especially come to street food from Asia.

Largo Central Park provide many events. This is community revitalization for the residents within the city and abroad. Recently we visited the park holiday light stroll. This is fun and free to public. I saw as far as Sun city retirees come to visit. The park is lighted with many Christmas light. It attracted young and old. The marry go around and the giant wheel added the excitement. 

The park has many events. It included the central railway with small train on certain calendar events and it is free to family to ride on the miniature train. Donation can be suggested to ride. They have movie in the park to drawn crown. Some of the features included the beauty and the beast and cars 3. 

The park has special event such as thirsty third Friday. Special guest performance. The Chinese New Year has event in the park 2018. Stay tune for this event.

During the Yelp restaurant week, this restaurant is top of my list to visit. It was great incentive to visit the restaurant during the Yelp Restaurants Week. The place is trendy. This is my first dinner to actually eat at David Island. 

We have Pollo Al Forno w/ Lemons and Pollo Margherita. The Pollo Al Forno w/ Lemons is roast chicken with Italian herb. When the menu said with lemon, it actually with lemon Italian tomato base sauce. If I know it ahead I may change my mind because I don't like sour food. Nonetheless, the chicken is great. I think the potatoes can be smaller pieces for all the herb. The chicken Margherita was a great dish. It has all bell and whistle for the farm to table item. The chicken is pounded and breaded with right crust. It sauce is amazing. I would definitely go for this dish. Very pleasant to enjoy this dish. 

The service is great. The only thing for the restaurant is not much choice on the protein side. Only chicken, sausage, meat ball. It will be difficult to grab hold on the the customers to visit from out side of David Island. Don't get me wrong, this is good restaurant.

Gateway Arch and Old Courthouse is belong to US park service. The arch and courthouse are located at the prime location of the city. It is gateway to welcome the boater from mighty Mississippi River. This gateway symbolizes St. Louis is the city of all float. 

The Arch Gate and the courthouse is align. It is perpendicular to the Mississippi River. The arch has tram to the top. They sold combo tickets with the river cruise and the movie. You can it as individual ticket when you don't have much time. The arch room of the top is limited room. You can see the entire city. The arch is 630 feet tall monument and open in 1965. President is not allow to the arch because of security reason except president president Eisenhower. 

The courthouse is built mid 1800. The dome is like church cathedral. It is beautiful building. A lot of civil right cases were ague here.

I have been using this store for 7 years. We use them for the professional print, overnight rush print, larger print (biggest than 11x 17 paper), poster print. 

My company has an account with them and it is easy to use. Sometime we have Orlando branch office email the marketing material to Pro Copy and we can pick up the print at next day. The nice thing about this store is they open 24 hours. I can go there at midnight to get my print done. USF student can have special 10% discount when they present the photo ID. I also learn that they promote the "green" printing. 

I have good experience there. The staff is very friendly. They always deliver on schedule. They have nice color printing and edge cutting. The only thing I would said is they printing cost is in the high side of many copy center. But if you like professional treatment, this is the place.

We were curious after Whole Food bought by Amazon if the grocery store lowered their price. The price of the food are still remains the same. This store location is some what unique because it located in mall compound but not link to mall interior way. 

I found the cotton candy grape here. The cotton candy grape is $4 a pound. The food here is high grade. I like ready to cook food at the meat area. Many choices of marinated meat either ready to grilled or cook.  I found lion fish for sales. There are many smoke fish including salmon Keta candy, hot smoke lion fish, smoke garlic herb sea bass, smoke shrimp. Those look good. 

The cheese section is amazing and plenty of good cheese to select. They dry noodle by bulk which is convenient for small portions meal. The hot deli section is huge. It is good by pound. I got two pieces of chimichurri steak. I like mochi section that you can pick up by pieces. This is something new to me.

This is the second Moonlight in the Pinellas Park. They open less than a month. The have the buy one get the second drink for 50% off until end of August. Not much time left for the promotion. 

The new Moonlight is about the same size of the first one. They several seating area. Only two people working on the drink. You may have to wait if the line in front of you have large order. They also serve finger food and simple meal plate for hot food. 

I got two smoothies with boba. The smoothies is $4.5 each and added boba is $0.59. Event with 50% off, I have to paid $8. I got the lavender and the taro smoothies with honey boba. The drinks are very nicely made. The boba amount is good quantity not the huge quantity. May be $0.59 for added on is a bit steep.

I like this seafood and bar restaurant because they have reasonable price their dish. The restaurant has good amount inside seating and more seat at outside. They do have TV when there is game time. Cuisine type is American and Cajun. 

We were having a chance to try their special of the day. The sautéed mussels for $8. This diss come with good number of PEI mussels. It is sautéed in garlic tomato. Very nice sauce to go with bread for dipping. 

We also order the pop boy with fried oyster. It come with fried. The pop boy is big. It has 8 giant oyster. Good size. Seafood we have try is fresh. The beer is $2.5. Good buy. 

Our experience is good with the services. The food also comes out right on time. It was not busy on 11:30 am in the morning. Not wait for the table. Food has good quality.

Nikkei try to be a restaurant at the center of the outlet mall. The location is perfect to attract good attention. It is located across Nike outlet. There is waiter stand outside to show the menu. I would said they are a good stand in the mall.

We got the fish ceviche. They give average number of fish. The ceviche is fresh. It has Peruvian corn. It is a bit sour due to lime. We also got the octopus salad. This dish I did not see many place serve this dish before. The octopus is decent. 

For the amount of food given and the location, I think their prices are in the high side. It will be a difficult to compare the a sit down restaurant at surrounding of the mall. But if you want something different. Here is the place in the mall.

Interesting poke place. Before I start, there is one thing the restaurant need to improve immediately. It is the ventilation inside the restaurant. The food smell in the restaurant is heavy. It will stick to the cloth you wear after you eat in there. The situation need to improve because the hot summer many customers want to eat in the restaurant. 

We have the crab corn dog. It is a lot of rice. Not much of the crab salad. But it is unique. The salmon donut also another interesting food. The rice shape as donut. The slice salmon was lay on top. The sauce is nice. I think this is worth the try because it is unique. 

The service is good. Food come out quick.

The bakery items here is good. I would said is about 3.5 stars for many Latin bakeries that I have been to. Don't come before the closing time because many hot items sold out.

Their popular items are devil crab, empanadas, stuff potatoes, meat pie, chorizo rolls, and sausage rolls. These items is $2.49 or $2.99 each. They also serve sandwiches including Cuban sandwich. The coffee includes cafe conleche, expresso, cappuccino, mocha, flavor latte. All these drinks are good. 

Breakfast can found here. As cheaper as Cuban toast to breakfast bowl. The breakfast bowl has 3 eggs, 2 meats and 2 veggies. There is plenty to share. I got the coconut turnover and coconut macaroons. The pastry is fresh and crunchy. Price is above the average in the Bay Area. Other than that. All is good.

This is my second time back to the grocery store and my first review. 80% of the store is the grocery store. If you like some Pinoy cuisine ingredients, look no further. You can get it here. 

I am here actually for their 20% of store space. They have back alley kitchen restaurant. They do have two tables. I got the lechon and halo-halo. Unfortunately the lechon grill is not what I imagine roast pig. But is similar to Chinese crispy pork. However I like their dipping sauce. The brown sweet sauce is complimented the crispy pork. 

The halo-halo is definitely an item to have. They have many ingredients below with ice cream on top. Great drink for summer. Sweet and savory. I like their purple grain. It is enjoyable bite in the drink. 

One thing to improve is the store only one person. When you have long line in front of you might as well go to other restaurant. Because the wait is long. For my next visit, I like to try their Daing Fish fried.

I like this bay looking restaurant. It is on the water. They have plenty of waiter and waitress. The time we have visited were Sunday lunch time at 11:00 am. It is a bit cold seat at the outside next to water for December. This is our first restaurant for progressive lunch. 

I got the grilled grouper sandwich with pretzels bun. The side we have the coconut rice. It was great. The grouper is fresh. They do give good pieces of grouper. We also has the lobster roll with sweet potatoes. The sweet potatoes were crunchy. The lobster is chunky and has less mayonnaise which show more lobster meat in the rolls. I like this way better. 

Our service is good. Food come out quick. We were able to finish our meal and paid less than 50 minutes.

New poke place near channelside. It is at the lower floor of the apartments complex. The parking can select the parking garage. The visitors parking is free. You may have to take the elevator of the residential apartment to downstairs since the parking is at third floor. 

We were there at the grand opening. They do have celebrations on the grand opening. It I has the prize drawing for the visit. It also has special on the poke. I got the two protein bowl. The protein includes shrimp, spicy tuna, ahi tuna, salmon, tofu and more I got the ahi tuna and shrimp. The add in has a lot option. They also have the up charge item such as avocado. 

The poke is right quantity. It is good for enough for a hungry person. It has a lot choices. I like they mixed sauce and poke then add to the meat.

It is about 3.5 stars restaurant. The food is simple. Nothing special. However, the price is reasonable. Especially for dinner. This newly open restaurant has open seating and contemporary design interior. It is pleasant to visit. 

The restaurant does not provide any bread or pre-meal items compared to many Italian restaurants nearby. It may be due to their reasonable price. We got the Vongole pasta. It come with seven clams, spaghetti with white wine and garlic clam sauce. Hint, I did not feel much of wine sauce. I like this dish because it is light. Great for older customers who don't like heavy sodium or sauce. The second dish we have is the Lemon Butter Salmon. This dish has pan sear salmon. Again, it is very light. 

We feel the dish is very much we can prepare ourselves. Nothing special. The reasonable price make up the worth of visit.

If you cannot stand the heat, don't try this restaurant. It brings the heat of spicy food to the table. I would said it is about medium Indian heat. The keyword is "Indian heat". You know it is spicier than normal medium spicy. 

When they have a word biryani in the restaurant which mean special Indian mixed curry rice. This type of food is normally seen in Muslim India, Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Iran, Iraq, Kenya, Kuwait, and more. It is very colorful rice and some with meat like chicken, goat or beef. 

The buffet here is a bit expensive. It does have the good veggies section with at least 10 choices. The meat section has 8 choices. It Clyde tandoori chicken, biryani chicken, curry chicken and more. The price is rather above average among the area located which is USF. 

I like the sweet Mango Kesari. It is good dessert. The service is good. It worth the money.

I think about 3.5 stars. Mainly is the price and the offer of the material are not measure up. My review is only focused on the shave ice. Not the drink. The drink may be speak differently. But shave ice is at the high side in compare to the same area cafe along the Park Blvd. 

We have the strawberry shave ice. Any topping will be additional cost. Which make this an expensive item for the initial price. We did add the rainbow jelly. The ice already has the flavor before they shave it. This is typical Taiwanese ice making process. It is delicious. 

The place is popular now. May be they need to think about some offer now to keep the customers coming. If they do it, it will last a bit longer.

This restaurant we have came a few time I finally have a chance to try it. The first time we are here they have close during the day of the week, second time was too busy. The third time we finally have a chance to try their happy hour menu. Love it. 

We started with Moroccan Spice Wing. The marinated or seasoning is special. Wing is good. The second dish is the tuna tartare. The tuna is fresh and well sauce. The wonton skin is crispy to accommodate the tuna. The third dish is the creole style crab cake. This dish has good meat burn side of crab cake. I like this method better. The quantity is small. The last item is the Korean St. Louis Rib. This dish I like the most. The rib is well prepared. Perfectly grilled. The sauce is beautifully done. 

Overall our experience is great. Love the food. Chef has good technique on grilled. Very good use of sauce. Definitely like to try other things in the menu. The construction on the street make it difficult to get to.

Just like to agree with the rest of Yelper. 4 stars. It is good to have their weekday specials. It is $3.95 a roll. The special is about six pieces per roll. They also has the weekend special for 50% off on the second roll. The week end special are specialty roll. 

The decorations of the restaurant is contemporary. I would give them a good effort for the bathroom details. During the lunch time, not too many people. We order the spicy tuna, spicy yellow tails, spicy scallops, Tampa roll, eel avocado, and the Boston roll. The food is good. The spicy scallops has the most tasty flavor. 

Food is fresh. It take 15 minutes for six roll to make. The important is the rice. They do have the right ideal about the rice seasoning. It right amount of rice. Close out is good.

The restaurant location has been through many other types of restaurant before today Mediterranean Cuisine. I wish they doing well since they do have good food. Winning the support of the customers is important. Such as doing something different than other Mediterranean cuisine restaurant typically do. One improvement can be done definitely has all dinner or meal with multi sides to accompany. Currently they allow one side which I feel to little and not comparable to the near by restaurant has done. 

I have chicken kabab and the lamb chop dinner. The chicken kabab I choose the baba ghanoush. The Baba ghanoush was delicious. The chicken was grilled with juicy meat and marinated sauce. It is a good dish to have. The lamb chop I have choose the yellow rice. The lamb chop was very nicely done. As I said above, for the price they have, they may want to include another side.

It one of good seafood place in Dunedin. This restaurant is about 4.5 stars. The reason they stay at 4 stars due to service during lunch time. They have one waiter and reception for the afternoon. I can see 6 table of customers but not enough waitress. Obviously this is a balancing act for the restaurant if they need to spend more overhead. 

With that said. The food are excellent. 5 stars. We started with fried crab crawl. This is special of the day. $12 for about 20 crawls. The crawl is fresh with great coating. Love it. 

Our main dish is oyster poboy and the blackened hogfish. They give a lot of oyster at the poboy. The oyster are great. My friend was not able to finish and take home. The hogfish blackened is ok. Not like the Cajun style. But the fish meat is good and tasty. It is good sandwich. 

Overall experience is good. Hope they continue the good food.

Very close to 4.5 stars restaurant. I would said they are good enough in this area. In fact, they are better than most of the Japanese restaurant which serves by non Japanese chef. I believe many enjoy the food once they have the sashimi. 

Restaurant is kind of tuck away in the plaza. Not visible to the Main Street. We got bento box special and the Arizona roll. We are kind of in hurry for a movie but we didn't tell them so. However, the speed of the serving, we were able to finish at 35 minutes. 

I like my bento box. It has sashimi, sushi, California roll, goyoza, teriyaki chicken, tempura shrimp and veggies. Accompanying with salad and soup. I like the way they prepared the sashimi. The fish was glazed with sesame oil. Nice touch. The temperature is crispy and evenly spread of flour. I like they special made goyoza. The infill include meat and scallions. Very nice. All fish is in good size. 

Overall very good experience.

It an interesting local produce place. The location of the store is actually close to the county line but not at county line. It is one street south of the county line at Hillsborough County. 

They have good piece of farm property at Lutz. It is large enough for the farm, building and food truck. The entrance may need some fixed up for the big hole cumulate the rain water. 

The produce they have is one of the kind. Basically have fresh veggies, home made drink, olive oil, soft drink and more. I got the cane soda. This cola made from sugar cane water. It is interesting. Their fresh fruit are store at the refrigerator to maintain freshness. This is the place I saw sell fresh blackberry juice.

Solid 4 stars. Very close to 4.5 stars. If they have more creative side, they probably 5 stars. This take out BBQ place is Riverview jewels. Many come here for the pickup food. The peach cobbler should not be miss. This is the item I recommend. 

We have the family meal deal with three meat types and 3 sides and a peach cobbler as a deal. The meat are ribs, chicken and pulled pork. The best is the rib. I like the way the have the rib with seasoning stick to the surface. The sons is the chicken. The sides we have is the yellow rice, garlic potatoes and collard greens. The best is the garlic potatoes. 

The deal is good for $25. It is in good quantity. The wait is good to order on side. Many call in. The smoke house just right outside.

About 4.25 stars. This newly added location is similar to the one at River View. But I think they are better location in compare to the one they have in River View. I like open space compare to restaurants that previously here. 

We were here since we know their sister company at the south. I have the Spaghetti Ortolano with grilled shrimp. I kind of changed the protein on this dish. It turn our very well. The ingredients included pine nuts, green bean, asparagus, broccoli, tomato. This pasta dish is harmony to go with grilled shrimp. We also got the Chicken Parmesan with pasta. The chicken is breaded. Both dishes are excellent. 

The food is on time. We were lucky to beat the Sunday lunch crowd. Not much of wait. The restaurant filled up in 30 minutes. So go early on Sunday.

I have been to this house two year ago close to Christmas. The owner always has the fun to set up the Christmas light and attract a lot of visitors. The entrée is free but suggest for donations to keep up the cost.  

The whole front yard is cover with Christmas light. They have good nativity scene with arc light over it. The trees is completely wrapped with light. Giant size snow man blow with air. Bubble fill with sky. Charles Stanley preached the sermon. These is the few set they do. The model train section with amusement park has a lot of moving part. The section with light show is dancing.  I like their North Pole penguin set up. 

There many photo spot opportunity. We took many of that. They even have people direct the traffic to keep vehicles moving. Street side parking is available.

This food truck located a the empty land. The entrance is from Old SR 54 not the Wesley Chapel Blvd.  the map may take you at non entrance way. They do have pepinos, patacone, cachapa and more. Is is Venezuelan food. Price is at the high side. 

I got the carne mechada (shredded beef). It look beautiful. The beef is a lot. I also like the fried patacone. It was crispy. The Venezuelan cheese is delicious. The sauce was well made. 

From order to finish is about 10 minutes. I don't mind the wait to get the freshly fried patacone.

Cinco De Mayo weekend, our office pick this restaurant to have the lunch before the week is over. This restaurant is hidden at temple terrace in a small plaza. If I don't have yelp, I would not have found it. 

They have $5 lunch special and margarita special. I have order one margarita and it come with 32 oz glass. Giant glass!!! It almost cannot fit my face. I have asked the help from my friend to take a sip. 

I have ordered the steak quesadilla, it come with lettuce and tomato. The steak is stir fried in flour taco. It is decent. Taste is good. I have added a dessert at the end with fried dough with cinnamon, powder sugar and honey. 

Service is friendly, food came out fast, the atmosphere is great. This is about 3.5 stars restaurant. Please check them out. Definitely a very budget lunch.

A little above 4 stars. Because of the good flavors. They located at Seminole Height. Parking is at the side street. The seating is limited at interior but they do have the courtyard seating share with the chicken place next door. 

They have vegan or veggies bowl. We got the surf and turf bowl. It is included the grilled shrimp and steak. I like it they cook your order. They grilled the steak right when you order it. Good seasoning to the steak and shrimp. The choices of the topping is by yourself. I like the broccoli and Brussels sprouts. Our base is the noodle. Every thing is great. Even the sauces are creative to be added on. 

Not much service. The workers there are very friendly with a smile. Love the food and we will be back to try other item. A+ on the seasoning and the sauce accompanying it.

Yummy House is alway to go restaurant. My recent visit drop a stars. Mainly is the taste and quantity. They still hold good menu selections. But I think the menu is reduced items. During pandemic and inflation, the price did increase by 20%. 

The main reason they deducted a stars from my previous review is the quantity of the protein is reduced and the price increase. They no longer the most economical restaurants. You can tell the customer also reduced during dinner time. Lunch time is still a lot of customers especially weekends due to dim sum. 

I also feel their best chefs is no longer here. Food taste is a bit less than their branch at Ocala.

Kao Thai is in my bookmark for a while. Finally I have a chance to visit the restaurant. The restaurant is well decorated. I like the clothing napkin setup on the table like bold tide. They have different menu. One is their regular menu and the other is the Thai street food menu. 

We Thee dishes from the Thai Street Menu. The first dish is the Yum Nam Kao Tod. This is salad dish with sausage, crispy curry rice that fried, peanut. To me, this dish is salty and sour to be eat along. The second dish is Hoy Tod. It s a mussels egg pancake and bean sprouts. It come with the dipping sweet chilies sauce. I like this dish. The third dish is my favorite. Kao Kook Ka Pi. This dish has seven combination items in one dish. The item I like the most is shrimp paste fried rice. I have this as Malay dish. But they carry it. This is the first I have in Tampa Bay. The dish also includes the caramelize pork belly, Thai sweet sausage, egg, onion, apple and string bean. It is well presented. 

Overall our experience is good. I really want to come back to try their main menu dish. This restaurant is about 4.5 stars since each dish is well decorated.

For the BBQ they are about middle of the pack in Tampa. Their combo compare to many place they are right portion not the generous portion. 

We got the combo package with collard greens and sweet corn as side. The main meat is the hog feed and the rib and brisket. The hog feed is the pull pork. I think the rib is better. Brisket is just good. We also got the pork sandwich. Their food is good but not to jump out the seat. 

Price is a bit in the expensive side. May be create something attractive to the side items will attract more business. I do like the choice of the sauce. We got the mango sauce and the guava sauce. It is interesting.

This is the restaurant we have visited sometime ago and finally I have sometime to write about it. Havana 86 is the restaurant may be open during pandemic. We visited two months ago. I like the restaurant because it has good Cuban cuisine. Especially this area has already many Cuban restaurants close. I am happy they open their door. 

We started with Tostones Rellenos - stuff fried green plantain. We got the stuffing at lobster. It comes with 5 pieces and delicious to share. For the main course, we have Vaca Frita and Churrasco ala Cubana. The vaca frita can be a little crispy by pan grilled longer. The skirt steak is delicious. 

Overall the food is good. It is close to 4.5 stars. Price is affordable. Hopefully they keep it this way. Service is ok nothing jump out.

It is about 3.5 stars. The lobster is definitely better quality than most lobster roll I have. They do have body meat not like most restaurants mainly crawl meat and the body sold to other dish. The preparation is butter lobster. I actually like this way better because you can taste the freshness of the lobster. 

They have three different size of the roll. 2 oz to 4 oz selection. You also go to mega roll foot long with 10oz to share. They also has the lobster fried or Macaroni to try. Other than lobster, hot, burger, fish sandwich also available. 

The truck just park outside. You can order the inside the brewery and they will give you a wait table. Food is great. I would said a good lobster roll in Tampa. I would suggest at least 3 oz roll.

A good barrier island food off the Pinellas county gulf coast. Rick is look like back to normal after pandemic. The customer come back to enjoy the mixed cocktails and food. It is St. Pete beach area restaurant. I pick this place after my visit to my project. 

I order the grilled grouper sandwich. It come with the side. And I got the deep corn on the cob. I have not have a deep fried corn in Florida. I have deep fried corn once at New Orlean. The corn is very delicious. I recommend this side order if you come here. The outward of the corn has apply a layer of salty coating. It match the corn sweetness. The grouper is fresh. Seem like fresh catch of the day. My friend has a he shrimp pasta. He like it and finish the entire bowl. 

Overall the service is good. I did not try their cocktails. But the food is good and has some unique item.

There are so many poke place pop up lately. This is second poke island I have seen. I like it particularly is their choices of the protein. They have something that other poke place do not offer. The protein has eel, Tempura shrimp, tomago, squid. These items is not normally serve. 

They have served a Yummy sauce which is spicy sesame is lovely. Mixed it with eel and poke sauce will make this perfect. I would said one part of yummy and poke sauce and two part of eel sauce is the way I like it. It you don't want it sweet, just use one part of eel sauce. I like the way they have the sauce on the rice first then pile all ingredients and sauce on the top. To make better, I would suggest sauce and ingredients mixed and put over rice. Then topping. This will increase the best taste. 

Price is good. But more protein did not mean you get more food. I would suggest that more protein with more food.

Flames Indian Restaurant is one of the up coming Indian cuisine at south Tampa. The cuisine does tone down a bit for the local American. It is still maintained a good spice mixture that represents the Indian cuisine. The decorations of the restaurant is nice. While we eating there, there are some local come to pickup the take out. 

We have the Phatthar Gosht Ka Saalan. It is a lamb dish from Hyderabadi Cuisine. This dish to me the spice is enough. However I think missing the heat of the spiciness. It has s still delicious. 

I like the most is the Chicken Chettinad. It is a classic chettinad dish with great flavor. I like the sophisticated of the spice. It is great dish to go with rice. 

Both dishes is good. Portion is a bit small. Service at the restaurant is good. If you not use to the spicy Indian foods, this may be a good choice. They do have good taste.

This Bento has great setup among many Bento I have been to. Set up is very nice with indoor or outdoor dining. The elevated outdoor concrete floor serve a very good view and away from the vehicles. 

I have sushi box with yellowtail caliente roll and salmon roll. It come with California roll, goyoza, salad and spicy cucumber pickles. This bento box is fresh and good. The food do improve a lot from old day. My wife have bento box of chicken katsu. The chicken was two flat pieces. It also accompanied with noodle and brown rice. The salad and wonton skin also includes in the box. 

There is not much of service. It is order at the counter and bring a number to your table. Food was delivered by your number.

Very close to 4.5 stars. This restaurant has potential. Newly open. It give good quantity of food. It is upscale fast food with good flavor. Menu is easy understanding. A three step process to select what you want. 

First step is to choose the your entree. This includes burritos, quesadilla, bowl, taco. Next step is to choose your protein, it includes different types of chicken, pork, steak or ground beef, shrimp. Base on type of protein will determine the price of the items. Next step to choose your add on. They have good choices. I got the steak quesadilla. The add on was delicious. It take 10 minutes to prepare my thick quesadilla. It has good cheese. My wife have BBQ pork. The bowl is huge with add on. She like the taste of it. 

Overall I said it is good value for the food we have. I like the good thick quesadilla. Enough steak in it. Good grilled steak.

This is our second stop happy hour restaurant. Malio is restaurant near Curtis Hixon park. If you happen to be there, you may want to check on their happy hour from 3 to 7 pm Tuesday to Friday. Their happy hour food item is great. 

I start with their high west old fashioned. It is a double Rye whiskey. It has some kick into it. Good deal at happy hour. Our selection for the appetizers begins with filet tips it was grilled very well. Good to share with friend. Our next appetizer is Ahi Tuna Tartare. It serve with wonton chip and pickles ginger. Tuna was good. Our last appetizer is the Shrimp Theresa. It is grilled shrimp with ponzu crispy outside. I like this appetizer the best. It come as six pieces. 

Overall we enjoy our time here. Service is good. Parking at the building is $6 if you want to park close. They do have coupons but still need to pay $6 for parking. I think it defeated the coupon.

My friend have a surgery here which give me an opportunity to visit this hospital. I was not aware of this hospital is located in the middle of south Tampa. It is convenient for the south Tampa residents to visit their love one if they need a surgery. I would suggest any short duration of surgery should be close to home. It allow immediate family care without traveling abroad. 

This hospital is rather nice because there was plenty of parking space for visitors. Their park is just a walking distance. The hospital keep clean and comfortable for the patients. The recovery room for overnight stay is good. The only thing is need a bit of visitors chair. I am guessing most recovery room due to short duration stay, the room is designed for patients and family. They don't want a party in the hospital due to many visitors.

100 Montaditos is actually 100 items of montaditos. It is the bun with the tapas item insert. This is new concept chain restaurant from Spain. The first store in the bay area is start at the Wire Grass Mall. We have been here two nights and finally I can gather the fact for this review.

I won't say I have tried each of items but I have enough for the general ideal of the concept. Although they have 100 different montaditos but their main ingredient as follow: Serrano ham, chorizo (sausage slice), salchichon (cure sausage), Lomo (dry cure pork-best item), Chistorra (basque sausage slice), tortilla, meatball, shrimp, tuna, philly steak, blue cheese, mozzarella, ground beef patty, hot dog, chicken, BBQ pull pork, garlic pork lion (one of the best), brie cheese, goat cheese, smoked salmon, anchovies. With this combination, they created the 95 items. The remaining 5 are the deserts. Although they have two different bun and the cost start at $1 to $3. The best pick are the Serrano ham, Lomo, Garlic Pork Lion. The manchego cheese is the 3 month cure cheese from Spain is also available. They have bigger platter such as calamari, croquette, and chicken wing. You also can order the cured meat alone.

For the visit, the new opening attracts lot of customer during the lunch and dinner time. When they don't have line, it is best to order as little as possible to keep the food warm. Then order the next item as you need. Every Wednesday all the montaditos is $1. I feel that we have too much bun by the time we have finish the meal. Although they are filling but do not give me the sensation as Tapas. The service is great. The team of the waiter and waitress is almost like the bee group that work around you.
